300#if !CLI11_HAS_CODECVT
302CLI11_INLINE void set_unicode_locale() {
303 static const std::array<const char *, 3> unicode_locales{{"C.UTF-8", "en_US.UTF-8", ".UTF-8"}};
304
305 for(const auto &locale_name : unicode_locales) {
306 if(std::setlocale(LC_ALL, locale_name) != nullptr) {
307 return;
308 }
309 }
310 throw std::runtime_error("CLI::narrow: could not set locale to C.UTF-8");
311}
312
313template <typename F> struct scope_guard_t {
314 F closure;
315
316 explicit scope_guard_t(F closure_) : closure(closure_) {}
317 ~scope_guard_t() { closure(); }
318};
319
320template <typename F> CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE scope_guard_t<F> scope_guard(F &&closure) {
321 return scope_guard_t<F>{std::forward<F>(closure)};
322}
323
324#endif // !CLI11_HAS_CODECVT
325
326CLI11_DIAGNOSTIC_PUSH
327CLI11_DIAGNOSTIC_IGNORE_DEPRECATED
328
329CLI11_INLINE std::string narrow_impl(const wchar_t *str, std::size_t str_size) {
330#if CLI11_HAS_CODECVT
331#ifdef _WIN32
332 return std::wstring_convert<std::codecvt_utf8_utf16<wchar_t>>().to_bytes(str, str + str_size);
333
334#else
335 return std::wstring_convert<std::codecvt_utf8<wchar_t>>().to_bytes(str, str + str_size);
336
337#endif // _WIN32
338#else // CLI11_HAS_CODECVT
339 (void)str_size;
340 std::mbstate_t state = std::mbstate_t();
341 const wchar_t *it = str;
342
343 std::string old_locale = std::setlocale(LC_ALL, nullptr);
344 auto sg = scope_guard([&] { std::setlocale(LC_ALL, old_locale.c_str()); });
345 set_unicode_locale();
346
347 std::size_t new_size = std::wcsrtombs(nullptr, &it, 0, &state);
348 if(new_size == static_cast<std::size_t>(-1)) {
349 throw std::runtime_error("CLI::narrow: conversion error in std::wcsrtombs at offset " +
350 std::to_string(it - str));
351 }
352 std::string result(new_size, '\0');
353 std::wcsrtombs(const_cast<char *>(result.data()), &str, new_size, &state);
354
355 return result;
356
357#endif // CLI11_HAS_CODECVT
358}
359
360CLI11_INLINE std::wstring widen_impl(const char *str, std::size_t str_size) {
361#if CLI11_HAS_CODECVT
362#ifdef _WIN32
363 return std::wstring_convert<std::codecvt_utf8_utf16<wchar_t>>().from_bytes(str, str + str_size);
364
365#else
366 return std::wstring_convert<std::codecvt_utf8<wchar_t>>().from_bytes(str, str + str_size);
367
368#endif // _WIN32
369#else // CLI11_HAS_CODECVT
370 (void)str_size;
371 std::mbstate_t state = std::mbstate_t();
372 const char *it = str;
373
374 std::string old_locale = std::setlocale(LC_ALL, nullptr);
375 auto sg = scope_guard([&] { std::setlocale(LC_ALL, old_locale.c_str()); });
376 set_unicode_locale();
377
378 std::size_t new_size = std::mbsrtowcs(nullptr, &it, 0, &state);
379 if(new_size == static_cast<std::size_t>(-1)) {
380 throw std::runtime_error("CLI::widen: conversion error in std::mbsrtowcs at offset " +
381 std::to_string(it - str));
382 }
383 std::wstring result(new_size, L'\0');
384 std::mbsrtowcs(const_cast<wchar_t *>(result.data()), &str, new_size, &state);
385
386 return result;
387
388#endif // CLI11_HAS_CODECVT
389}
390
391CLI11_DIAGNOSTIC_POP
392
393} // namespace detail

434namespace detail {
435
436#ifdef _WIN32
437CLI11_INLINE std::vector<std::string> compute_win32_argv() {
438 std::vector<std::string> result;
439 int argc = 0;
440
441 auto deleter = [](wchar_t **ptr) { LocalFree(ptr); };
442 // NOLINTBEGIN(*-avoid-c-arrays)
443 auto wargv = std::unique_ptr<wchar_t *[], decltype(deleter)>(CommandLineToArgvW(GetCommandLineW(), &argc), deleter);
444 // NOLINTEND(*-avoid-c-arrays)
445
446 if(wargv == nullptr) {
447 throw std::runtime_error("CommandLineToArgvW failed with code " + std::to_string(GetLastError()));
448 }
449
450 result.reserve(static_cast<size_t>(argc));
451 for(size_t i = 0; i < static_cast<size_t>(argc); ++i) {
452 result.push_back(narrow(wargv[i]));
453 }
454
455 return result;
456}
457#endif
458
459} // namespace detail

483constexpr int expected_max_vector_size{1 << 29};
484// Based on http://stackoverflow.com/questions/236129/split-a-string-in-c
486CLI11_INLINE std::vector<std::string> split(const std::string &s, char delim);
487
489template <typename T> std::string join(const T &v, std::string delim = ",") {
490 std::ostringstream s;
491 auto beg = std::begin(v);
492 auto end = std::end(v);
493 if(beg != end)
494 s << *beg++;
495 while(beg != end) {
496 s << delim << *beg++;
497 }
498 auto rval = s.str();
499 if(!rval.empty() && delim.size() == 1 && rval.back() == delim[0]) {
500 // remove trailing delimiter if the last entry was empty
501 rval.pop_back();
502 }
503 return rval;
504}
505
507template <typename T,
508 typename Callable,
509 typename = typename std::enable_if<!std::is_constructible<std::string, Callable>::value>::type>
510std::string join(const T &v, Callable func, std::string delim = ",") {
511 std::ostringstream s;
512 auto beg = std::begin(v);
513 auto end = std::end(v);
514 auto loc = s.tellp();
515 while(beg != end) {
516 auto nloc = s.tellp();
517 if(nloc > loc) {
518 s << delim;
519 loc = nloc;
520 }
521 s << func(*beg++);
522 }
523 return s.str();
524}
525
527template <typename T> std::string rjoin(const T &v, std::string delim = ",") {
528 std::ostringstream s;
529 for(std::size_t start = 0; start < v.size(); start++) {
530 if(start > 0)
531 s << delim;
532 s << v[v.size() - start - 1];
533 }
534 return s.str();
535}

586template <typename T> bool valid_first_char(T c) {
587 return ((c != '-') && (static_cast<unsigned char>(c) > 33)); // space and '!' not allowed
588}
589
591template <typename T> bool valid_later_char(T c) {
592 // = and : are value separators, { has special meaning for option defaults,
593 // and control codes other than tab would just be annoying to deal with in many places allowing space here has too
594 // much potential for inadvertent entry errors and bugs
595 return ((c != '=') && (c != ':') && (c != '{') && ((static_cast<unsigned char>(c) > 32) || c == '\t'));
596}

602inline bool valid_alias_name_string(const std::string &str) {
603 static const std::string badChars(std::string("\n") + '\0');
604 return (str.find_first_of(badChars) == std::string::npos);
605}

608inline bool is_separator(const std::string &str) {
609 static const std::string sep("%%");
610 return (str.empty() || str == sep);
611}
612
614inline bool isalpha(const std::string &str) {
615 return std::all_of(str.begin(), str.end(), [](char c) { return std::isalpha(c, std::locale()); });
616}
617
619inline std::string to_lower(std::string str) {
620 std::transform(std::begin(str), std::end(str), std::begin(str), [](const std::string::value_type &x) {
621 return std::tolower(x, std::locale());
622 });
623 return str;
624}
625
627inline std::string remove_underscore(std::string str) {
628 str.erase(std::remove(std::begin(str), std::end(str), '_'), std::end(str));
629 return str;
630}

650template <typename Callable> inline std::string find_and_modify(std::string str, std::string trigger, Callable modify) {
651 std::size_t start_pos = 0;
652 while((start_pos = str.find(trigger, start_pos)) != std::string::npos) {
653 start_pos = modify(str, start_pos);
654 }
655 return str;
656}

712namespace detail {
713CLI11_INLINE std::vector<std::string> split(const std::string &s, char delim) {
714 std::vector<std::string> elems;
715 // Check to see if empty string, give consistent result
716 if(s.empty()) {
717 elems.emplace_back();
718 } else {
719 std::stringstream ss;
720 ss.str(s);
721 std::string item;
722 while(std::getline(ss, item, delim)) {
723 elems.push_back(item);
724 }
725 }
726 return elems;
727}
728
729CLI11_INLINE std::string &ltrim(std::string &str) {
730 auto it = std::find_if(str.begin(), str.end(), [](char ch) { return !std::isspace<char>(ch, std::locale()); });
731 str.erase(str.begin(), it);
732 return str;
733}
734
735CLI11_INLINE std::string &ltrim(std::string &str, const std::string &filter) {
736 auto it = std::find_if(str.begin(), str.end(), [&filter](char ch) { return filter.find(ch) == std::string::npos; });
737 str.erase(str.begin(), it);
738 return str;
739}
740
741CLI11_INLINE std::string &rtrim(std::string &str) {
742 auto it = std::find_if(str.rbegin(), str.rend(), [](char ch) { return !std::isspace<char>(ch, std::locale()); });
743 str.erase(it.base(), str.end());
744 return str;
745}
746
747CLI11_INLINE std::string &rtrim(std::string &str, const std::string &filter) {
748 auto it =
749 std::find_if(str.rbegin(), str.rend(), [&filter](char ch) { return filter.find(ch) == std::string::npos; });
750 str.erase(it.base(), str.end());
751 return str;
752}
753
754CLI11_INLINE std::string &remove_quotes(std::string &str) {
755 if(str.length() > 1 && (str.front() == '"' || str.front() == '\'' || str.front() == '`')) {
756 if(str.front() == str.back()) {
757 str.pop_back();
758 str.erase(str.begin(), str.begin() + 1);
759 }
760 }
761 return str;
762}
763
764CLI11_INLINE std::string &remove_outer(std::string &str, char key) {
765 if(str.length() > 1 && (str.front() == key)) {
766 if(str.front() == str.back()) {
767 str.pop_back();
768 str.erase(str.begin(), str.begin() + 1);
769 }
770 }
771 return str;
772}
773
774CLI11_INLINE std::string fix_newlines(const std::string &leader, std::string input) {
775 std::string::size_type n = 0;
776 while(n != std::string::npos && n < input.size()) {
777 n = input.find('\n', n);
778 if(n != std::string::npos) {
779 input = input.substr(0, n + 1) + leader + input.substr(n + 1);
780 n += leader.size();
781 }
782 }
783 return input;
784}
785
786CLI11_INLINE std::ostream &format_aliases(std::ostream &out, const std::vector<std::string> &aliases, std::size_t wid) {
787 if(!aliases.empty()) {
788 out << std::setw(static_cast<int>(wid)) << " aliases: ";
789 bool front = true;
790 for(const auto &alias : aliases) {
791 if(!front) {
792 out << ", ";
793 } else {
794 front = false;
795 }
796 out << detail::fix_newlines(" ", alias);
797 }
798 out << "\n";
799 }
800 return out;
801}
802
803CLI11_INLINE bool valid_name_string(const std::string &str) {
804 if(str.empty() || !valid_first_char(str[0])) {
805 return false;
806 }
807 auto e = str.end();
808 for(auto c = str.begin() + 1; c != e; ++c)
809 if(!valid_later_char(*c))
810 return false;
811 return true;
812}
813
814CLI11_INLINE std::string find_and_replace(std::string str, std::string from, std::string to) {
815
816 std::size_t start_pos = 0;
817
818 while((start_pos = str.find(from, start_pos)) != std::string::npos) {
819 str.replace(start_pos, from.length(), to);
820 start_pos += to.length();
821 }
822
823 return str;
824}
825
826CLI11_INLINE void remove_default_flag_values(std::string &flags) {
827 auto loc = flags.find_first_of('{', 2);
828 while(loc != std::string::npos) {
829 auto finish = flags.find_first_of("},", loc + 1);
830 if((finish != std::string::npos) && (flags[finish] == '}')) {
831 flags.erase(flags.begin() + static_cast<std::ptrdiff_t>(loc),
832 flags.begin() + static_cast<std::ptrdiff_t>(finish) + 1);
833 }
834 loc = flags.find_first_of('{', loc + 1);
835 }
836 flags.erase(std::remove(flags.begin(), flags.end(), '!'), flags.end());
837}
838
839CLI11_INLINE std::ptrdiff_t
840find_member(std::string name, const std::vector<std::string> names, bool ignore_case, bool ignore_underscore) {
841 auto it = std::end(names);
842 if(ignore_case) {
843 if(ignore_underscore) {
844 name = detail::to_lower(detail::remove_underscore(name));
845 it = std::find_if(std::begin(names), std::end(names), [&name](std::string local_name) {
846 return detail::to_lower(detail::remove_underscore(local_name)) == name;
847 });
848 } else {
849 name = detail::to_lower(name);
850 it = std::find_if(std::begin(names), std::end(names), [&name](std::string local_name) {
851 return detail::to_lower(local_name) == name;
852 });
853 }
854
855 } else if(ignore_underscore) {
856 name = detail::remove_underscore(name);
857 it = std::find_if(std::begin(names), std::end(names), [&name](std::string local_name) {
858 return detail::remove_underscore(local_name) == name;
859 });
860 } else {
861 it = std::find(std::begin(names), std::end(names), name);
862 }
863
864 return (it != std::end(names)) ? (it - std::begin(names)) : (-1);
865}
866
867static const std::string escapedChars("\b\t\n\f\r\"\\");
868static const std::string escapedCharsCode("btnfr\"\\");
869static const std::string bracketChars{"\"'`[(<{"};
870static const std::string matchBracketChars("\"'`])>}");
871
872CLI11_INLINE bool has_escapable_character(const std::string &str) {
873 return (str.find_first_of(escapedChars) != std::string::npos);
874}
875
876CLI11_INLINE std::string add_escaped_characters(const std::string &str) {
877 std::string out;
878 out.reserve(str.size() + 4);
879 for(char s : str) {
880 auto sloc = escapedChars.find_first_of(s);
881 if(sloc != std::string::npos) {
882 out.push_back('\\');
883 out.push_back(escapedCharsCode[sloc]);
884 } else {
885 out.push_back(s);
886 }
887 }
888 return out;
889}
890
891CLI11_INLINE std::uint32_t hexConvert(char hc) {
892 int hcode{0};
893 if(hc >= '0' && hc <= '9') {
894 hcode = (hc - '0');
895 } else if(hc >= 'A' && hc <= 'F') {
896 hcode = (hc - 'A' + 10);
897 } else if(hc >= 'a' && hc <= 'f') {
898 hcode = (hc - 'a' + 10);
899 } else {
900 hcode = -1;
901 }
902 return static_cast<uint32_t>(hcode);
903}
904
905CLI11_INLINE char make_char(std::uint32_t code) { return static_cast<char>(static_cast<unsigned char>(code)); }
906
907CLI11_INLINE void append_codepoint(std::string &str, std::uint32_t code) {
908 if(code < 0x80) { // ascii code equivalent
909 str.push_back(static_cast<char>(code));
910 } else if(code < 0x800) { // \u0080 to \u07FF
911 // 110yyyyx 10xxxxxx; 0x3f == 0b0011'1111
912 str.push_back(make_char(0xC0 | code >> 6));
913 str.push_back(make_char(0x80 | (code & 0x3F)));
914 } else if(code < 0x10000) { // U+0800...U+FFFF
915 if(0xD800 <= code && code <= 0xDFFF) {
916 throw std::invalid_argument("[0xD800, 0xDFFF] are not valid UTF-8.");
917 }
918 // 1110yyyy 10yxxxxx 10xxxxxx
919 str.push_back(make_char(0xE0 | code >> 12));
920 str.push_back(make_char(0x80 | (code >> 6 & 0x3F)));
921 str.push_back(make_char(0x80 | (code & 0x3F)));
922 } else if(code < 0x110000) { // U+010000 ... U+10FFFF
923 // 11110yyy 10yyxxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
924 str.push_back(make_char(0xF0 | code >> 18));
925 str.push_back(make_char(0x80 | (code >> 12 & 0x3F)));
926 str.push_back(make_char(0x80 | (code >> 6 & 0x3F)));
927 str.push_back(make_char(0x80 | (code & 0x3F)));
928 }
929}
930
931CLI11_INLINE std::string remove_escaped_characters(const std::string &str) {
932
933 std::string out;
934 out.reserve(str.size());
935 for(auto loc = str.begin(); loc < str.end(); ++loc) {
936 if(*loc == '\\') {
937 if(str.end() - loc < 2) {
938 throw std::invalid_argument("invalid escape sequence " + str);
939 }
940 auto ecloc = escapedCharsCode.find_first_of(*(loc + 1));
941 if(ecloc != std::string::npos) {
942 out.push_back(escapedChars[ecloc]);
943 ++loc;
944 } else if(*(loc + 1) == 'u') {
945 // must have 4 hex characters
946 if(str.end() - loc < 6) {
947 throw std::invalid_argument("unicode sequence must have 4 hex codes " + str);
948 }
949 std::uint32_t code{0};
950 std::uint32_t mplier{16 * 16 * 16};
951 for(int ii = 2; ii < 6; ++ii) {
952 std::uint32_t res = hexConvert(*(loc + ii));
953 if(res > 0x0F) {
954 throw std::invalid_argument("unicode sequence must have 4 hex codes " + str);
955 }
956 code += res * mplier;
957 mplier = mplier / 16;
958 }
959 append_codepoint(out, code);
960 loc += 5;
961 } else if(*(loc + 1) == 'U') {
962 // must have 8 hex characters
963 if(str.end() - loc < 10) {
964 throw std::invalid_argument("unicode sequence must have 8 hex codes " + str);
965 }
966 std::uint32_t code{0};
967 std::uint32_t mplier{16 * 16 * 16 * 16 * 16 * 16 * 16};
968 for(int ii = 2; ii < 10; ++ii) {
969 std::uint32_t res = hexConvert(*(loc + ii));
970 if(res > 0x0F) {
971 throw std::invalid_argument("unicode sequence must have 8 hex codes " + str);
972 }
973 code += res * mplier;
974 mplier = mplier / 16;
975 }
976 append_codepoint(out, code);
977 loc += 9;
978 } else if(*(loc + 1) == '0') {
979 out.push_back('\0');
980 ++loc;
981 } else {
982 throw std::invalid_argument(std::string("unrecognized escape sequence \\") + *(loc + 1) + " in " + str);
983 }
984 } else {
985 out.push_back(*loc);
986 }
987 }
988 return out;
989}
990
991CLI11_INLINE std::size_t close_string_quote(const std::string &str, std::size_t start, char closure_char) {
992 std::size_t loc{0};
993 for(loc = start + 1; loc < str.size(); ++loc) {
994 if(str[loc] == closure_char) {
995 break;
996 }
997 if(str[loc] == '\\') {
998 // skip the next character for escaped sequences
999 ++loc;
1000 }
1001 }
1002 return loc;
1003}
1004
1005CLI11_INLINE std::size_t close_literal_quote(const std::string &str, std::size_t start, char closure_char) {
1006 auto loc = str.find_first_of(closure_char, start + 1);
1007 return (loc != std::string::npos ? loc : str.size());
1008}
1009
1010CLI11_INLINE std::size_t close_sequence(const std::string &str, std::size_t start, char closure_char) {
1011
1012 auto bracket_loc = matchBracketChars.find(closure_char);
1013 switch(bracket_loc) {
1014 case 0:
1015 return close_string_quote(str, start, closure_char);
1016 case 1:
1017 case 2:
1018 case std::string::npos:
1019 return close_literal_quote(str, start, closure_char);
1020 default:
1021 break;
1022 }
1023
1024 std::string closures(1, closure_char);
1025 auto loc = start + 1;
1026
1027 while(loc < str.size()) {
1028 if(str[loc] == closures.back()) {
1029 closures.pop_back();
1030 if(closures.empty()) {
1031 return loc;
1032 }
1033 }
1034 bracket_loc = bracketChars.find(str[loc]);
1035 if(bracket_loc != std::string::npos) {
1036 switch(bracket_loc) {
1037 case 0:
1038 loc = close_string_quote(str, loc, str[loc]);
1039 break;
1040 case 1:
1041 case 2:
1042 loc = close_literal_quote(str, loc, str[loc]);
1043 break;
1044 default:
1045 closures.push_back(matchBracketChars[bracket_loc]);
1046 break;
1047 }
1048 }
1049 ++loc;
1050 }
1051 if(loc > str.size()) {
1052 loc = str.size();
1053 }
1054 return loc;
1055}
1056
1057CLI11_INLINE std::vector<std::string> split_up(std::string str, char delimiter) {
1058
1059 auto find_ws = [delimiter](char ch) {
1060 return (delimiter == '\0') ? std::isspace<char>(ch, std::locale()) : (ch == delimiter);
1061 };
1062 trim(str);
1063
1064 std::vector<std::string> output;
1065 while(!str.empty()) {
1066 if(bracketChars.find_first_of(str[0]) != std::string::npos) {
1067 auto bracketLoc = bracketChars.find_first_of(str[0]);
1068 auto end = close_sequence(str, 0, matchBracketChars[bracketLoc]);
1069 if(end >= str.size()) {
1070 output.push_back(std::move(str));
1071 str.clear();
1072 } else {
1073 output.push_back(str.substr(0, end + 1));
1074 if(end + 2 < str.size()) {
1075 str = str.substr(end + 2);
1076 } else {
1077 str.clear();
1078 }
1079 }
1080
1081 } else {
1082 auto it = std::find_if(std::begin(str), std::end(str), find_ws);
1083 if(it != std::end(str)) {
1084 std::string value = std::string(str.begin(), it);
1085 output.push_back(value);
1086 str = std::string(it + 1, str.end());
1087 } else {
1088 output.push_back(str);
1089 str.clear();
1090 }
1091 }
1092 trim(str);
1093 }
1094 return output;
1095}
1096
1097CLI11_INLINE std::size_t escape_detect(std::string &str, std::size_t offset) {
1098 auto next = str[offset + 1];
1099 if((next == '\"') || (next == '\'') || (next == '`')) {
1100 auto astart = str.find_last_of("-/ \"\'`", offset - 1);
1101 if(astart != std::string::npos) {
1102 if(str[astart] == ((str[offset] == '=') ? '-' : '/'))
1103 str[offset] = ' '; // interpret this as a space so the split_up works properly
1104 }
1105 }
1106 return offset + 1;
1107}
1108
1109CLI11_INLINE std::string binary_escape_string(const std::string &string_to_escape) {
1110 // s is our escaped output string
1111 std::string escaped_string{};
1112 // loop through all characters
1113 for(char c : string_to_escape) {
1114 // check if a given character is printable
1115 // the cast is necessary to avoid undefined behaviour
1116 if(isprint(static_cast<unsigned char>(c)) == 0) {
1117 std::stringstream stream;
1118 // if the character is not printable
1119 // we'll convert it to a hex string using a stringstream
1120 // note that since char is signed we have to cast it to unsigned first
1121 stream << std::hex << static_cast<unsigned int>(static_cast<unsigned char>(c));
1122 std::string code = stream.str();
1123 escaped_string += std::string("\\x") + (code.size() < 2 ? "0" : "") + code;
1124 } else if(c == 'x' || c == 'X') {
1125 // need to check for inadvertent binary sequences
1126 if(!escaped_string.empty() && escaped_string.back() == '\\') {
1127 escaped_string += std::string("\\x") + (c == 'x' ? "78" : "58");
1128 } else {
1129 escaped_string.push_back(c);
1130 }
1131
1132 } else {
1133 escaped_string.push_back(c);
1134 }
1135 }
1136 if(escaped_string != string_to_escape) {
1137 auto sqLoc = escaped_string.find('\'');
1138 while(sqLoc != std::string::npos) {
1139 escaped_string[sqLoc] = '\\';
1140 escaped_string.insert(sqLoc + 1, "x27");
1141 sqLoc = escaped_string.find('\'');
1142 }
1143 escaped_string.insert(0, "'B\"(");
1144 escaped_string.push_back(')');
1145 escaped_string.push_back('"');
1146 escaped_string.push_back('\'');
1147 }
1148 return escaped_string;
1149}
1150
1151CLI11_INLINE bool is_binary_escaped_string(const std::string &escaped_string) {
1152 size_t ssize = escaped_string.size();
1153 if(escaped_string.compare(0, 3, "B\"(") == 0 && escaped_string.compare(ssize - 2, 2, ")\"") == 0) {
1154 return true;
1155 }
1156 return (escaped_string.compare(0, 4, "'B\"(") == 0 && escaped_string.compare(ssize - 3, 3, ")\"'") == 0);
1157}
1158
1159CLI11_INLINE std::string extract_binary_string(const std::string &escaped_string) {
1160 std::size_t start{0};
1161 std::size_t tail{0};
1162 size_t ssize = escaped_string.size();
1163 if(escaped_string.compare(0, 3, "B\"(") == 0 && escaped_string.compare(ssize - 2, 2, ")\"") == 0) {
1164 start = 3;
1165 tail = 2;
1166 } else if(escaped_string.compare(0, 4, "'B\"(") == 0 && escaped_string.compare(ssize - 3, 3, ")\"'") == 0) {
1167 start = 4;
1168 tail = 3;
1169 }
1170
1171 if(start == 0) {
1172 return escaped_string;
1173 }
1174 std::string outstring;
1175
1176 outstring.reserve(ssize - start - tail);
1177 std::size_t loc = start;
1178 while(loc < ssize - tail) {
1179 // ssize-2 to skip )" at the end
1180 if(escaped_string[loc] == '\\' && (escaped_string[loc + 1] == 'x' || escaped_string[loc + 1] == 'X')) {
1181 auto c1 = escaped_string[loc + 2];
1182 auto c2 = escaped_string[loc + 3];
1183
1184 std::uint32_t res1 = hexConvert(c1);
1185 std::uint32_t res2 = hexConvert(c2);
1186 if(res1 <= 0x0F && res2 <= 0x0F) {
1187 loc += 4;
1188 outstring.push_back(static_cast<char>(res1 * 16 + res2));
1189 continue;
1190 }
1191 }
1192 outstring.push_back(escaped_string[loc]);
1193 ++loc;
1194 }
1195 return outstring;
1196}
1197
1198CLI11_INLINE void remove_quotes(std::vector<std::string> &args) {
1199 for(auto &arg : args) {
1200 if(arg.front() == '\"' && arg.back() == '\"') {
1201 remove_quotes(arg);
1202 // only remove escaped for string arguments not literal strings
1203 arg = remove_escaped_characters(arg);
1204 } else {
1205 remove_quotes(arg);
1206 }
1207 }
1208}
1209
1210CLI11_INLINE void handle_secondary_array(std::string &str) {
1211 if(str.size() >= 2 && str.front() == '[' && str.back() == ']') {
1212 // handle some special array processing for arguments if it might be interpreted as a secondary array
1213 std::string tstr{"[["};
1214 for(std::size_t ii = 1; ii < str.size(); ++ii) {
1215 tstr.push_back(str[ii]);
1216 tstr.push_back(str[ii]);
1217 }
1218 str = std::move(tstr);
1219 }
1220}
1221
1222CLI11_INLINE bool process_quoted_string(std::string &str, char string_char, char literal_char) {
1223 if(str.size() <= 1) {
1224 return false;
1225 }
1226 if(detail::is_binary_escaped_string(str)) {
1227 str = detail::extract_binary_string(str);
1228 handle_secondary_array(str);
1229 return true;
1230 }
1231 if(str.front() == string_char && str.back() == string_char) {
1232 detail::remove_outer(str, string_char);
1233 if(str.find_first_of('\\') != std::string::npos) {
1234 str = detail::remove_escaped_characters(str);
1235 }
1236 handle_secondary_array(str);
1237 return true;
1238 }
1239 if((str.front() == literal_char || str.front() == '`') && str.back() == str.front()) {
1240 detail::remove_outer(str, str.front());
1241 handle_secondary_array(str);
1242 return true;
1243 }
1244 return false;
1245}
1246
1247std::string get_environment_value(const std::string &env_name) {
1248 char *buffer = nullptr;
1249 std::string ename_string;
1250
1251#ifdef _MSC_VER
1252 // Windows version
1253 std::size_t sz = 0;
1254 if(_dupenv_s(&buffer, &sz, env_name.c_str()) == 0 && buffer != nullptr) {
1255 ename_string = std::string(buffer);
1256 free(buffer);
1257 }
1258#else
1259 // This also works on Windows, but gives a warning
1260 buffer = std::getenv(env_name.c_str());
1261 if(buffer != nullptr) {
1262 ename_string = std::string(buffer);
1263 }
1264#endif
1265 return ename_string;
1266}
1267
1268CLI11_INLINE std::ostream &streamOutAsParagraph(std::ostream &out,
1269 const std::string &text,
1270 std::size_t paragraphWidth,
1271 const std::string &linePrefix,
1272 bool skipPrefixOnFirstLine) {
1273 if(!skipPrefixOnFirstLine)
1274 out << linePrefix; // First line prefix
1275
1276 std::istringstream lss(text);
1277 std::string line = "";
1278 while(std::getline(lss, line)) {
1279 std::istringstream iss(line);
1280 std::string word = "";
1281 std::size_t charsWritten = 0;
1282
1283 while(iss >> word) {
1284 if(word.length() + charsWritten > paragraphWidth) {
1285 out << '\n' << linePrefix;
1286 charsWritten = 0;
1287 }
1288
1289 out << word << " ";
1290 charsWritten += word.length() + 1;
1291 }
1292
1293 if(!lss.eof())
1294 out << '\n' << linePrefix;
1295 }
1296 return out;
1297}

1303// Use one of these on all error classes.
1304// These are temporary and are undef'd at the end of this file.
1305#define CLI11_ERROR_DEF(parent, name) \
1306 protected: \
1307 name(std::string ename, std::string msg, int exit_code) : parent(std::move(ename), std::move(msg), exit_code) {} \
1308 name(std::string ename, std::string msg, ExitCodes exit_code) \
1309 : parent(std::move(ename), std::move(msg), exit_code) {} \
1310 \
1311 public: \
1312 name(std::string msg, ExitCodes exit_code) : parent(#name, std::move(msg), exit_code) {} \
1313 name(std::string msg, int exit_code) : parent(#name, std::move(msg), exit_code) {}
1314
1315// This is added after the one above if a class is used directly and builds its own message
1316#define CLI11_ERROR_SIMPLE(name) \
1317 explicit name(std::string msg) : name(#name, msg, ExitCodes::name) {}

1350class Error : public std::runtime_error {
1351 int actual_exit_code;
1352 std::string error_name{"Error"};
1353
1354 public:
1355 CLI11_NODISCARD int get_exit_code() const { return actual_exit_code; }
1356
1357 CLI11_NODISCARD std::string get_name() const { return error_name; }
1358
1359 Error(std::string name, std::string msg, int exit_code = static_cast<int>(ExitCodes::BaseClass))
1360 : runtime_error(msg), actual_exit_code(exit_code), error_name(std::move(name)) {}
1361
1362 Error(std::string name, std::string msg, ExitCodes exit_code) : Error(name, msg, static_cast<int>(exit_code)) {}
1363};
1364

1505class RequiredError : public ParseError {
1506 CLI11_ERROR_DEF(ParseError, RequiredError)
1507 explicit RequiredError(std::string name) : RequiredError(name + " is required", ExitCodes::RequiredError) {}
1508 static RequiredError Subcommand(std::size_t min_subcom) {
1509 if(min_subcom == 1) {
1510 return RequiredError("A subcommand");
1511 }
1512 return {"Requires at least " + std::to_string(min_subcom) + " subcommands", ExitCodes::RequiredError};
1513 }
1514 static RequiredError
1515 Option(std::size_t min_option, std::size_t max_option, std::size_t used, const std::string &option_list) {
1516 if((min_option == 1) && (max_option == 1) && (used == 0))
1517 return RequiredError("Exactly 1 option from [" + option_list + "]");
1518 if((min_option == 1) && (max_option == 1) && (used > 1)) {
1519 return {"Exactly 1 option from [" + option_list + "] is required but " + std::to_string(used) +
1520 " were given",
1521 ExitCodes::RequiredError};
1522 }
1523 if((min_option == 1) && (used == 0))
1524 return RequiredError("At least 1 option from [" + option_list + "]");
1525 if(used < min_option) {
1526 return {"Requires at least " + std::to_string(min_option) + " options used but only " +
1527 std::to_string(used) + " were given from [" + option_list + "]",
1528 ExitCodes::RequiredError};
1529 }
1530 if(max_option == 1)
1531 return {"Requires at most 1 options be given from [" + option_list + "]", ExitCodes::RequiredError};
1532
1533 return {"Requires at most " + std::to_string(max_option) + " options be used but " + std::to_string(used) +
1534 " were given from [" + option_list + "]",
1535 ExitCodes::RequiredError};
1536 }
1537};
1538
1540class ArgumentMismatch : public ParseError {
1541 CLI11_ERROR_DEF(ParseError, ArgumentMismatch)
1542 CLI11_ERROR_SIMPLE(ArgumentMismatch)
1543 ArgumentMismatch(std::string name, int expected, std::size_t received)
1544 : ArgumentMismatch(expected > 0 ? ("Expected exactly " + std::to_string(expected) + " arguments to " + name +
1545 ", got " + std::to_string(received))
1546 : ("Expected at least " + std::to_string(-expected) + " arguments to " + name +
1547 ", got " + std::to_string(received)),
1548 ExitCodes::ArgumentMismatch) {}
1549
1550 static ArgumentMismatch AtLeast(std::string name, int num, std::size_t received) {
1551 return ArgumentMismatch(name + ": At least " + std::to_string(num) + " required but received " +
1552 std::to_string(received));
1553 }
1554 static ArgumentMismatch AtMost(std::string name, int num, std::size_t received) {
1555 return ArgumentMismatch(name + ": At Most " + std::to_string(num) + " required but received " +
1556 std::to_string(received));
1557 }
1558 static ArgumentMismatch TypedAtLeast(std::string name, int num, std::string type) {
1559 return ArgumentMismatch(name + ": " + std::to_string(num) + " required " + type + " missing");
1560 }
1561 static ArgumentMismatch FlagOverride(std::string name) {
1562 return ArgumentMismatch(name + " was given a disallowed flag override");
1563 }
1564 static ArgumentMismatch PartialType(std::string name, int num, std::string type) {
1565 return ArgumentMismatch(name + ": " + type + " only partially specified: " + std::to_string(num) +
1566 " required for each element");
1567 }
1568};

1658template <bool B, class T = void> using enable_if_t = typename std::enable_if<B, T>::type;

1688 static bool const value = is_shared_ptr<T>::value || std::is_pointer<T>::value;
1689};

1707template <typename T, typename S = std::string> class is_lexical_castable {
1708 template <typename TT, typename SS>
1709 static auto test(int) -> decltype(lexical_cast(std::declval<const SS &>(), std::declval<TT &>()), std::true_type());
1710
1711 template <typename, typename> static auto test(...) -> std::false_type;
1712
1713 public:
1714 static constexpr bool value = decltype(test<T, S>(0))::value;
1715};
1716} // namespace adl_detail

1727 using type = T;
1728};

1730template <typename T> struct element_type<T, typename std::enable_if<is_copyable_ptr<T>::value>::type> {
1731 using type = typename std::pointer_traits<T>::element_type;

1741template <typename T, typename _ = void> struct pair_adaptor : std::false_type {
1742 using value_type = typename T::value_type;
1743 using first_type = typename std::remove_const<value_type>::type;
1744 using second_type = typename std::remove_const<value_type>::type;
1745
1747 template <typename Q> static auto first(Q &&pair_value) -> decltype(std::forward<Q>(pair_value)) {
1748 return std::forward<Q>(pair_value);
1749 }
1750
1751 template <typename Q> static auto second(Q &&pair_value) -> decltype(std::forward<Q>(pair_value)) {
1752 return std::forward<Q>(pair_value);
1753 }
1754};
1755
1758template <typename T>
1759struct pair_adaptor<
1760 T,
1761 conditional_t<false, void_t<typename T::value_type::first_type, typename T::value_type::second_type>, void>>
1762 : std::true_type {
1763 using value_type = typename T::value_type;
1764 using first_type = typename std::remove_const<typename value_type::first_type>::type;
1765 using second_type = typename std::remove_const<typename value_type::second_type>::type;
1766
1768 template <typename Q> static auto first(Q &&pair_value) -> decltype(std::get<0>(std::forward<Q>(pair_value))) {
1769 return std::get<0>(std::forward<Q>(pair_value));
1770 }
1771
1772 template <typename Q> static auto second(Q &&pair_value) -> decltype(std::get<1>(std::forward<Q>(pair_value))) {
1773 return std::get<1>(std::forward<Q>(pair_value));
1774 }
1775};

1777// Warning is suppressed due to "bug" in gcc<5.0 and gcc 7.0 with c++17 enabled that generates a -Wnarrowing warning
1778// in the unevaluated context even if the function that was using this wasn't used. The standard says narrowing in
1779// brace initialization shouldn't be allowed but for backwards compatibility gcc allows it in some contexts. It is a
1780// little fuzzy what happens in template constructs and I think that was something GCC took a little while to work out.
1781// But regardless some versions of gcc generate a warning when they shouldn't from the following code so that should be
1782// suppressed
1783#ifdef __GNUC__
1784#pragma GCC diagnostic push
1785#pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wnarrowing"
1786#endif
1787// check for constructibility from a specific type and copy assignable used in the parse detection
1788template <typename T, typename C> class is_direct_constructible {
1789 template <typename TT, typename CC>
1790 static auto test(int, std::true_type) -> decltype(
1791// NVCC warns about narrowing conversions here
1792#ifdef __CUDACC__
1793#ifdef __NVCC_DIAG_PRAGMA_SUPPORT__
1794#pragma nv_diag_suppress 2361
1795#else
1796#pragma diag_suppress 2361
1797#endif
1798#endif
1799 TT{std::declval<CC>()}
1800#ifdef __CUDACC__
1801#ifdef __NVCC_DIAG_PRAGMA_SUPPORT__
1802#pragma nv_diag_default 2361
1803#else
1804#pragma diag_default 2361
1805#endif
1806#endif
1807 ,
1808 std::is_move_assignable<TT>());
1809
1810 template <typename TT, typename CC> static auto test(int, std::false_type) -> std::false_type;
1811
1812 template <typename, typename> static auto test(...) -> std::false_type;
1813
1814 public:
1815 static constexpr bool value = decltype(test<T, C>(0, typename std::is_constructible<T, C>::type()))::value;
1816};
1817#ifdef __GNUC__
1818#pragma GCC diagnostic pop
1819#endif

1821// Check for output streamability
1822// Based on https://stackoverflow.com/questions/22758291/how-can-i-detect-if-a-type-can-be-streamed-to-an-stdostream
1823
1824template <typename T, typename S = std::ostringstream> class is_ostreamable {
1825 template <typename TT, typename SS>
1826 static auto test(int) -> decltype(std::declval<SS &>() << std::declval<TT>(), std::true_type());
1827
1828 template <typename, typename> static auto test(...) -> std::false_type;
1829
1830 public:
1831 static constexpr bool value = decltype(test<T, S>(0))::value;
1832};
1833
1835template <typename T, typename S = std::istringstream> class is_istreamable {
1836 template <typename TT, typename SS>
1837 static auto test(int) -> decltype(std::declval<SS &>() >> std::declval<TT &>(), std::true_type());
1838
1839 template <typename, typename> static auto test(...) -> std::false_type;
1840
1841 public:
1842 static constexpr bool value = decltype(test<T, S>(0))::value;
1843};
1844
1846template <typename T> class is_complex {
1847 template <typename TT>
1848 static auto test(int) -> decltype(std::declval<TT>().real(), std::declval<TT>().imag(), std::true_type());
1849
1850 template <typename> static auto test(...) -> std::false_type;
1851
1852 public:
1853 static constexpr bool value = decltype(test<T>(0))::value;
1854};
1855
1857template <typename T, enable_if_t<is_istreamable<T>::value, detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
1858bool from_stream(const std::string &istring, T &obj) {
1859 std::istringstream is;
1860 is.str(istring);
1861 is >> obj;
1862 return !is.fail() && !is.rdbuf()->in_avail();
1863}
1864
1865template <typename T, enable_if_t<!is_istreamable<T>::value, detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
1866bool from_stream(const std::string & /*istring*/, T & /*obj*/) {
1867 return false;
1868}

1870// check to see if an object is a mutable container (fail by default)
1871template <typename T, typename _ = void> struct is_mutable_container : std::false_type {};
1872
1876template <typename T>
1877struct is_mutable_container<
1878 T,
1879 conditional_t<false,
1880 void_t<typename T::value_type,
1881 decltype(std::declval<T>().end()),
1882 decltype(std::declval<T>().clear()),
1883 decltype(std::declval<T>().insert(std::declval<decltype(std::declval<T>().end())>(),
1884 std::declval<const typename T::value_type &>()))>,
1885 void>> : public conditional_t<std::is_constructible<T, std::string>::value ||
1886 std::is_constructible<T, std::wstring>::value,
1887 std::false_type,
1888 std::true_type> {};
1889
1890// check to see if an object is a mutable container (fail by default)
1891template <typename T, typename _ = void> struct is_readable_container : std::false_type {};
1892
1895template <typename T>
1896struct is_readable_container<
1897 T,
1898 conditional_t<false, void_t<decltype(std::declval<T>().end()), decltype(std::declval<T>().begin())>, void>>
1899 : public std::true_type {};
1900
1901// check to see if an object is a wrapper (fail by default)
1902template <typename T, typename _ = void> struct is_wrapper : std::false_type {};
1903
1904// check if an object is a wrapper (it has a value_type defined)
1905template <typename T>
1906struct is_wrapper<T, conditional_t<false, void_t<typename T::value_type>, void>> : public std::true_type {};
1907
1908// Check for tuple like types, as in classes with a tuple_size type trait
1909// Even though in C++26 std::complex gains a std::tuple interface, for our purposes we treat is as NOT a tuple
1910template <typename S> class is_tuple_like {
1911 template <typename SS, enable_if_t<!is_complex<SS>::value, detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
1912 // static auto test(int)
1913 // -> decltype(std::conditional<(std::tuple_size<SS>::value > 0), std::true_type, std::false_type>::type());
1914 static auto test(int) -> decltype(std::tuple_size<typename std::decay<SS>::type>::value, std::true_type{});
1915 template <typename> static auto test(...) -> std::false_type;
1916
1917 public:
1918 static constexpr bool value = decltype(test<S>(0))::value;
1919};
1920
1922template <typename T, typename Enable = void> struct type_count_base {
1923 static const int value{0};
1924};
1925
1927template <typename T>
1928struct type_count_base<T,
1929 typename std::enable_if<!is_tuple_like<T>::value && !is_mutable_container<T>::value &&
1930 !std::is_void<T>::value>::type> {
1931 static constexpr int value{1};
1932};
1933
1935template <typename T>
1936struct type_count_base<T, typename std::enable_if<is_tuple_like<T>::value && !is_mutable_container<T>::value>::type> {
1937 static constexpr int value{// cppcheck-suppress unusedStructMember
1938 std::tuple_size<typename std::decay<T>::type>::value};
1939};
1940
1942template <typename T> struct type_count_base<T, typename std::enable_if<is_mutable_container<T>::value>::type> {
1943 static constexpr int value{type_count_base<typename T::value_type>::value};
1944};

1947template <typename T, enable_if_t<std::is_convertible<T, std::string>::value, detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
1948auto to_string(T &&value) -> decltype(std::forward<T>(value)) {
1949 return std::forward<T>(value);
1950}
1951
1953template <typename T,
1954 enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<std::string, T>::value && !std::is_convertible<T, std::string>::value,
1955 detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
1956std::string to_string(T &&value) {
1957 return std::string(value); // NOLINT(google-readability-casting)
1958}
1959
1961template <typename T,
1962 enable_if_t<!std::is_convertible<T, std::string>::value && !std::is_constructible<std::string, T>::value &&
1963 is_ostreamable<T>::value,
1964 detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
1965std::string to_string(T &&value) {
1966 std::stringstream stream;
1967 stream << value;
1968 return stream.str();
1969}

1971// additional forward declarations
1972
1974template <typename T,
1975 enable_if_t<!std::is_convertible<T, std::string>::value && !std::is_constructible<std::string, T>::value &&
1976 !is_ostreamable<T>::value && is_tuple_like<T>::value && type_count_base<T>::value == 1,
1977 detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
1978inline std::string to_string(T &&value);
1979
1981template <typename T,
1982 enable_if_t<!std::is_convertible<T, std::string>::value && !std::is_constructible<std::string, T>::value &&
1983 !is_ostreamable<T>::value && is_tuple_like<T>::value && type_count_base<T>::value >= 2,
1984 detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
1985inline std::string to_string(T &&value);
1986
1988template <
1989 typename T,
1990 enable_if_t<!std::is_convertible<T, std::string>::value && !std::is_constructible<std::string, T>::value &&
1991 !is_ostreamable<T>::value && !is_readable_container<typename std::remove_const<T>::type>::value &&
1992 !is_tuple_like<T>::value,
1993 detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
1994inline std::string to_string(T &&) {
1995 return {};
1996}
1997
1999template <typename T,
2000 enable_if_t<!std::is_convertible<T, std::string>::value && !std::is_constructible<std::string, T>::value &&
2001 !is_ostreamable<T>::value && is_readable_container<T>::value,
2002 detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
2003inline std::string to_string(T &&variable) {
2004 auto cval = variable.begin();
2005 auto end = variable.end();
2006 if(cval == end) {
2007 return {"{}"};
2008 }
2009 std::vector<std::string> defaults;
2010 while(cval != end) {
2011 defaults.emplace_back(CLI::detail::to_string(*cval));
2012 ++cval;
2013 }
2014 return {"[" + detail::join(defaults) + "]"};
2015}

2241// Enumeration of the different supported categorizations of objects
2242enum class object_category : int {
2243 char_value = 1,
2244 integral_value = 2,
2245 unsigned_integral = 4,
2246 enumeration = 6,
2247 boolean_value = 8,
2248 floating_point = 10,
2249 number_constructible = 12,
2250 double_constructible = 14,
2251 integer_constructible = 16,
2252 // string like types
2253 string_assignable = 23,
2254 string_constructible = 24,
2255 wstring_assignable = 25,
2256 wstring_constructible = 26,
2257 other = 45,
2258 // special wrapper or container types
2259 wrapper_value = 50,
2260 complex_number = 60,
2261 tuple_value = 70,
2262 container_value = 80,
2263
2264};

2410template <typename T>
2411struct classify_object<
2412 T,
2413 typename std::enable_if<is_tuple_like<T>::value &&
2414 ((type_count<T>::value >= 2 && !is_wrapper<T>::value) ||
2415 (uncommon_type<T>::value && !is_direct_constructible<T, double>::value &&
2416 !is_direct_constructible<T, int>::value) ||
2417 (uncommon_type<T>::value && type_count<T>::value >= 2))>::type> {
2418 static constexpr object_category value{object_category::tuple_value};
2419 // the condition on this class requires it be like a tuple, but on some compilers (like Xcode) tuples can be
2420 // constructed from just the first element so tuples of <string, int,int> can be constructed from a string, which
2421 // could lead to issues so there are two variants of the condition, the first isolates things with a type size >=2
2422 // mainly to get tuples on Xcode with the exception of wrappers, the second is the main one and just separating out
2423 // those cases that are caught by other object classifications
2424};

2550
2551// Lexical cast
2552
2554template <typename T, enable_if_t<std::is_unsigned<T>::value, detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
2555bool integral_conversion(const std::string &input, T &output) noexcept {
2556 if(input.empty() || input.front() == '-') {
2557 return false;
2558 }
2559 char *val{nullptr};
2560 errno = 0;
2561 std::uint64_t output_ll = std::strtoull(input.c_str(), &val, 0);
2562 if(errno == ERANGE) {
2563 return false;
2564 }
2565 output = static_cast<T>(output_ll);
2566 if(val == (input.c_str() + input.size()) && static_cast<std::uint64_t>(output) == output_ll) {
2567 return true;
2568 }
2569 val = nullptr;
2570 std::int64_t output_sll = std::strtoll(input.c_str(), &val, 0);
2571 if(val == (input.c_str() + input.size())) {
2572 output = (output_sll < 0) ? static_cast<T>(0) : static_cast<T>(output_sll);
2573 return (static_cast<std::int64_t>(output) == output_sll);
2574 }
2575 // remove separators
2576 if(input.find_first_of("_'") != std::string::npos) {
2577 std::string nstring = input;
2578 nstring.erase(std::remove(nstring.begin(), nstring.end(), '_'), nstring.end());
2579 nstring.erase(std::remove(nstring.begin(), nstring.end(), '\''), nstring.end());
2580 return integral_conversion(nstring, output);
2581 }
2582 if(std::isspace(static_cast<unsigned char>(input.back()))) {
2583 return integral_conversion(trim_copy(input), output);
2584 }
2585 if(input.compare(0, 2, "0o") == 0 || input.compare(0, 2, "0O") == 0) {
2586 val = nullptr;
2587 errno = 0;
2588 output_ll = std::strtoull(input.c_str() + 2, &val, 8);
2589 if(errno == ERANGE) {
2590 return false;
2591 }
2592 output = static_cast<T>(output_ll);
2593 return (val == (input.c_str() + input.size()) && static_cast<std::uint64_t>(output) == output_ll);
2594 }
2595 if(input.compare(0, 2, "0b") == 0 || input.compare(0, 2, "0B") == 0) {
2596 // LCOV_EXCL_START
2597 // In some new compilers including the coverage testing one binary strings are handled properly in strtoull
2598 // automatically so this coverage is missing but is well tested in other compilers
2599 val = nullptr;
2600 errno = 0;
2601 output_ll = std::strtoull(input.c_str() + 2, &val, 2);
2602 if(errno == ERANGE) {
2603 return false;
2604 }
2605 output = static_cast<T>(output_ll);
2606 return (val == (input.c_str() + input.size()) && static_cast<std::uint64_t>(output) == output_ll);
2607 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
2608 }
2609 return false;
2610}
2611
2613template <typename T, enable_if_t<std::is_signed<T>::value, detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
2614bool integral_conversion(const std::string &input, T &output) noexcept {
2615 if(input.empty()) {
2616 return false;
2617 }
2618 char *val = nullptr;
2619 errno = 0;
2620 std::int64_t output_ll = std::strtoll(input.c_str(), &val, 0);
2621 if(errno == ERANGE) {
2622 return false;
2623 }
2624 output = static_cast<T>(output_ll);
2625 if(val == (input.c_str() + input.size()) && static_cast<std::int64_t>(output) == output_ll) {
2626 return true;
2627 }
2628 if(input == "true") {
2629 // this is to deal with a few oddities with flags and wrapper int types
2630 output = static_cast<T>(1);
2631 return true;
2632 }
2633 // remove separators and trailing spaces
2634 if(input.find_first_of("_'") != std::string::npos) {
2635 std::string nstring = input;
2636 nstring.erase(std::remove(nstring.begin(), nstring.end(), '_'), nstring.end());
2637 nstring.erase(std::remove(nstring.begin(), nstring.end(), '\''), nstring.end());
2638 return integral_conversion(nstring, output);
2639 }
2640 if(std::isspace(static_cast<unsigned char>(input.back()))) {
2641 return integral_conversion(trim_copy(input), output);
2642 }
2643 if(input.compare(0, 2, "0o") == 0 || input.compare(0, 2, "0O") == 0) {
2644 val = nullptr;
2645 errno = 0;
2646 output_ll = std::strtoll(input.c_str() + 2, &val, 8);
2647 if(errno == ERANGE) {
2648 return false;
2649 }
2650 output = static_cast<T>(output_ll);
2651 return (val == (input.c_str() + input.size()) && static_cast<std::int64_t>(output) == output_ll);
2652 }
2653 if(input.compare(0, 2, "0b") == 0 || input.compare(0, 2, "0B") == 0) {
2654 // LCOV_EXCL_START
2655 // In some new compilers including the coverage testing one binary strings are handled properly in strtoll
2656 // automatically so this coverage is missing but is well tested in other compilers
2657 val = nullptr;
2658 errno = 0;
2659 output_ll = std::strtoll(input.c_str() + 2, &val, 2);
2660 if(errno == ERANGE) {
2661 return false;
2662 }
2663 output = static_cast<T>(output_ll);
2664 return (val == (input.c_str() + input.size()) && static_cast<std::int64_t>(output) == output_ll);
2665 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
2666 }
2667 return false;
2668}
2669
2671inline std::int64_t to_flag_value(std::string val) noexcept {
2672 static const std::string trueString("true");
2673 static const std::string falseString("false");
2674 if(val == trueString) {
2675 return 1;
2676 }
2677 if(val == falseString) {
2678 return -1;
2679 }
2680 val = detail::to_lower(val);
2681 std::int64_t ret = 0;
2682 if(val.size() == 1) {
2683 if(val[0] >= '1' && val[0] <= '9') {
2684 return (static_cast<std::int64_t>(val[0]) - '0');
2685 }
2686 switch(val[0]) {
2687 case '0':
2688 case 'f':
2689 case 'n':
2690 case '-':
2691 ret = -1;
2692 break;
2693 case 't':
2694 case 'y':
2695 case '+':
2696 ret = 1;
2697 break;
2698 default:
2699 errno = EINVAL;
2700 return -1;
2701 }
2702 return ret;
2703 }
2704 if(val == trueString || val == "on" || val == "yes" || val == "enable") {
2705 ret = 1;
2706 } else if(val == falseString || val == "off" || val == "no" || val == "disable") {
2707 ret = -1;
2708 } else {
2709 char *loc_ptr{nullptr};
2710 ret = std::strtoll(val.c_str(), &loc_ptr, 0);
2711 if(loc_ptr != (val.c_str() + val.size()) && errno == 0) {
2712 errno = EINVAL;
2713 }
2714 }
2715 return ret;
2716}
2717
2719template <typename T,
2720 enable_if_t<classify_object<T>::value == object_category::integral_value ||
2721 classify_object<T>::value == object_category::unsigned_integral,
2722 detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
2723bool lexical_cast(const std::string &input, T &output) {
2724 return integral_conversion(input, output);
2725}

2728template <typename T,
2729 enable_if_t<classify_object<T>::value == object_category::char_value, detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
2730bool lexical_cast(const std::string &input, T &output) {
2731 if(input.size() == 1) {
2732 output = static_cast<T>(input[0]);
2733 return true;
2734 }
2735 return integral_conversion(input, output);
2736}

2739template <typename T,
2740 enable_if_t<classify_object<T>::value == object_category::boolean_value, detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
2741bool lexical_cast(const std::string &input, T &output) {
2742 errno = 0;
2743 auto out = to_flag_value(input);
2744 if(errno == 0) {
2745 output = (out > 0);
2746 } else if(errno == ERANGE) {
2747 output = (input[0] != '-');
2748 } else {
2749 return false;
2750 }
2751 return true;
2752}
2753
2755template <typename T,
2756 enable_if_t<classify_object<T>::value == object_category::floating_point, detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
2757bool lexical_cast(const std::string &input, T &output) {
2758 if(input.empty()) {
2759 return false;
2760 }
2761 char *val = nullptr;
2762 auto output_ld = std::strtold(input.c_str(), &val);
2763 output = static_cast<T>(output_ld);
2764 if(val == (input.c_str() + input.size())) {
2765 return true;
2766 }
2767 while(std::isspace(static_cast<unsigned char>(*val))) {
2768 ++val;
2769 if(val == (input.c_str() + input.size())) {
2770 return true;
2771 }
2772 }
2773
2774 // remove separators
2775 if(input.find_first_of("_'") != std::string::npos) {
2776 std::string nstring = input;
2777 nstring.erase(std::remove(nstring.begin(), nstring.end(), '_'), nstring.end());
2778 nstring.erase(std::remove(nstring.begin(), nstring.end(), '\''), nstring.end());
2779 return lexical_cast(nstring, output);
2780 }
2781 return false;
2782}
2783
2785template <typename T,
2786 enable_if_t<classify_object<T>::value == object_category::complex_number, detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
2787bool lexical_cast(const std::string &input, T &output) {
2788 using XC = typename wrapped_type<T, double>::type;
2789 XC x{0.0}, y{0.0};
2790 auto str1 = input;
2791 bool worked = false;
2792 auto nloc = str1.find_last_of("+-");
2793 if(nloc != std::string::npos && nloc > 0) {
2794 worked = lexical_cast(str1.substr(0, nloc), x);
2795 str1 = str1.substr(nloc);
2796 if(str1.back() == 'i' || str1.back() == 'j')
2797 str1.pop_back();
2798 worked = worked && lexical_cast(str1, y);
2799 } else {
2800 if(str1.back() == 'i' || str1.back() == 'j') {
2801 str1.pop_back();
2802 worked = lexical_cast(str1, y);
2803 x = XC{0};
2804 } else {
2805 worked = lexical_cast(str1, x);
2806 y = XC{0};
2807 }
2808 }
2809 if(worked) {
2810 output = T{x, y};
2811 return worked;
2812 }
2813 return from_stream(input, output);
2814}

2936template <typename T,

2938 detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
2939bool lexical_cast(const std::string &input, T &output) {
2940 int val = 0;
2941 if(integral_conversion(input, val)) {
2942#ifdef _MSC_VER
2943#pragma warning(push)
2944#pragma warning(disable : 4800)
2945#endif
2946 // with Atomic<XX> this could produce a warning due to the conversion but if atomic gets here it is an old style
2947 // so will most likely still work
2948 output = val;
2949#ifdef _MSC_VER
2950#pragma warning(pop)
2951#endif
2952 return true;
2953 }
2954 // LCOV_EXCL_START
2955 // This version of cast is only used for odd cases in an older compilers the fail over
2956 // from_stream is tested elsewhere an not relevant for coverage here
2957 return from_stream(input, output);
2958 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
2959}

3032template <typename AssignTo,
3033 typename ConvertTo,
3034 enable_if_t<std::is_same<AssignTo, ConvertTo>::value && !std::is_assignable<AssignTo &, AssignTo>::value &&
3035 classify_object<AssignTo>::value != object_category::wrapper_value &&
3036 std::is_assignable<AssignTo &, int>::value,
3037 detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
3038bool lexical_assign(const std::string &input, AssignTo &output) {
3039 if(input.empty()) {
3040 output = 0;

3047#pragma clang diagnostic push
3048#pragma clang diagnostic ignored "-Wsign-conversion"
3049#endif
3050 output = val;
3051#if defined(__clang__)
3052#pragma clang diagnostic pop
3053#endif
3054 return true;
3055 }
3056 return false;

3060template <typename AssignTo,

3067 if(parse_result) {
3068 output = val;

3101template <typename AssignTo,
3102 typename ConvertTo,
3103 enable_if_t<(type_count<AssignTo>::value <= 2) && expected_count<AssignTo>::value == 1 &&
3104 is_tuple_like<ConvertTo>::value && type_count_base<ConvertTo>::value == 2,
3105 detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
3106bool lexical_conversion(const std::vector<std ::string> &strings, AssignTo &output) {
3107 // the remove const is to handle pair types coming from a container
3108 using FirstType = typename std::remove_const<typename std::tuple_element<0, ConvertTo>::type>::type;
3109 using SecondType = typename std::tuple_element<1, ConvertTo>::type;
3110 FirstType v1;
3111 SecondType v2;
3112 bool retval = lexical_assign<FirstType, FirstType>(strings[0], v1);
3113 retval = retval && lexical_assign<SecondType, SecondType>((strings.size() > 1) ? strings[1] : std::string{}, v2);
3114 if(retval) {
3115 output = AssignTo{v1, v2};
3116 }
3117 return retval;
3118}

3121template <class AssignTo,
3122 class ConvertTo,
3123 enable_if_t<is_mutable_container<AssignTo>::value && is_mutable_container<ConvertTo>::value &&
3124 type_count<ConvertTo>::value == 1,
3125 detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
3126bool lexical_conversion(const std::vector<std ::string> &strings, AssignTo &output) {
3127 output.erase(output.begin(), output.end());
3128 if(strings.empty()) {
3129 return true;
3130 }
3131 if(strings.size() == 1 && strings[0] == "{}") {
3132 return true;
3133 }
3134 bool skip_remaining = false;
3135 if(strings.size() == 2 && strings[0] == "{}" && is_separator(strings[1])) {
3136 skip_remaining = true;
3137 }
3138 for(const auto &elem : strings) {
3139 typename AssignTo::value_type out;
3140 bool retval = lexical_assign<typename AssignTo::value_type, typename ConvertTo::value_type>(elem, out);
3141 if(!retval) {
3142 return false;
3143 }
3144 output.insert(output.end(), std::move(out));
3145 if(skip_remaining) {
3146 break;
3147 }
3148 }
3149 return (!output.empty());
3150}

3153template <class AssignTo, class ConvertTo, enable_if_t<is_complex<ConvertTo>::value, detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
3154bool lexical_conversion(const std::vector<std::string> &strings, AssignTo &output) {
3155
3156 if(strings.size() >= 2 && !strings[1].empty()) {
3157 using XC2 = typename wrapped_type<ConvertTo, double>::type;
3158 XC2 x{0.0}, y{0.0};
3159 auto str1 = strings[1];
3160 if(str1.back() == 'i' || str1.back() == 'j') {
3161 str1.pop_back();
3162 }
3163 auto worked = lexical_cast(strings[0], x) && lexical_cast(str1, y);
3164 if(worked) {
3165 output = ConvertTo{x, y};
3166 }
3167 return worked;
3168 }
3169 return lexical_assign<AssignTo, ConvertTo>(strings[0], output);
3170}

3173template <class AssignTo,
3174 class ConvertTo,
3175 enable_if_t<is_mutable_container<AssignTo>::value && (expected_count<ConvertTo>::value == 1) &&
3176 (type_count<ConvertTo>::value == 1),
3177 detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
3178bool lexical_conversion(const std::vector<std ::string> &strings, AssignTo &output) {
3179 bool retval = true;
3180 output.clear();
3181 output.reserve(strings.size());
3182 for(const auto &elem : strings) {
3183
3184 output.emplace_back();
3185 retval = retval && lexical_assign<typename AssignTo::value_type, ConvertTo>(elem, output.back());
3186 }
3187 return (!output.empty()) && retval;
3188}

3221template <typename AssignTo,

3224 classify_object<ConvertTo>::value != object_category::wrapper_value &&

3240template <class AssignTo, class ConvertTo, std::size_t I>
3241inline typename std::enable_if<(I >= type_count_base<AssignTo>::value), bool>::type
3242tuple_conversion(const std::vector<std::string> &, AssignTo &) {
3243 return true;
3244}
3245
3247template <class AssignTo, class ConvertTo>
3248inline typename std::enable_if<!is_mutable_container<ConvertTo>::value && type_count<ConvertTo>::value == 1, bool>::type
3249tuple_type_conversion(std::vector<std::string> &strings, AssignTo &output) {
3250 auto retval = lexical_assign<AssignTo, ConvertTo>(strings[0], output);
3251 strings.erase(strings.begin());
3252 return retval;
3253}
3254
3256template <class AssignTo, class ConvertTo>
3257inline typename std::enable_if<!is_mutable_container<ConvertTo>::value && (type_count<ConvertTo>::value > 1) &&
3258 type_count<ConvertTo>::value == type_count_min<ConvertTo>::value,
3259 bool>::type
3260tuple_type_conversion(std::vector<std::string> &strings, AssignTo &output) {
3261 auto retval = lexical_conversion<AssignTo, ConvertTo>(strings, output);
3262 strings.erase(strings.begin(), strings.begin() + type_count<ConvertTo>::value);
3263 return retval;
3264}
3265
3267template <class AssignTo, class ConvertTo>
3268inline typename std::enable_if<is_mutable_container<ConvertTo>::value ||
3269 type_count<ConvertTo>::value != type_count_min<ConvertTo>::value,
3270 bool>::type
3271tuple_type_conversion(std::vector<std::string> &strings, AssignTo &output) {
3272
3273 std::size_t index{subtype_count_min<ConvertTo>::value};
3274 const std::size_t mx_count{subtype_count<ConvertTo>::value};
3275 const std::size_t mx{(std::min)(mx_count, strings.size() - 1)};
3276
3277 while(index < mx) {
3278 if(is_separator(strings[index])) {
3279 break;
3280 }
3281 ++index;
3282 }
3283 bool retval = lexical_conversion<AssignTo, ConvertTo>(
3284 std::vector<std::string>(strings.begin(), strings.begin() + static_cast<std::ptrdiff_t>(index)), output);
3285 if(strings.size() > index) {
3286 strings.erase(strings.begin(), strings.begin() + static_cast<std::ptrdiff_t>(index) + 1);
3287 } else {
3288 strings.clear();
3289 }
3290 return retval;
3291}
3292
3294template <class AssignTo, class ConvertTo, std::size_t I>
3295inline typename std::enable_if<(I < type_count_base<AssignTo>::value), bool>::type
3296tuple_conversion(std::vector<std::string> strings, AssignTo &output) {
3297 bool retval = true;
3298 using ConvertToElement = typename std::
3299 conditional<is_tuple_like<ConvertTo>::value, typename std::tuple_element<I, ConvertTo>::type, ConvertTo>::type;
3300 if(!strings.empty()) {
3301 retval = retval && tuple_type_conversion<typename std::tuple_element<I, AssignTo>::type, ConvertToElement>(
3302 strings, std::get<I>(output));
3303 }
3304 retval = retval && tuple_conversion<AssignTo, ConvertTo, I + 1>(std::move(strings), output);
3305 return retval;
3306}
3307
3309template <class AssignTo,
3310 class ConvertTo,
3311 enable_if_t<is_mutable_container<AssignTo>::value && is_mutable_container<ConvertTo>::value &&
3312 type_count_base<ConvertTo>::value == 2,
3313 detail::enabler>>
3314bool lexical_conversion(std::vector<std::string> strings, AssignTo &output) {
3315 output.clear();
3316 while(!strings.empty()) {
3317
3318 typename std::remove_const<typename std::tuple_element<0, typename ConvertTo::value_type>::type>::type v1;
3319 typename std::tuple_element<1, typename ConvertTo::value_type>::type v2;
3320 bool retval = tuple_type_conversion<decltype(v1), decltype(v1)>(strings, v1);
3321 if(!strings.empty()) {
3322 retval = retval && tuple_type_conversion<decltype(v2), decltype(v2)>(strings, v2);
3323 }
3324 if(retval) {
3325 output.insert(output.end(), typename AssignTo::value_type{v1, v2});
3326 } else {
3327 return false;
3328 }
3329 }
3330 return (!output.empty());
3331}
3332
3334template <class AssignTo,
3335 class ConvertTo,
3336 enable_if_t<is_tuple_like<AssignTo>::value && is_tuple_like<ConvertTo>::value &&
3337 (type_count_base<ConvertTo>::value != type_count<ConvertTo>::value ||
3338 type_count<ConvertTo>::value > 2),
3339 detail::enabler>>
3340bool lexical_conversion(const std::vector<std ::string> &strings, AssignTo &output) {
3341 static_assert(
3342 !is_tuple_like<ConvertTo>::value || type_count_base<AssignTo>::value == type_count_base<ConvertTo>::value,
3343 "if the conversion type is defined as a tuple it must be the same size as the type you are converting to");
3344 return tuple_conversion<AssignTo, ConvertTo, 0>(strings, output);
3345}
3346
3348template <class AssignTo,
3349 class ConvertTo,
3350 enable_if_t<is_mutable_container<AssignTo>::value && is_mutable_container<ConvertTo>::value &&
3351 type_count_base<ConvertTo>::value != 2 &&
3352 ((type_count<ConvertTo>::value > 2) ||
3353 (type_count<ConvertTo>::value > type_count_base<ConvertTo>::value)),
3354 detail::enabler>>
3355bool lexical_conversion(const std::vector<std ::string> &strings, AssignTo &output) {
3356 bool retval = true;
3357 output.clear();
3358 std::vector<std::string> temp;
3359 std::size_t ii{0};
3360 std::size_t icount{0};
3361 std::size_t xcm{type_count<ConvertTo>::value};
3362 auto ii_max = strings.size();
3363 while(ii < ii_max) {
3364 temp.push_back(strings[ii]);
3365 ++ii;
3366 ++icount;
3367 if(icount == xcm || is_separator(temp.back()) || ii == ii_max) {
3368 if(static_cast<int>(xcm) > type_count_min<ConvertTo>::value && is_separator(temp.back())) {
3369 temp.pop_back();
3370 }
3371 typename AssignTo::value_type temp_out;
3372 retval = retval &&
3373 lexical_conversion<typename AssignTo::value_type, typename ConvertTo::value_type>(temp, temp_out);
3374 temp.clear();
3375 if(!retval) {
3376 return false;
3377 }
3378 output.insert(output.end(), std::move(temp_out));
3379 icount = 0;
3380 }
3381 }
3382 return retval;
3383}
3384
3386template <typename AssignTo,
3387 class ConvertTo,
3388 enable_if_t<classify_object<ConvertTo>::value == object_category::wrapper_value &&
3389 std::is_assignable<ConvertTo &, ConvertTo>::value,
3390 detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
3391bool lexical_conversion(const std::vector<std::string> &strings, AssignTo &output) {
3392 if(strings.empty() || strings.front().empty()) {
3393 output = ConvertTo{};
3394 return true;
3395 }
3396 typename ConvertTo::value_type val;
3397 if(lexical_conversion<typename ConvertTo::value_type, typename ConvertTo::value_type>(strings, val)) {
3398 output = ConvertTo{val};
3399 return true;
3400 }
3401 return false;
3402}
3403
3405template <typename AssignTo,
3406 class ConvertTo,
3407 enable_if_t<classify_object<ConvertTo>::value == object_category::wrapper_value &&
3408 !std::is_assignable<AssignTo &, ConvertTo>::value,
3409 detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
3410bool lexical_conversion(const std::vector<std::string> &strings, AssignTo &output) {
3411 using ConvertType = typename ConvertTo::value_type;
3412 if(strings.empty() || strings.front().empty()) {
3413 output = ConvertType{};
3414 return true;
3415 }
3416 ConvertType val;
3417 if(lexical_conversion<typename ConvertTo::value_type, typename ConvertTo::value_type>(strings, val)) {
3418 output = val;
3419 return true;
3420 }
3421 return false;
3422}
3423
3425inline std::string sum_string_vector(const std::vector<std::string> &values) {
3426 double val{0.0};
3427 bool fail{false};
3428 std::string output;
3429 for(const auto &arg : values) {
3430 double tv{0.0};
3431 auto comp = lexical_cast(arg, tv);
3432 if(!comp) {
3433 errno = 0;
3434 auto fv = detail::to_flag_value(arg);
3435 fail = (errno != 0);
3436 if(fail) {
3437 break;
3438 }
3439 tv = static_cast<double>(fv);
3440 }
3441 val += tv;
3442 }
3443 if(fail) {
3444 for(const auto &arg : values) {
3445 output.append(arg);
3446 }
3447 } else {
3448 std::ostringstream out;
3449 out.precision(16);
3450 out << val;
3451 output = out.str();
3452 }
3453 return output;
3454}

3462// Returns false if not a short option. Otherwise, sets opt name and rest and returns true
3463CLI11_INLINE bool split_short(const std::string &current, std::string &name, std::string &rest);
3464
3465// Returns false if not a long option. Otherwise, sets opt name and other side of = and returns true
3466CLI11_INLINE bool split_long(const std::string &current, std::string &name, std::string &value);
3467
3468// Returns false if not a windows style option. Otherwise, sets opt name and value and returns true
3469CLI11_INLINE bool split_windows_style(const std::string &current, std::string &name, std::string &value);
3470
3471// Splits a string into multiple long and short names
3472CLI11_INLINE std::vector<std::string> split_names(std::string current);
3473
3475CLI11_INLINE std::vector<std::pair<std::string, std::string>> get_default_flag_values(const std::string &str);
3476
3478CLI11_INLINE std::tuple<std::vector<std::string>, std::vector<std::string>, std::string>
3479get_names(const std::vector<std::string> &input, bool allow_non_standard = false);

3485namespace detail {
3486
3487CLI11_INLINE bool split_short(const std::string &current, std::string &name, std::string &rest) {
3488 if(current.size() > 1 && current[0] == '-' && valid_first_char(current[1])) {
3489 name = current.substr(1, 1);
3490 rest = current.substr(2);
3491 return true;
3492 }
3493 return false;
3494}
3495
3496CLI11_INLINE bool split_long(const std::string &current, std::string &name, std::string &value) {
3497 if(current.size() > 2 && current.compare(0, 2, "--") == 0 && valid_first_char(current[2])) {
3498 auto loc = current.find_first_of('=');
3499 if(loc != std::string::npos) {
3500 name = current.substr(2, loc - 2);
3501 value = current.substr(loc + 1);
3502 } else {
3503 name = current.substr(2);
3504 value = "";
3505 }
3506 return true;
3507 }
3508 return false;
3509}
3510
3511CLI11_INLINE bool split_windows_style(const std::string &current, std::string &name, std::string &value) {
3512 if(current.size() > 1 && current[0] == '/' && valid_first_char(current[1])) {
3513 auto loc = current.find_first_of(':');
3514 if(loc != std::string::npos) {
3515 name = current.substr(1, loc - 1);
3516 value = current.substr(loc + 1);
3517 } else {
3518 name = current.substr(1);
3519 value = "";
3520 }
3521 return true;
3522 }
3523 return false;
3524}
3525
3526CLI11_INLINE std::vector<std::string> split_names(std::string current) {
3527 std::vector<std::string> output;
3528 std::size_t val = 0;
3529 while((val = current.find(',')) != std::string::npos) {
3530 output.push_back(trim_copy(current.substr(0, val)));
3531 current = current.substr(val + 1);
3532 }
3533 output.push_back(trim_copy(current));
3534 return output;
3535}
3536
3537CLI11_INLINE std::vector<std::pair<std::string, std::string>> get_default_flag_values(const std::string &str) {
3538 std::vector<std::string> flags = split_names(str);
3539 flags.erase(std::remove_if(flags.begin(),
3540 flags.end(),
3541 [](const std::string &name) {
3542 return ((name.empty()) || (!(((name.find_first_of('{') != std::string::npos) &&
3543 (name.back() == '}')) ||
3544 (name[0] == '!'))));
3545 }),
3546 flags.end());
3547 std::vector<std::pair<std::string, std::string>> output;
3548 output.reserve(flags.size());
3549 for(auto &flag : flags) {
3550 auto def_start = flag.find_first_of('{');
3551 std::string defval = "false";
3552 if((def_start != std::string::npos) && (flag.back() == '}')) {
3553 defval = flag.substr(def_start + 1);
3554 defval.pop_back();
3555 flag.erase(def_start, std::string::npos); // NOLINT(readability-suspicious-call-argument)
3556 }
3557 flag.erase(0, flag.find_first_not_of("-!"));
3558 output.emplace_back(flag, defval);
3559 }
3560 return output;
3561}
3562
3563CLI11_INLINE std::tuple<std::vector<std::string>, std::vector<std::string>, std::string>
3564get_names(const std::vector<std::string> &input, bool allow_non_standard) {
3565
3566 std::vector<std::string> short_names;
3567 std::vector<std::string> long_names;
3568 std::string pos_name;
3569 for(std::string name : input) {
3570 if(name.length() == 0) {
3571 continue;
3572 }
3573 if(name.length() > 1 && name[0] == '-' && name[1] != '-') {
3574 if(name.length() == 2 && valid_first_char(name[1])) {
3575 short_names.emplace_back(1, name[1]);
3576 } else if(name.length() > 2) {
3577 if(allow_non_standard) {
3578 name = name.substr(1);
3579 if(valid_name_string(name)) {
3580 short_names.push_back(name);
3581 } else {
3582 throw BadNameString::BadLongName(name);
3583 }
3584 } else {
3585 throw BadNameString::MissingDash(name);
3586 }
3587 } else {
3588 throw BadNameString::OneCharName(name);
3589 }
3590 } else if(name.length() > 2 && name.substr(0, 2) == "--") {
3591 name = name.substr(2);
3592 if(valid_name_string(name)) {
3593 long_names.push_back(name);
3594 } else {
3595 throw BadNameString::BadLongName(name);
3596 }
3597 } else if(name == "-" || name == "--" || name == "++") {
3598 throw BadNameString::ReservedName(name);
3599 } else {
3600 if(!pos_name.empty()) {
3601 throw BadNameString::MultiPositionalNames(name);
3602 }
3603 if(valid_name_string(name)) {
3604 pos_name = name;
3605 } else {
3606 throw BadNameString::BadPositionalName(name);
3607 }
3608 }
3609 }
3610 return std::make_tuple(short_names, long_names, pos_name);
3611}
3612
3613} // namespace detail

3620struct ConfigItem {
3622 std::vector<std::string> parents{};
3623
3625 std::string name{};
3627 std::vector<std::string> inputs{};
3629 bool multiline{false};
3631 CLI11_NODISCARD std::string fullname() const {
3632 std::vector<std::string> tmp = parents;
3633 tmp.emplace_back(name);
3634 return detail::join(tmp, ".");
3635 (void)multiline; // suppression for cppcheck false positive
3636 }
3637};

3640class Config {
3641 protected:
3642 std::vector<ConfigItem> items{};
3643
3644 public:
3646 virtual std::string to_config(const App *, bool, bool, std::string) const = 0;
3647
3649 virtual std::vector<ConfigItem> from_config(std::istream &) const = 0;
3650
3652 CLI11_NODISCARD virtual std::string to_flag(const ConfigItem &item) const {
3653 if(item.inputs.size() == 1) {
3654 return item.inputs.at(0);
3655 }
3656 if(item.inputs.empty()) {
3657 return "{}";
3658 }
3659 throw ConversionError::TooManyInputsFlag(item.fullname()); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
3660 }
3661
3663 CLI11_NODISCARD std::vector<ConfigItem> from_file(const std::string &name) const {
3664 std::ifstream input{name};
3665 if(!input.good())
3666 throw FileError::Missing(name);
3667
3668 return from_config(input);
3669 }
3670
3672 virtual ~Config() = default;
3673};

3808class Validator {
3809 protected:
3811 std::function<std::string()> desc_function_{[]() { return std::string{}; }};
3812
3815 std::function<std::string(std::string &)> func_{[](std::string &) { return std::string{}; }};
3817 std::string name_{};
3819 int application_index_ = -1;
3821 bool active_{true};
3823 bool non_modifying_{false};
3824
3825 Validator(std::string validator_desc, std::function<std::string(std::string &)> func)
3826 : desc_function_([validator_desc]() { return validator_desc; }), func_(std::move(func)) {}
3827
3828 public:
3829 Validator() = default;
3831 explicit Validator(std::string validator_desc) : desc_function_([validator_desc]() { return validator_desc; }) {}
3833 Validator(std::function<std::string(std::string &)> op, std::string validator_desc, std::string validator_name = "")
3834 : desc_function_([validator_desc]() { return validator_desc; }), func_(std::move(op)),
3835 name_(std::move(validator_name)) {}
3836
3837 Validator &operation(std::function<std::string(std::string &)> op) {
3838 func_ = std::move(op);
3839 return *this;
3840 }
3841
3843 std::string operator()(std::string &str) const;
3844
3847 std::string operator()(const std::string &str) const {
3848 std::string value = str;
3849 return (active_) ? func_(value) : std::string{};
3850 }
3851
3853 Validator &description(std::string validator_desc) {
3854 desc_function_ = [validator_desc]() { return validator_desc; };
3855 return *this;
3856 }
3857
3858 CLI11_NODISCARD Validator description(std::string validator_desc) const;
3859
3861 CLI11_NODISCARD std::string get_description() const {
3862 if(active_) {
3863 return desc_function_();
3864 }
3865 return std::string{};
3866 }
3867
3868 Validator &name(std::string validator_name) {
3869 name_ = std::move(validator_name);
3870 return *this;
3871 }
3872
3873 CLI11_NODISCARD Validator name(std::string validator_name) const {
3874 Validator newval(*this);
3875 newval.name_ = std::move(validator_name);
3876 return newval;
3877 }
3878
3879 CLI11_NODISCARD const std::string &get_name() const { return name_; }
3881 Validator &active(bool active_val = true) {
3882 active_ = active_val;
3883 return *this;
3884 }
3885
3886 CLI11_NODISCARD Validator active(bool active_val = true) const {
3887 Validator newval(*this);
3888 newval.active_ = active_val;
3889 return newval;
3890 }
3891
3893 Validator &non_modifying(bool no_modify = true) {
3894 non_modifying_ = no_modify;
3895 return *this;
3896 }
3897
3898 Validator &application_index(int app_index) {
3899 application_index_ = app_index;
3900 return *this;
3901 }
3902
3903 CLI11_NODISCARD Validator application_index(int app_index) const {
3904 Validator newval(*this);
3905 newval.application_index_ = app_index;
3906 return newval;
3907 }
3908
3909 CLI11_NODISCARD int get_application_index() const { return application_index_; }
3911 CLI11_NODISCARD bool get_active() const { return active_; }
3912
3914 CLI11_NODISCARD bool get_modifying() const { return !non_modifying_; }
3915
3918 Validator operator&(const Validator &other) const;
3919
3922 Validator operator|(const Validator &other) const;
3923
3925 Validator operator!() const;
3926
3927 private:
3928 void _merge_description(const Validator &val1, const Validator &val2, const std::string &merger);
3929};

4004template <typename DesiredType> class TypeValidator : public Validator {
4005 public:
4006 explicit TypeValidator(const std::string &validator_name)
4007 : Validator(validator_name, [](std::string &input_string) {
4008 using CLI::detail::lexical_cast;
4009 auto val = DesiredType();
4010 if(!lexical_cast(input_string, val)) {
4011 return std::string("Failed parsing ") + input_string + " as a " + detail::type_name<DesiredType>();
4012 }
4013 return std::string();
4014 }) {}
4015 TypeValidator() : TypeValidator(detail::type_name<DesiredType>()) {}
4016};

4029class Range : public Validator {
4030 public:
4035 template <typename T>
4036 Range(T min_val, T max_val, const std::string &validator_name = std::string{}) : Validator(validator_name) {
4037 if(validator_name.empty()) {
4038 std::stringstream out;
4039 out << detail::type_name<T>() << " in [" << min_val << " - " << max_val << "]";
4040 description(out.str());
4041 }
4042
4043 func_ = [min_val, max_val](std::string &input) {
4044 using CLI::detail::lexical_cast;
4045 T val;
4046 bool converted = lexical_cast(input, val);
4047 if((!converted) || (val < min_val || val > max_val)) {
4048 std::stringstream out;
4049 out << "Value " << input << " not in range [";
4050 out << min_val << " - " << max_val << "]";
4051 return out.str();
4052 }
4053 return std::string{};
4054 };
4055 }
4056
4058 template <typename T>
4059 explicit Range(T max_val, const std::string &validator_name = std::string{})
4060 : Range(static_cast<T>(0), max_val, validator_name) {}
4061};

4064const Range NonNegativeNumber((std::numeric_limits<double>::max)(), "NONNEGATIVE");
4065
4067const Range PositiveNumber((std::numeric_limits<double>::min)(), (std::numeric_limits<double>::max)(), "POSITIVE");

4070class Bound : public Validator {
4071 public:
4076 template <typename T> Bound(T min_val, T max_val) {
4077 std::stringstream out;
4078 out << detail::type_name<T>() << " bounded to [" << min_val << " - " << max_val << "]";
4079 description(out.str());
4080
4081 func_ = [min_val, max_val](std::string &input) {
4082 using CLI::detail::lexical_cast;
4083 T val;
4084 bool converted = lexical_cast(input, val);
4085 if(!converted) {
4086 return std::string("Value ") + input + " could not be converted";
4087 }
4088 if(val < min_val)
4089 input = detail::to_string(min_val);
4090 else if(val > max_val)
4091 input = detail::to_string(max_val);
4092
4093 return std::string{};
4094 };
4095 }
4096
4098 template <typename T> explicit Bound(T max_val) : Bound(static_cast<T>(0), max_val) {}
4099};
