4101namespace detail {
4102template <typename T,
4103 enable_if_t<is_copyable_ptr<typename std::remove_reference<T>::type>::value, detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
4104auto smart_deref(T value) -> decltype(*value) {
4105 return *value;
4106}
4107
4108template <
4109 typename T,
4110 enable_if_t<!is_copyable_ptr<typename std::remove_reference<T>::type>::value, detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
4111typename std::remove_reference<T>::type &smart_deref(T &value) {
4112 return value;
4113}
4114
4115template <typename T> std::string generate_set(const T &set) {
4116 using element_t = typename detail::element_type<T>::type;
4117 using iteration_type_t = typename detail::pair_adaptor<element_t>::value_type; // the type of the object pair
4118 std::string out(1, '{');
4119 out.append(detail::join(
4120 detail::smart_deref(set),
4121 [](const iteration_type_t &v) { return detail::pair_adaptor<element_t>::first(v); },
4122 ","));
4123 out.push_back('}');
4124 return out;
4125}
4126
4128template <typename T> std::string generate_map(const T &map, bool key_only = false) {
4129 using element_t = typename detail::element_type<T>::type;
4130 using iteration_type_t = typename detail::pair_adaptor<element_t>::value_type; // the type of the object pair
4131 std::string out(1, '{');
4132 out.append(detail::join(
4133 detail::smart_deref(map),
4134 [key_only](const iteration_type_t &v) {
4135 std::string res{detail::to_string(detail::pair_adaptor<element_t>::first(v))};
4136
4137 if(!key_only) {
4138 res.append("->");
4139 res += detail::to_string(detail::pair_adaptor<element_t>::second(v));
4140 }
4141 return res;
4142 },
4143 ","));
4144 out.push_back('}');
4145 return out;
4146}
4147
4148template <typename C, typename V> struct has_find {
4149 template <typename CC, typename VV>
4150 static auto test(int) -> decltype(std::declval<CC>().find(std::declval<VV>()), std::true_type());
4151 template <typename, typename> static auto test(...) -> decltype(std::false_type());
4152
4153 static const auto value = decltype(test<C, V>(0))::value;
4154 using type = std::integral_constant<bool, value>;
4155};
4156
4158template <typename T, typename V, enable_if_t<!has_find<T, V>::value, detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
4159auto search(const T &set, const V &val) -> std::pair<bool, decltype(std::begin(detail::smart_deref(set)))> {
4160 using element_t = typename detail::element_type<T>::type;
4161 auto &setref = detail::smart_deref(set);
4162 auto it = std::find_if(std::begin(setref), std::end(setref), [&val](decltype(*std::begin(setref)) v) {
4163 return (detail::pair_adaptor<element_t>::first(v) == val);
4164 });
4165 return {(it != std::end(setref)), it};
4166}
4167
4169template <typename T, typename V, enable_if_t<has_find<T, V>::value, detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
4170auto search(const T &set, const V &val) -> std::pair<bool, decltype(std::begin(detail::smart_deref(set)))> {
4171 auto &setref = detail::smart_deref(set);
4172 auto it = setref.find(val);
4173 return {(it != std::end(setref)), it};
4174}
4175
4177template <typename T, typename V>
4178auto search(const T &set, const V &val, const std::function<V(V)> &filter_function)
4179 -> std::pair<bool, decltype(std::begin(detail::smart_deref(set)))> {
4180 using element_t = typename detail::element_type<T>::type;
4181 // do the potentially faster first search
4182 auto res = search(set, val);
4183 if((res.first) || (!(filter_function))) {
4184 return res;
4185 }
4186 // if we haven't found it do the longer linear search with all the element translations
4187 auto &setref = detail::smart_deref(set);
4188 auto it = std::find_if(std::begin(setref), std::end(setref), [&](decltype(*std::begin(setref)) v) {
4189 V a{detail::pair_adaptor<element_t>::first(v)};
4190 a = filter_function(a);
4191 return (a == val);
4192 });
4193 return {(it != std::end(setref)), it};
4194}
4195
4196// the following suggestion was made by Nikita Ofitserov(@himikof)
4197// done in templates to prevent compiler warnings on negation of unsigned numbers
4198
4200template <typename T>
4201inline typename std::enable_if<std::is_signed<T>::value, T>::type overflowCheck(const T &a, const T &b) {
4202 if((a > 0) == (b > 0)) {
4203 return ((std::numeric_limits<T>::max)() / (std::abs)(a) < (std::abs)(b));
4204 }
4205 return ((std::numeric_limits<T>::min)() / (std::abs)(a) > -(std::abs)(b));
4206}
4207
4208template <typename T>
4209inline typename std::enable_if<!std::is_signed<T>::value, T>::type overflowCheck(const T &a, const T &b) {
4210 return ((std::numeric_limits<T>::max)() / a < b);
4211}
4212
4214template <typename T> typename std::enable_if<std::is_integral<T>::value, bool>::type checked_multiply(T &a, T b) {
4215 if(a == 0 || b == 0 || a == 1 || b == 1) {
4216 a *= b;
4217 return true;
4218 }
4219 if(a == (std::numeric_limits<T>::min)() || b == (std::numeric_limits<T>::min)()) {
4220 return false;
4221 }
4222 if(overflowCheck(a, b)) {
4223 return false;
4224 }
4225 a *= b;
4226 return true;
4227}
4228
4230template <typename T>
4231typename std::enable_if<std::is_floating_point<T>::value, bool>::type checked_multiply(T &a, T b) {
4232 T c = a * b;
4233 if(std::isinf(c) && !std::isinf(a) && !std::isinf(b)) {
4234 return false;
4235 }
4236 a = c;
4237 return true;
4238}

4242class IsMember : public Validator {
4243 public:
4244 using filter_fn_t = std::function<std::string(std::string)>;
4245
4247 template <typename T, typename... Args>
4248 IsMember(std::initializer_list<T> values, Args &&...args)
4249 : IsMember(std::vector<T>(values), std::forward<Args>(args)...) {}
4250
4252 template <typename T> explicit IsMember(T &&set) : IsMember(std::forward<T>(set), nullptr) {}
4253
4256 template <typename T, typename F> explicit IsMember(T set, F filter_function) {
4257
4258 // Get the type of the contained item - requires a container have ::value_type
4259 // if the type does not have first_type and second_type, these are both value_type
4260 using element_t = typename detail::element_type<T>::type; // Removes (smart) pointers if needed
4261 using item_t = typename detail::pair_adaptor<element_t>::first_type; // Is value_type if not a map
4262
4263 using local_item_t = typename IsMemberType<item_t>::type; // This will convert bad types to good ones
4264 // (const char * to std::string)
4265
4266 // Make a local copy of the filter function, using a std::function if not one already
4267 std::function<local_item_t(local_item_t)> filter_fn = filter_function;
4268
4269 // This is the type name for help, it will take the current version of the set contents
4270 desc_function_ = [set]() { return detail::generate_set(detail::smart_deref(set)); };
4271
4272 // This is the function that validates
4273 // It stores a copy of the set pointer-like, so shared_ptr will stay alive
4274 func_ = [set, filter_fn](std::string &input) {
4275 using CLI::detail::lexical_cast;
4276 local_item_t b;
4277 if(!lexical_cast(input, b)) {
4278 throw ValidationError(input); // name is added later
4279 }
4280 if(filter_fn) {
4281 b = filter_fn(b);
4282 }
4283 auto res = detail::search(set, b, filter_fn);
4284 if(res.first) {
4285 // Make sure the version in the input string is identical to the one in the set
4286 if(filter_fn) {
4287 input = detail::value_string(detail::pair_adaptor<element_t>::first(*(res.second)));
4288 }
4289
4290 // Return empty error string (success)
4291 return std::string{};
4292 }
4293
4294 // If you reach this point, the result was not found
4295 return input + " not in " + detail::generate_set(detail::smart_deref(set));
4296 };
4297 }
4298
4300 template <typename T, typename... Args>
4301 IsMember(T &&set, filter_fn_t filter_fn_1, filter_fn_t filter_fn_2, Args &&...other)
4302 : IsMember(
4303 std::forward<T>(set),
4304 [filter_fn_1, filter_fn_2](std::string a) { return filter_fn_2(filter_fn_1(a)); },
4305 other...) {}
4306};

4309template <typename T> using TransformPairs = std::vector<std::pair<std::string, T>>;
4310
4312class Transformer : public Validator {
4313 public:
4314 using filter_fn_t = std::function<std::string(std::string)>;
4315
4317 template <typename... Args>
4318 Transformer(std::initializer_list<std::pair<std::string, std::string>> values, Args &&...args)
4319 : Transformer(TransformPairs<std::string>(values), std::forward<Args>(args)...) {}
4320
4322 template <typename T> explicit Transformer(T &&mapping) : Transformer(std::forward<T>(mapping), nullptr) {}
4323
4326 template <typename T, typename F> explicit Transformer(T mapping, F filter_function) {
4327
4328 static_assert(detail::pair_adaptor<typename detail::element_type<T>::type>::value,
4329 "mapping must produce value pairs");
4330 // Get the type of the contained item - requires a container have ::value_type
4331 // if the type does not have first_type and second_type, these are both value_type
4332 using element_t = typename detail::element_type<T>::type; // Removes (smart) pointers if needed
4333 using item_t = typename detail::pair_adaptor<element_t>::first_type; // Is value_type if not a map
4334 using local_item_t = typename IsMemberType<item_t>::type; // Will convert bad types to good ones
4335 // (const char * to std::string)
4336
4337 // Make a local copy of the filter function, using a std::function if not one already
4338 std::function<local_item_t(local_item_t)> filter_fn = filter_function;
4339
4340 // This is the type name for help, it will take the current version of the set contents
4341 desc_function_ = [mapping]() { return detail::generate_map(detail::smart_deref(mapping)); };
4342
4343 func_ = [mapping, filter_fn](std::string &input) {
4344 using CLI::detail::lexical_cast;
4345 local_item_t b;
4346 if(!lexical_cast(input, b)) {
4347 return std::string();
4348 // there is no possible way we can match anything in the mapping if we can't convert so just return
4349 }
4350 if(filter_fn) {
4351 b = filter_fn(b);
4352 }
4353 auto res = detail::search(mapping, b, filter_fn);
4354 if(res.first) {
4355 input = detail::value_string(detail::pair_adaptor<element_t>::second(*res.second));
4356 }
4357 return std::string{};
4358 };
4359 }
4360
4362 template <typename T, typename... Args>
4363 Transformer(T &&mapping, filter_fn_t filter_fn_1, filter_fn_t filter_fn_2, Args &&...other)
4364 : Transformer(
4365 std::forward<T>(mapping),
4366 [filter_fn_1, filter_fn_2](std::string a) { return filter_fn_2(filter_fn_1(a)); },
4367 other...) {}
4368};

4371class CheckedTransformer : public Validator {
4372 public:
4373 using filter_fn_t = std::function<std::string(std::string)>;
4374
4376 template <typename... Args>
4377 CheckedTransformer(std::initializer_list<std::pair<std::string, std::string>> values, Args &&...args)
4378 : CheckedTransformer(TransformPairs<std::string>(values), std::forward<Args>(args)...) {}
4379
4381 template <typename T> explicit CheckedTransformer(T mapping) : CheckedTransformer(std::move(mapping), nullptr) {}
4382
4385 template <typename T, typename F> explicit CheckedTransformer(T mapping, F filter_function) {
4386
4387 static_assert(detail::pair_adaptor<typename detail::element_type<T>::type>::value,
4388 "mapping must produce value pairs");
4389 // Get the type of the contained item - requires a container have ::value_type
4390 // if the type does not have first_type and second_type, these are both value_type
4391 using element_t = typename detail::element_type<T>::type; // Removes (smart) pointers if needed
4392 using item_t = typename detail::pair_adaptor<element_t>::first_type; // Is value_type if not a map
4393 using local_item_t = typename IsMemberType<item_t>::type; // Will convert bad types to good ones
4394 // (const char * to std::string)
4395 using iteration_type_t = typename detail::pair_adaptor<element_t>::value_type; // the type of the object pair
4396
4397 // Make a local copy of the filter function, using a std::function if not one already
4398 std::function<local_item_t(local_item_t)> filter_fn = filter_function;
4399
4400 auto tfunc = [mapping]() {
4401 std::string out("value in ");
4402 out += detail::generate_map(detail::smart_deref(mapping)) + " OR {";
4403 out += detail::join(
4404 detail::smart_deref(mapping),
4405 [](const iteration_type_t &v) { return detail::to_string(detail::pair_adaptor<element_t>::second(v)); },
4406 ",");
4407 out.push_back('}');
4408 return out;
4409 };
4410
4411 desc_function_ = tfunc;
4412
4413 func_ = [mapping, tfunc, filter_fn](std::string &input) {
4414 using CLI::detail::lexical_cast;
4415 local_item_t b;
4416 bool converted = lexical_cast(input, b);
4417 if(converted) {
4418 if(filter_fn) {
4419 b = filter_fn(b);
4420 }
4421 auto res = detail::search(mapping, b, filter_fn);
4422 if(res.first) {
4423 input = detail::value_string(detail::pair_adaptor<element_t>::second(*res.second));
4424 return std::string{};
4425 }
4426 }
4427 for(const auto &v : detail::smart_deref(mapping)) {
4428 auto output_string = detail::value_string(detail::pair_adaptor<element_t>::second(v));
4429 if(output_string == input) {
4430 return std::string();
4431 }
4432 }
4433
4434 return "Check " + input + " " + tfunc() + " FAILED";
4435 };
4436 }
4437
4439 template <typename T, typename... Args>
4440 CheckedTransformer(T &&mapping, filter_fn_t filter_fn_1, filter_fn_t filter_fn_2, Args &&...other)
4441 : CheckedTransformer(
4442 std::forward<T>(mapping),
4443 [filter_fn_1, filter_fn_2](std::string a) { return filter_fn_2(filter_fn_1(a)); },
4444 other...) {}
4445};
4446
4448inline std::string ignore_case(std::string item) { return detail::to_lower(item); }
4449
4451inline std::string ignore_underscore(std::string item) { return detail::remove_underscore(item); }
4452
4454inline std::string ignore_space(std::string item) {
4455 item.erase(std::remove(std::begin(item), std::end(item), ' '), std::end(item));
4456 item.erase(std::remove(std::begin(item), std::end(item), '\t'), std::end(item));
4457 return item;
4458}
4459
4471class AsNumberWithUnit : public Validator {
4472 public:
4477 enum Options {
4478 CASE_SENSITIVE = 0,
4479 CASE_INSENSITIVE = 1,
4480 UNIT_OPTIONAL = 0,
4481 UNIT_REQUIRED = 2,
4482 DEFAULT = CASE_INSENSITIVE | UNIT_OPTIONAL
4483 };
4484
4485 template <typename Number>
4486 explicit AsNumberWithUnit(std::map<std::string, Number> mapping,
4487 Options opts = DEFAULT,
4488 const std::string &unit_name = "UNIT") {
4489 description(generate_description<Number>(unit_name, opts));
4490 validate_mapping(mapping, opts);
4491
4492 // transform function
4493 func_ = [mapping, opts](std::string &input) -> std::string {
4494 Number num{};
4495
4496 detail::rtrim(input);
4497 if(input.empty()) {
4498 throw ValidationError("Input is empty");
4499 }
4500
4501 // Find split position between number and prefix
4502 auto unit_begin = input.end();
4503 while(unit_begin > input.begin() && std::isalpha(*(unit_begin - 1), std::locale())) {
4504 --unit_begin;
4505 }
4506
4507 std::string unit{unit_begin, input.end()};
4508 input.resize(static_cast<std::size_t>(std::distance(input.begin(), unit_begin)));
4509 detail::trim(input);
4510
4511 if(opts & UNIT_REQUIRED && unit.empty()) {
4512 throw ValidationError("Missing mandatory unit");
4513 }
4514 if(opts & CASE_INSENSITIVE) {
4515 unit = detail::to_lower(unit);
4516 }
4517 if(unit.empty()) {
4518 using CLI::detail::lexical_cast;
4519 if(!lexical_cast(input, num)) {
4520 throw ValidationError(std::string("Value ") + input + " could not be converted to " +
4521 detail::type_name<Number>());
4522 }
4523 // No need to modify input if no unit passed
4524 return {};
4525 }
4526
4527 // find corresponding factor
4528 auto it = mapping.find(unit);
4529 if(it == mapping.end()) {
4530 throw ValidationError(unit +
4531 " unit not recognized. "
4532 "Allowed values: " +
4533 detail::generate_map(mapping, true));
4534 }
4535
4536 if(!input.empty()) {
4537 using CLI::detail::lexical_cast;
4538 bool converted = lexical_cast(input, num);
4539 if(!converted) {
4540 throw ValidationError(std::string("Value ") + input + " could not be converted to " +
4541 detail::type_name<Number>());
4542 }
4543 // perform safe multiplication
4544 bool ok = detail::checked_multiply(num, it->second);
4545 if(!ok) {
4546 throw ValidationError(detail::to_string(num) + " multiplied by " + unit +
4547 " factor would cause number overflow. Use smaller value.");
4548 }
4549 } else {
4550 num = static_cast<Number>(it->second);
4551 }
4552
4553 input = detail::to_string(num);
4554
4555 return {};
4556 };
4557 }
4558
4559 private:
4562 template <typename Number> static void validate_mapping(std::map<std::string, Number> &mapping, Options opts) {
4563 for(auto &kv : mapping) {
4564 if(kv.first.empty()) {
4565 throw ValidationError("Unit must not be empty.");
4566 }
4567 if(!detail::isalpha(kv.first)) {
4568 throw ValidationError("Unit must contain only letters.");
4569 }
4570 }
4571
4572 // make all units lowercase if CASE_INSENSITIVE
4573 if(opts & CASE_INSENSITIVE) {
4574 std::map<std::string, Number> lower_mapping;
4575 for(auto &kv : mapping) {
4576 auto s = detail::to_lower(kv.first);
4577 if(lower_mapping.count(s)) {
4578 throw ValidationError(std::string("Several matching lowercase unit representations are found: ") +
4579 s);
4580 }
4581 lower_mapping[detail::to_lower(kv.first)] = kv.second;
4582 }
4583 mapping = std::move(lower_mapping);
4584 }
4585 }
4586
4588 template <typename Number> static std::string generate_description(const std::string &name, Options opts) {
4589 std::stringstream out;
4590 out << detail::type_name<Number>() << ' ';
4591 if(opts & UNIT_REQUIRED) {
4592 out << name;
4593 } else {
4594 out << '[' << name << ']';
4595 }
4596 return out.str();
4597 }
4598};
4599
4600inline AsNumberWithUnit::Options operator|(const AsNumberWithUnit::Options &a, const AsNumberWithUnit::Options &b) {
4601 return static_cast<AsNumberWithUnit::Options>(static_cast<int>(a) | static_cast<int>(b));
4602}

4648
4649CLI11_INLINE std::string Validator::operator()(std::string &str) const {
4650 std::string retstring;
4651 if(active_) {
4652 if(non_modifying_) {
4653 std::string value = str;
4654 retstring = func_(value);
4655 } else {
4656 retstring = func_(str);
4657 }
4658 }
4659 return retstring;
4660}
4661
4662CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE Validator Validator::description(std::string validator_desc) const {
4663 Validator newval(*this);
4664 newval.desc_function_ = [validator_desc]() { return validator_desc; };
4665 return newval;
4666}
4667
4668CLI11_INLINE Validator Validator::operator&(const Validator &other) const {
4669 Validator newval;
4670
4671 newval._merge_description(*this, other, " AND ");
4672
4673 // Give references (will make a copy in lambda function)
4674 const std::function<std::string(std::string & filename)> &f1 = func_;
4675 const std::function<std::string(std::string & filename)> &f2 = other.func_;
4676
4677 newval.func_ = [f1, f2](std::string &input) {
4678 std::string s1 = f1(input);
4679 std::string s2 = f2(input);
4680 if(!s1.empty() && !s2.empty())
4681 return std::string("(") + s1 + ") AND (" + s2 + ")";
4682 return s1 + s2;
4683 };
4684
4685 newval.active_ = active_ && other.active_;
4686 newval.application_index_ = application_index_;
4687 return newval;
4688}
4689
4690CLI11_INLINE Validator Validator::operator|(const Validator &other) const {
4691 Validator newval;
4692
4693 newval._merge_description(*this, other, " OR ");
4694
4695 // Give references (will make a copy in lambda function)
4696 const std::function<std::string(std::string &)> &f1 = func_;
4697 const std::function<std::string(std::string &)> &f2 = other.func_;
4698
4699 newval.func_ = [f1, f2](std::string &input) {
4700 std::string s1 = f1(input);
4701 std::string s2 = f2(input);
4702 if(s1.empty() || s2.empty())
4703 return std::string();
4704
4705 return std::string("(") + s1 + ") OR (" + s2 + ")";
4706 };
4707 newval.active_ = active_ && other.active_;
4708 newval.application_index_ = application_index_;
4709 return newval;
4710}
4711
4712CLI11_INLINE Validator Validator::operator!() const {
4713 Validator newval;
4714 const std::function<std::string()> &dfunc1 = desc_function_;
4715 newval.desc_function_ = [dfunc1]() {
4716 auto str = dfunc1();
4717 return (!str.empty()) ? std::string("NOT ") + str : std::string{};
4718 };
4719 // Give references (will make a copy in lambda function)
4720 const std::function<std::string(std::string & res)> &f1 = func_;
4721
4722 newval.func_ = [f1, dfunc1](std::string &test) -> std::string {
4723 std::string s1 = f1(test);
4724 if(s1.empty()) {
4725 return std::string("check ") + dfunc1() + " succeeded improperly";
4726 }
4727 return std::string{};
4728 };
4729 newval.active_ = active_;
4730 newval.application_index_ = application_index_;
4731 return newval;
4732}
4733
4734CLI11_INLINE void
4735Validator::_merge_description(const Validator &val1, const Validator &val2, const std::string &merger) {
4736
4737 const std::function<std::string()> &dfunc1 = val1.desc_function_;
4738 const std::function<std::string()> &dfunc2 = val2.desc_function_;
4739
4740 desc_function_ = [=]() {
4741 std::string f1 = dfunc1();
4742 std::string f2 = dfunc2();
4743 if((f1.empty()) || (f2.empty())) {
4744 return f1 + f2;
4745 }
4746 return std::string(1, '(') + f1 + ')' + merger + '(' + f2 + ')';
4747 };
4748}

4750namespace detail {
4751
4752#if defined CLI11_HAS_FILESYSTEM && CLI11_HAS_FILESYSTEM > 0
4753CLI11_INLINE path_type check_path(const char *file) noexcept {
4754 std::error_code ec;
4755 auto stat = std::filesystem::status(to_path(file), ec);
4756 if(ec) {
4757 return path_type::nonexistent;
4758 }
4759 switch(stat.type()) {
4760 case std::filesystem::file_type::none: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
4761 case std::filesystem::file_type::not_found:
4762 return path_type::nonexistent; // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
4763 case std::filesystem::file_type::directory:
4764 return path_type::directory;
4765 case std::filesystem::file_type::symlink:
4766 case std::filesystem::file_type::block:
4767 case std::filesystem::file_type::character:
4768 case std::filesystem::file_type::fifo:
4769 case std::filesystem::file_type::socket:
4770 case std::filesystem::file_type::regular:
4771 case std::filesystem::file_type::unknown:
4772 default:
4773 return path_type::file;
4774 }
4775}
4776#else
4777CLI11_INLINE path_type check_path(const char *file) noexcept {
4778#if defined(_MSC_VER)
4779 struct __stat64 buffer;
4780 if(_stat64(file, &buffer) == 0) {
4781 return ((buffer.st_mode & S_IFDIR) != 0) ? path_type::directory : path_type::file;
4782 }
4783#else
4784 struct stat buffer;
4785 if(stat(file, &buffer) == 0) {
4786 return ((buffer.st_mode & S_IFDIR) != 0) ? path_type::directory : path_type::file;
4787 }
4788#endif
4789 return path_type::nonexistent;
4790}
4791#endif
4792
4793CLI11_INLINE ExistingFileValidator::ExistingFileValidator() : Validator("FILE") {
4794 func_ = [](std::string &filename) {
4795 auto path_result = check_path(filename.c_str());
4796 if(path_result == path_type::nonexistent) {
4797 return "File does not exist: " + filename;
4798 }
4799 if(path_result == path_type::directory) {
4800 return "File is actually a directory: " + filename;
4801 }
4802 return std::string();
4803 };
4804}
4805
4806CLI11_INLINE ExistingDirectoryValidator::ExistingDirectoryValidator() : Validator("DIR") {
4807 func_ = [](std::string &filename) {
4808 auto path_result = check_path(filename.c_str());
4809 if(path_result == path_type::nonexistent) {
4810 return "Directory does not exist: " + filename;
4811 }
4812 if(path_result == path_type::file) {
4813 return "Directory is actually a file: " + filename;
4814 }
4815 return std::string();
4816 };
4817}
4818
4819CLI11_INLINE ExistingPathValidator::ExistingPathValidator() : Validator("PATH(existing)") {
4820 func_ = [](std::string &filename) {
4821 auto path_result = check_path(filename.c_str());
4822 if(path_result == path_type::nonexistent) {
4823 return "Path does not exist: " + filename;
4824 }
4825 return std::string();
4826 };
4827}
4828
4829CLI11_INLINE NonexistentPathValidator::NonexistentPathValidator() : Validator("PATH(non-existing)") {
4830 func_ = [](std::string &filename) {
4831 auto path_result = check_path(filename.c_str());
4832 if(path_result != path_type::nonexistent) {
4833 return "Path already exists: " + filename;
4834 }
4835 return std::string();
4836 };
4837}
4838
4839CLI11_INLINE IPV4Validator::IPV4Validator() : Validator("IPV4") {
4840 func_ = [](std::string &ip_addr) {
4841 auto result = CLI::detail::split(ip_addr, '.');
4842 if(result.size() != 4) {
4843 return std::string("Invalid IPV4 address must have four parts (") + ip_addr + ')';
4844 }
4845 int num = 0;
4846 for(const auto &var : result) {
4847 using CLI::detail::lexical_cast;
4848 bool retval = lexical_cast(var, num);
4849 if(!retval) {
4850 return std::string("Failed parsing number (") + var + ')';
4851 }
4852 if(num < 0 || num > 255) {
4853 return std::string("Each IP number must be between 0 and 255 ") + var;
4854 }
4855 }
4856 return std::string{};
4857 };
4858}
4859
4860CLI11_INLINE EscapedStringTransformer::EscapedStringTransformer() {
4861 func_ = [](std::string &str) {
4862 try {
4863 if(str.size() > 1 && (str.front() == '\"' || str.front() == '\'' || str.front() == '`') &&
4864 str.front() == str.back()) {
4865 process_quoted_string(str);
4866 } else if(str.find_first_of('\\') != std::string::npos) {
4867 if(detail::is_binary_escaped_string(str)) {
4868 str = detail::extract_binary_string(str);
4869 } else {
4870 str = remove_escaped_characters(str);
4871 }
4872 }
4873 return std::string{};
4874 } catch(const std::invalid_argument &ia) {
4875 return std::string(ia.what());
4876 }
4877 };
4878}
4879} // namespace detail
4880
4881CLI11_INLINE FileOnDefaultPath::FileOnDefaultPath(std::string default_path, bool enableErrorReturn)
4882 : Validator("FILE") {
4883 func_ = [default_path, enableErrorReturn](std::string &filename) {
4884 auto path_result = detail::check_path(filename.c_str());
4885 if(path_result == detail::path_type::nonexistent) {
4886 std::string test_file_path = default_path;
4887 if(default_path.back() != '/' && default_path.back() != '\\') {
4888 // Add folder separator
4889 test_file_path += '/';
4890 }
4891 test_file_path.append(filename);
4892 path_result = detail::check_path(test_file_path.c_str());
4893 if(path_result == detail::path_type::file) {
4894 filename = test_file_path;
4895 } else {
4896 if(enableErrorReturn) {
4897 return "File does not exist: " + filename;
4898 }
4899 }
4900 }
4901 return std::string{};
4902 };
4903}
4904
4905CLI11_INLINE AsSizeValue::AsSizeValue(bool kb_is_1000) : AsNumberWithUnit(get_mapping(kb_is_1000)) {
4906 if(kb_is_1000) {
4907 description("SIZE [b, kb(=1000b), kib(=1024b), ...]");
4908 } else {
4909 description("SIZE [b, kb(=1024b), ...]");
4910 }
4911}
4912
4913CLI11_INLINE std::map<std::string, AsSizeValue::result_t> AsSizeValue::init_mapping(bool kb_is_1000) {
4914 std::map<std::string, result_t> m;
4915 result_t k_factor = kb_is_1000 ? 1000 : 1024;
4916 result_t ki_factor = 1024;
4917 result_t k = 1;
4918 result_t ki = 1;
4919 m["b"] = 1;
4920 for(std::string p : {"k", "m", "g", "t", "p", "e"}) {
4921 k *= k_factor;
4922 ki *= ki_factor;
4923 m[p] = k;
4924 m[p + "b"] = k;
4925 m[p + "i"] = ki;
4926 m[p + "ib"] = ki;
4927 }
4928 return m;
4929}
4930
4931CLI11_INLINE std::map<std::string, AsSizeValue::result_t> AsSizeValue::get_mapping(bool kb_is_1000) {
4932 if(kb_is_1000) {
4933 static auto m = init_mapping(true);
4934 return m;
4935 }
4936 static auto m = init_mapping(false);
4937 return m;
4938}
4939
4940namespace detail {
4941
4942CLI11_INLINE std::pair<std::string, std::string> split_program_name(std::string commandline) {
4943 // try to determine the programName
4944 std::pair<std::string, std::string> vals;
4945 trim(commandline);
4946 auto esp = commandline.find_first_of(' ', 1);
4947 while(detail::check_path(commandline.substr(0, esp).c_str()) != path_type::file) {
4948 esp = commandline.find_first_of(' ', esp + 1);
4949 if(esp == std::string::npos) {
4950 // if we have reached the end and haven't found a valid file just assume the first argument is the
4951 // program name
4952 if(commandline[0] == '"' || commandline[0] == '\'' || commandline[0] == '`') {
4953 bool embeddedQuote = false;
4954 auto keyChar = commandline[0];
4955 auto end = commandline.find_first_of(keyChar, 1);
4956 while((end != std::string::npos) && (commandline[end - 1] == '\\')) { // deal with escaped quotes
4957 end = commandline.find_first_of(keyChar, end + 1);
4958 embeddedQuote = true;
4959 }
4960 if(end != std::string::npos) {
4961 vals.first = commandline.substr(1, end - 1);
4962 esp = end + 1;
4963 if(embeddedQuote) {
4964 vals.first = find_and_replace(vals.first, std::string("\\") + keyChar, std::string(1, keyChar));
4965 }
4966 } else {
4967 esp = commandline.find_first_of(' ', 1);
4968 }
4969 } else {
4970 esp = commandline.find_first_of(' ', 1);
4971 }
4972
4973 break;
4974 }
4975 }
4976 if(vals.first.empty()) {
4977 vals.first = commandline.substr(0, esp);
4978 rtrim(vals.first);
4979 }
4980
4981 // strip the program name
4982 vals.second = (esp < commandline.length() - 1) ? commandline.substr(esp + 1) : std::string{};
4983 ltrim(vals.second);
4984 return vals;
4985}
4986
4987} // namespace detail

5205template <typename CRTP> class OptionBase {
5206 friend App;
5207
5208 protected:
5210 std::string group_ = std::string("OPTIONS");
5211
5213 bool required_{false};

5828
5830 template <typename T> void results(T &output) const {
5831 bool retval = false;
5832 if(current_option_state_ >= option_state::reduced || (results_.size() == 1 && validators_.empty())) {
5833 const results_t &res = (proc_results_.empty()) ? results_ : proc_results_;
5834 retval = detail::lexical_conversion<T, T>(res, output);
5835 } else {
5836 results_t res;
5837 if(results_.empty()) {
5838 if(!default_str_.empty()) {
5839 // _add_results takes an rvalue only
5840 _add_result(std::string(default_str_), res);
5841 _validate_results(res);
5842 results_t extra;
5843 _reduce_results(extra, res);
5844 if(!extra.empty()) {
5845 res = std::move(extra);
5846 }
5847 } else {
5848 res.emplace_back();
5849 }
5850 } else {
5851 res = reduced_results();
5852 }
5853 retval = detail::lexical_conversion<T, T>(res, output);
5854 }
5855 if(!retval) {
5856 throw ConversionError(get_name(), results_);
5857 }
5858 }
5859
5861 template <typename T> CLI11_NODISCARD T as() const {
5862 T output;
5863 results(output);
5864 return output;
5865 }
5866
5868 CLI11_NODISCARD bool get_callback_run() const { return (current_option_state_ == option_state::callback_run); }

5882 type_name_fn([typeval]() { return typeval; });

5910 Option *default_str(std::string val) {
5911 default_str_ = std::move(val);
5912 return this;
5913 }
5914
5917 template <typename X> Option *default_val(const X &val) {
5918 std::string val_str = detail::to_string(val);
5919 auto old_option_state = current_option_state_;
5920 results_t old_results{std::move(results_)};
5921 results_.clear();
5922 try {
5923 add_result(val_str);
5924 // if trigger_on_result_ is set the callback already ran
5925 if(run_callback_for_default_ && !trigger_on_result_) {
5926 run_callback(); // run callback sets the state, we need to reset it again
5927 current_option_state_ = option_state::parsing;
5928 } else {
5929 _validate_results(results_);
5930 current_option_state_ = old_option_state;
5931 }
5932 } catch(const ValidationError &err) {
5933 // this should be done
5934 results_ = std::move(old_results);
5935 current_option_state_ = old_option_state;
5936 // try an alternate way to convert
5937 std::string alternate = detail::value_string(val);
5938 if(!alternate.empty() && alternate != val_str) {
5939 return default_val(alternate);
5940 }
5941
5942 throw ValidationError(get_name(),
5943 std::string("given default value does not pass validation :") + err.what());
5944 } catch(const ConversionError &err) {
5945 // this should be done
5946 results_ = std::move(old_results);
5947 current_option_state_ = old_option_state;
5948
5949 throw ConversionError(
5950 get_name(), std::string("given default value(\"") + val_str + "\") produces an error : " + err.what());
5951 } catch(const CLI::Error &) {
5952 results_ = std::move(old_results);
5953 current_option_state_ = old_option_state;
5954 throw;
5955 }
5956 results_ = std::move(old_results);
5957 default_str_ = std::move(val_str);
5958 return this;
5959 }
5960
5962 CLI11_NODISCARD std::string get_type_name() const;
5963
5964 private:
5966 void _validate_results(results_t &res) const;
5967
5971 void _reduce_results(results_t &out, const results_t &original) const;
5972
5973 // Run a result through the Validators
5974 std::string _validate(std::string &result, int index) const;
5975
5977 int _add_result(std::string &&result, std::vector<std::string> &res) const;
5978};

5983template <typename CRTP> template <typename T> void OptionBase<CRTP>::copy_to(T *other) const {

5987 other->ignore_underscore(ignore_underscore_);

5993}
5994
5995CLI11_INLINE Option *Option::expected(int value) {
5996 if(value < 0) {
5997 expected_min_ = -value;
5998 if(expected_max_ < expected_min_) {
5999 expected_max_ = expected_min_;
6000 }
6001 allow_extra_args_ = true;
6002 flag_like_ = false;
6003 } else if(value == detail::expected_max_vector_size) {
6004 expected_min_ = 1;
6005 expected_max_ = detail::expected_max_vector_size;
6006 allow_extra_args_ = true;
6007 flag_like_ = false;
6008 } else {
6009 expected_min_ = value;
6010 expected_max_ = value;
6011 flag_like_ = (expected_min_ == 0);
6012 }
6013 return this;
6014}
6015
6016CLI11_INLINE Option *Option::expected(int value_min, int value_max) {
6017 if(value_min < 0) {
6018 value_min = -value_min;
6019 }
6020
6021 if(value_max < 0) {
6022 value_max = detail::expected_max_vector_size;
6023 }
6024 if(value_max < value_min) {
6025 expected_min_ = value_max;
6026 expected_max_ = value_min;
6027 } else {
6028 expected_max_ = value_max;
6029 expected_min_ = value_min;
6030 }
6031
6032 return this;
6033}

6035CLI11_INLINE Option *Option::check(Validator validator, const std::string &validator_name) {
6036 validator.non_modifying();
6037 validators_.push_back(std::move(validator));
6038 if(!validator_name.empty())
6039 validators_.back().name(validator_name);
6040 return this;
6041}
6042
6043CLI11_INLINE Option *Option::check(std::function<std::string(const std::string &)> Validator,
6044 std::string Validator_description,
6045 std::string Validator_name) {
6046 validators_.emplace_back(Validator, std::move(Validator_description), std::move(Validator_name));
6047 validators_.back().non_modifying();
6048 return this;
6049}
6050
6051CLI11_INLINE Option *Option::transform(Validator Validator, const std::string &Validator_name) {
6052 validators_.insert(validators_.begin(), std::move(Validator));
6053 if(!Validator_name.empty())
6054 validators_.front().name(Validator_name);
6055 return this;
6056}
6057
6058CLI11_INLINE Option *Option::transform(const std::function<std::string(std::string)> &func,
6059 std::string transform_description,
6060 std::string transform_name) {
6061 validators_.insert(validators_.begin(),
6062 Validator(
6063 [func](std::string &val) {
6064 val = func(val);
6065 return std::string{};
6066 },
6067 std::move(transform_description),
6068 std::move(transform_name)));
6069
6070 return this;
6071}
6072
6073CLI11_INLINE Option *Option::each(const std::function<void(std::string)> &func) {
6074 validators_.emplace_back(
6075 [func](std::string &inout) {
6076 func(inout);
6077 return std::string{};
6078 },
6079 std::string{});
6080 return this;
6081}
6082
6083CLI11_INLINE Validator *Option::get_validator(const std::string &Validator_name) {
6084 for(auto &Validator : validators_) {
6085 if(Validator_name == Validator.get_name()) {
6086 return &Validator;
6087 }
6088 }
6089 if((Validator_name.empty()) && (!validators_.empty())) {
6090 return &(validators_.front());
6091 }
6092 throw OptionNotFound(std::string{"Validator "} + Validator_name + " Not Found");
6093}
6094
6095CLI11_INLINE Validator *Option::get_validator(int index) {
6096 // This is an signed int so that it is not equivalent to a pointer.
6097 if(index >= 0 && index < static_cast<int>(validators_.size())) {
6098 return &(validators_[static_cast<decltype(validators_)::size_type>(index)]);
6099 }
6100 throw OptionNotFound("Validator index is not valid");
6101}
6102
6103CLI11_INLINE bool Option::remove_needs(Option *opt) {
6104 auto iterator = std::find(std::begin(needs_), std::end(needs_), opt);
6105
6106 if(iterator == std::end(needs_)) {
6107 return false;
6108 }
6109 needs_.erase(iterator);
6110 return true;
6111}
6112
6113CLI11_INLINE Option *Option::excludes(Option *opt) {
6114 if(opt == this) {
6115 throw(IncorrectConstruction("and option cannot exclude itself"));
6116 }
6117 excludes_.insert(opt);
6118
6119 // Help text should be symmetric - excluding a should exclude b
6120 opt->excludes_.insert(this);
6121
6122 // Ignoring the insert return value, excluding twice is now allowed.
6123 // (Mostly to allow both directions to be excluded by user, even though the library does it for you.)
6124
6125 return this;
6126}
6127
6128CLI11_INLINE bool Option::remove_excludes(Option *opt) {
6129 auto iterator = std::find(std::begin(excludes_), std::end(excludes_), opt);
6130
6131 if(iterator == std::end(excludes_)) {
6132 return false;
6133 }
6134 excludes_.erase(iterator);
6135 return true;
6136}
6137
6138template <typename T> Option *Option::ignore_case(bool value) {
6139 if(!ignore_case_ && value) {
6140 ignore_case_ = value;
6141 auto *parent = static_cast<T *>(parent_);
6142 for(const Option_p &opt : parent->options_) {
6143 if(opt.get() == this) {
6144 continue;
6145 }
6146 const auto &omatch = opt->matching_name(*this);
6147 if(!omatch.empty()) {
6148 ignore_case_ = false;
6149 throw OptionAlreadyAdded("adding ignore case caused a name conflict with " + omatch);
6150 }
6151 }
6152 } else {
6153 ignore_case_ = value;
6154 }
6155 return this;
6156}
6157
6158template <typename T> Option *Option::ignore_underscore(bool value) {
6159
6160 if(!ignore_underscore_ && value) {
6161 ignore_underscore_ = value;
6162 auto *parent = static_cast<T *>(parent_);
6163 for(const Option_p &opt : parent->options_) {
6164 if(opt.get() == this) {
6165 continue;
6166 }
6167 const auto &omatch = opt->matching_name(*this);
6168 if(!omatch.empty()) {
6169 ignore_underscore_ = false;
6170 throw OptionAlreadyAdded("adding ignore underscore caused a name conflict with " + omatch);
6171 }
6172 }
6173 } else {
6174 ignore_underscore_ = value;
6175 }
6176 return this;
6177}
6178
6179CLI11_INLINE Option *Option::multi_option_policy(MultiOptionPolicy value) {
6180 if(value != multi_option_policy_) {
6181 if(multi_option_policy_ == MultiOptionPolicy::Throw && expected_max_ == detail::expected_max_vector_size &&
6182 expected_min_ > 1) { // this bizarre condition is to maintain backwards compatibility
6183 // with the previous behavior of expected_ with vectors
6184 expected_max_ = expected_min_;
6185 }
6186 multi_option_policy_ = value;
6187 current_option_state_ = option_state::parsing;
6188 }
6189 return this;
6190}
6191
6192CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE std::string Option::get_name(bool positional, bool all_options) const {
6193 if(get_group().empty())
6194 return {}; // Hidden
6195
6196 if(all_options) {
6197
6198 std::vector<std::string> name_list;
6199
6201 if((positional && (!pname_.empty())) || (snames_.empty() && lnames_.empty())) {
6202 name_list.push_back(pname_);
6203 }
6204 if((get_items_expected() == 0) && (!fnames_.empty())) {
6205 for(const std::string &sname : snames_) {
6206 name_list.push_back("-" + sname);
6207 if(check_fname(sname)) {
6208 name_list.back() += "{" + get_flag_value(sname, "") + "}";
6209 }
6210 }
6211
6212 for(const std::string &lname : lnames_) {
6213 name_list.push_back("--" + lname);
6214 if(check_fname(lname)) {
6215 name_list.back() += "{" + get_flag_value(lname, "") + "}";
6216 }
6217 }
6218 } else {
6219 for(const std::string &sname : snames_)
6220 name_list.push_back("-" + sname);
6221
6222 for(const std::string &lname : lnames_)
6223 name_list.push_back("--" + lname);
6224 }
6225
6226 return detail::join(name_list);
6227 }
6228
6229 // This returns the positional name no matter what
6230 if(positional)
6231 return pname_;
6232
6233 // Prefer long name
6234 if(!lnames_.empty())
6235 return std::string(2, '-') + lnames_[0];
6236
6237 // Or short name if no long name
6238 if(!snames_.empty())
6239 return std::string(1, '-') + snames_[0];
6240
6241 // If positional is the only name, it's okay to use that
6242 return pname_;
6243}
6244
6245CLI11_INLINE void Option::run_callback() {
6246 bool used_default_str = false;
6247 if(force_callback_ && results_.empty()) {
6248 used_default_str = true;
6249 add_result(default_str_);
6250 }
6251 if(current_option_state_ == option_state::parsing) {
6252 _validate_results(results_);
6253 current_option_state_ = option_state::validated;
6254 }
6255
6256 if(current_option_state_ < option_state::reduced) {
6257 _reduce_results(proc_results_, results_);
6258 }
6259
6260 current_option_state_ = option_state::callback_run;
6261 if(callback_) {
6262 const results_t &send_results = proc_results_.empty() ? results_ : proc_results_;
6263 bool local_result = callback_(send_results);
6264 if(used_default_str) {
6265 // we only clear the results if the callback was actually used
6266 // otherwise the callback is the storage of the default
6267 results_.clear();
6268 proc_results_.clear();
6269 }
6270 if(!local_result)
6271 throw ConversionError(get_name(), results_);
6272 }
6273}
6274
6275CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE const std::string &Option::matching_name(const Option &other) const {
6276 static const std::string estring;
6277 bool bothConfigurable = configurable_ && other.configurable_;
6278 for(const std::string &sname : snames_) {
6279 if(other.check_sname(sname))
6280 return sname;
6281 if(bothConfigurable && other.check_lname(sname))
6282 return sname;
6283 }
6284 for(const std::string &lname : lnames_) {
6285 if(other.check_lname(lname))
6286 return lname;
6287 if(lname.size() == 1 && bothConfigurable) {
6288 if(other.check_sname(lname)) {
6289 return lname;
6290 }
6291 }
6292 }
6293 if(bothConfigurable && snames_.empty() && lnames_.empty() && !pname_.empty()) {
6294 if(other.check_sname(pname_) || other.check_lname(pname_) || pname_ == other.pname_)
6295 return pname_;
6296 }
6297 if(bothConfigurable && other.snames_.empty() && other.fnames_.empty() && !other.pname_.empty()) {
6298 if(check_sname(other.pname_) || check_lname(other.pname_) || (pname_ == other.pname_))
6299 return other.pname_;
6300 }
6301 if(ignore_case_ ||
6302 ignore_underscore_) { // We need to do the inverse, in case we are ignore_case or ignore underscore
6303 for(const std::string &sname : other.snames_)
6304 if(check_sname(sname))
6305 return sname;
6306 for(const std::string &lname : other.lnames_)
6307 if(check_lname(lname))
6308 return lname;
6309 }
6310 return estring;
6311}
6312
6313CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE bool Option::check_name(const std::string &name) const {
6314
6315 if(name.length() > 2 && name[0] == '-' && name[1] == '-')
6316 return check_lname(name.substr(2));
6317 if(name.length() > 1 && name.front() == '-')
6318 return check_sname(name.substr(1));
6319 if(!pname_.empty()) {
6320 std::string local_pname = pname_;
6321 std::string local_name = name;
6322 if(ignore_underscore_) {
6323 local_pname = detail::remove_underscore(local_pname);
6324 local_name = detail::remove_underscore(local_name);
6325 }
6326 if(ignore_case_) {
6327 local_pname = detail::to_lower(local_pname);
6328 local_name = detail::to_lower(local_name);
6329 }
6330 if(local_name == local_pname) {
6331 return true;
6332 }
6333 }
6334
6335 if(!envname_.empty()) {
6336 // this needs to be the original since envname_ shouldn't match on case insensitivity
6337 return (name == envname_);
6338 }
6339 return false;
6340}
6341
6342CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE std::string Option::get_flag_value(const std::string &name,
6343 std::string input_value) const {
6344 static const std::string trueString{"true"};
6345 static const std::string falseString{"false"};
6346 static const std::string emptyString{"{}"};
6347 // check for disable flag override_
6348 if(disable_flag_override_) {
6349 if(!((input_value.empty()) || (input_value == emptyString))) {
6350 auto default_ind = detail::find_member(name, fnames_, ignore_case_, ignore_underscore_);
6351 if(default_ind >= 0) {
6352 // We can static cast this to std::size_t because it is more than 0 in this block
6353 if(default_flag_values_[static_cast<std::size_t>(default_ind)].second != input_value) {
6354 if(input_value == default_str_ && force_callback_) {
6355 return input_value;
6356 }
6357 throw(ArgumentMismatch::FlagOverride(name));
6358 }
6359 } else {
6360 if(input_value != trueString) {
6361 throw(ArgumentMismatch::FlagOverride(name));
6362 }
6363 }
6364 }
6365 }
6366 auto ind = detail::find_member(name, fnames_, ignore_case_, ignore_underscore_);
6367 if((input_value.empty()) || (input_value == emptyString)) {
6368 if(flag_like_) {
6369 return (ind < 0) ? trueString : default_flag_values_[static_cast<std::size_t>(ind)].second;
6370 }
6371 return (ind < 0) ? default_str_ : default_flag_values_[static_cast<std::size_t>(ind)].second;
6372 }
6373 if(ind < 0) {
6374 return input_value;
6375 }
6376 if(default_flag_values_[static_cast<std::size_t>(ind)].second == falseString) {
6377 errno = 0;
6378 auto val = detail::to_flag_value(input_value);
6379 if(errno != 0) {
6380 errno = 0;
6381 return input_value;
6382 }
6383 return (val == 1) ? falseString : (val == (-1) ? trueString : std::to_string(-val));
6384 }
6385 return input_value;
6386}

6388CLI11_INLINE Option *Option::add_result(std::string s) {
6389 _add_result(std::move(s), results_);
6390 current_option_state_ = option_state::parsing;
6391 return this;
6392}
6393
6394CLI11_INLINE Option *Option::add_result(std::string s, int &results_added) {
6395 results_added = _add_result(std::move(s), results_);
6396 current_option_state_ = option_state::parsing;
6397 return this;
6398}
6399
6400CLI11_INLINE Option *Option::add_result(std::vector<std::string> s) {
6401 current_option_state_ = option_state::parsing;
6402 for(auto &str : s) {
6403 _add_result(std::move(str), results_);
6404 }
6405 return this;
6406}
6407
6408CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE results_t Option::reduced_results() const {
6409 results_t res = proc_results_.empty() ? results_ : proc_results_;
6410 if(current_option_state_ < option_state::reduced) {
6411 if(current_option_state_ == option_state::parsing) {
6412 res = results_;
6413 _validate_results(res);
6414 }
6415 if(!res.empty()) {
6416 results_t extra;
6417 _reduce_results(extra, res);
6418 if(!extra.empty()) {
6419 res = std::move(extra);
6420 }
6421 }
6422 }
6423 return res;
6424}
6425
6426CLI11_INLINE Option *Option::type_size(int option_type_size) {
6427 if(option_type_size < 0) {
6428 // this section is included for backwards compatibility
6429 type_size_max_ = -option_type_size;
6430 type_size_min_ = -option_type_size;
6431 expected_max_ = detail::expected_max_vector_size;
6432 } else {
6433 type_size_max_ = option_type_size;
6434 if(type_size_max_ < detail::expected_max_vector_size) {
6435 type_size_min_ = option_type_size;
6436 } else {
6437 inject_separator_ = true;
6438 }
6439 if(type_size_max_ == 0)
6440 required_ = false;
6441 }
6442 return this;
6443}
6444
6445CLI11_INLINE Option *Option::type_size(int option_type_size_min, int option_type_size_max) {
6446 if(option_type_size_min < 0 || option_type_size_max < 0) {
6447 // this section is included for backwards compatibility
6448 expected_max_ = detail::expected_max_vector_size;
6449 option_type_size_min = (std::abs)(option_type_size_min);
6450 option_type_size_max = (std::abs)(option_type_size_max);
6451 }
6452
6453 if(option_type_size_min > option_type_size_max) {
6454 type_size_max_ = option_type_size_min;
6455 type_size_min_ = option_type_size_max;
6456 } else {
6457 type_size_min_ = option_type_size_min;
6458 type_size_max_ = option_type_size_max;
6459 }
6460 if(type_size_max_ == 0) {
6461 required_ = false;
6462 }
6463 if(type_size_max_ >= detail::expected_max_vector_size) {
6464 inject_separator_ = true;
6465 }
6466 return this;
6467}
6468
6469CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE std::string Option::get_type_name() const {
6470 std::string full_type_name = type_name_();
6471 if(!validators_.empty()) {
6472 for(const auto &Validator : validators_) {
6473 std::string vtype = Validator.get_description();
6474 if(!vtype.empty()) {
6475 full_type_name += ":" + vtype;
6476 }
6477 }
6478 }
6479 return full_type_name;
6480}
6481
6482CLI11_INLINE void Option::_validate_results(results_t &res) const {
6483 // Run the Validators (can change the string)
6484 if(!validators_.empty()) {
6485 if(type_size_max_ > 1) { // in this context index refers to the index in the type
6486 int index = 0;
6487 if(get_items_expected_max() < static_cast<int>(res.size()) &&
6488 (multi_option_policy_ == CLI::MultiOptionPolicy::TakeLast ||
6489 multi_option_policy_ == CLI::MultiOptionPolicy::Reverse)) {
6490 // create a negative index for the earliest ones
6491 index = get_items_expected_max() - static_cast<int>(res.size());
6492 }
6493
6494 for(std::string &result : res) {
6495 if(detail::is_separator(result) && type_size_max_ != type_size_min_ && index >= 0) {
6496 index = 0; // reset index for variable size chunks
6497 continue;
6498 }
6499 auto err_msg = _validate(result, (index >= 0) ? (index % type_size_max_) : index);
6500 if(!err_msg.empty())
6501 throw ValidationError(get_name(), err_msg);
6502 ++index;
6503 }
6504 } else {
6505 int index = 0;
6506 if(expected_max_ < static_cast<int>(res.size()) &&
6507 (multi_option_policy_ == CLI::MultiOptionPolicy::TakeLast ||
6508 multi_option_policy_ == CLI::MultiOptionPolicy::Reverse)) {
6509 // create a negative index for the earliest ones
6510 index = expected_max_ - static_cast<int>(res.size());
6511 }
6512 for(std::string &result : res) {
6513 auto err_msg = _validate(result, index);
6514 ++index;
6515 if(!err_msg.empty())
6516 throw ValidationError(get_name(), err_msg);
6517 }
6518 }
6519 }
6520}
6521
6522CLI11_INLINE void Option::_reduce_results(results_t &out, const results_t &original) const {
6523
6524 // max num items expected or length of vector, always at least 1
6525 // Only valid for a trimming policy
6526
6527 out.clear();
6528 // Operation depends on the policy setting
6529 switch(multi_option_policy_) {
6530 case MultiOptionPolicy::TakeAll:
6531 break;
6532 case MultiOptionPolicy::TakeLast: {
6533 // Allow multi-option sizes (including 0)
6534 std::size_t trim_size = std::min<std::size_t>(
6535 static_cast<std::size_t>(std::max<int>(get_items_expected_max(), 1)), original.size());
6536 if(original.size() != trim_size) {
6537 out.assign(original.end() - static_cast<results_t::difference_type>(trim_size), original.end());
6538 }
6539 } break;
6540 case MultiOptionPolicy::Reverse: {
6541 // Allow multi-option sizes (including 0)
6542 std::size_t trim_size = std::min<std::size_t>(
6543 static_cast<std::size_t>(std::max<int>(get_items_expected_max(), 1)), original.size());
6544 if(original.size() != trim_size || trim_size > 1) {
6545 out.assign(original.end() - static_cast<results_t::difference_type>(trim_size), original.end());
6546 }
6547 std::reverse(out.begin(), out.end());
6548 } break;
6549 case MultiOptionPolicy::TakeFirst: {
6550 std::size_t trim_size = std::min<std::size_t>(
6551 static_cast<std::size_t>(std::max<int>(get_items_expected_max(), 1)), original.size());
6552 if(original.size() != trim_size) {
6553 out.assign(original.begin(), original.begin() + static_cast<results_t::difference_type>(trim_size));
6554 }
6555 } break;
6556 case MultiOptionPolicy::Join:
6557 if(results_.size() > 1) {
6558 out.push_back(detail::join(original, std::string(1, (delimiter_ == '\0') ? '\n' : delimiter_)));
6559 }
6560 break;
6561 case MultiOptionPolicy::Sum:
6562 out.push_back(detail::sum_string_vector(original));
6563 break;
6564 case MultiOptionPolicy::Throw:
6565 default: {
6566 auto num_min = static_cast<std::size_t>(get_items_expected_min());
6567 auto num_max = static_cast<std::size_t>(get_items_expected_max());
6568 if(num_min == 0) {
6569 num_min = 1;
6570 }
6571 if(num_max == 0) {
6572 num_max = 1;
6573 }
6574 if(original.size() < num_min) {
6575 throw ArgumentMismatch::AtLeast(get_name(), static_cast<int>(num_min), original.size());
6576 }
6577 if(original.size() > num_max) {
6578 if(original.size() == 2 && num_max == 1 && original[1] == "%%" && original[0] == "{}") {
6579 // this condition is a trap for the following empty indicator check on config files
6580 out = original;
6581 } else {
6582 throw ArgumentMismatch::AtMost(get_name(), static_cast<int>(num_max), original.size());
6583 }
6584 }
6585 break;
6586 }
6587 }
6588 // this check is to allow an empty vector in certain circumstances but not if expected is not zero.
6589 // {} is the indicator for an empty container
6590 if(out.empty()) {
6591 if(original.size() == 1 && original[0] == "{}" && get_items_expected_min() > 0) {
6592 out.emplace_back("{}");
6593 out.emplace_back("%%");
6594 }
6595 } else if(out.size() == 1 && out[0] == "{}" && get_items_expected_min() > 0) {
6596 out.emplace_back("%%");
6597 }
6598}
6599
6600CLI11_INLINE std::string Option::_validate(std::string &result, int index) const {
6601 std::string err_msg;
6602 if(result.empty() && expected_min_ == 0) {
6603 // an empty with nothing expected is allowed
6604 return err_msg;
6605 }
6606 for(const auto &vali : validators_) {
6607 auto v = vali.get_application_index();
6608 if(v == -1 || v == index) {
6609 try {
6610 err_msg = vali(result);
6611 } catch(const ValidationError &err) {
6612 err_msg = err.what();
6613 }
6614 if(!err_msg.empty())
6615 break;
6616 }
6617 }
6618
6619 return err_msg;
6620}
6621
6622CLI11_INLINE int Option::_add_result(std::string &&result, std::vector<std::string> &res) const {
6623 int result_count = 0;
6624
6625 // Handle the vector escape possibility all characters duplicated and starting with [[ ending with ]]
6626 // this is always a single result
6627 if(result.size() >= 4 && result[0] == '[' && result[1] == '[' && result.back() == ']' &&
6628 (*(result.end() - 2) == ']')) {
6629 // this is an escape clause for odd strings
6630 std::string nstrs{'['};
6631 bool duplicated{true};
6632 for(std::size_t ii = 2; ii < result.size() - 2; ii += 2) {
6633 if(result[ii] == result[ii + 1]) {
6634 nstrs.push_back(result[ii]);
6635 } else {
6636 duplicated = false;
6637 break;
6638 }
6639 }
6640 if(duplicated) {
6641 nstrs.push_back(']');
6642 res.push_back(std::move(nstrs));
6643 ++result_count;
6644 return result_count;
6645 }
6646 }
6647
6648 if((allow_extra_args_ || get_expected_max() > 1) && !result.empty() && result.front() == '[' &&
6649 result.back() == ']') { // this is now a vector string likely from the default or user entry
6650
6651 result.pop_back();
6652 result.erase(result.begin());
6653 bool skipSection{false};
6654 for(auto &var : CLI::detail::split_up(result, ',')) {
6655 if(!var.empty()) {
6656 result_count += _add_result(std::move(var), res);
6657 }
6658 }
6659 if(!skipSection) {
6660 return result_count;
6661 }
6662 }
6663 if(delimiter_ == '\0') {
6664 res.push_back(std::move(result));
6665 ++result_count;
6666 } else {
6667 if((result.find_first_of(delimiter_) != std::string::npos)) {
6668 for(const auto &var : CLI::detail::split(result, delimiter_)) {
6669 if(!var.empty()) {
6670 res.push_back(var);
6671 ++result_count;
6672 }
6673 }
6674 } else {
6675 res.push_back(std::move(result));
6676 ++result_count;
6677 }
6678 }
6679 return result_count;
6680}

7162
7177 Option *add_option(std::string option_name,
7178 callback_t option_callback,
7179 std::string option_description = "",
7180 bool defaulted = false,
7181 std::function<std::string()> func = {});
7182
7184 template <typename AssignTo,
7185 typename ConvertTo = AssignTo,
7186 enable_if_t<!std::is_const<ConvertTo>::value, detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
7187 Option *add_option(std::string option_name,
7188 AssignTo &variable,
7189 std::string option_description = "") {
7190
7191 auto fun = [&variable](const CLI::results_t &res) { // comment for spacing
7192 return detail::lexical_conversion<AssignTo, ConvertTo>(res, variable);
7193 };
7194
7195 Option *opt = add_option(option_name, fun, option_description, false, [&variable]() {
7196 return CLI::detail::checked_to_string<AssignTo, ConvertTo>(variable);
7197 });
7198 opt->type_name(detail::type_name<ConvertTo>());
7199 // these must be actual lvalues since (std::max) sometimes is defined in terms of references and references
7200 // to structs used in the evaluation can be temporary so that would cause issues.
7201 auto Tcount = detail::type_count<AssignTo>::value;
7202 auto XCcount = detail::type_count<ConvertTo>::value;
7203 opt->type_size(detail::type_count_min<ConvertTo>::value, (std::max)(Tcount, XCcount));
7204 opt->expected(detail::expected_count<ConvertTo>::value);
7205 opt->run_callback_for_default();
7206 return opt;
7207 }
7208
7210 template <typename AssignTo, enable_if_t<!std::is_const<AssignTo>::value, detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
7211 Option *add_option_no_stream(std::string option_name,
7212 AssignTo &variable,
7213 std::string option_description = "") {
7214
7215 auto fun = [&variable](const CLI::results_t &res) { // comment for spacing
7216 return detail::lexical_conversion<AssignTo, AssignTo>(res, variable);
7217 };
7218
7219 Option *opt = add_option(option_name, fun, option_description, false, []() { return std::string{}; });
7220 opt->type_name(detail::type_name<AssignTo>());
7221 opt->type_size(detail::type_count_min<AssignTo>::value, detail::type_count<AssignTo>::value);
7222 opt->expected(detail::expected_count<AssignTo>::value);
7223 opt->run_callback_for_default();
7224 return opt;
7225 }
7226
7228 template <typename ArgType>
7229 Option *add_option_function(std::string option_name,
7230 const std::function<void(const ArgType &)> &func,
7231 std::string option_description = "") {
7232
7233 auto fun = [func](const CLI::results_t &res) {
7234 ArgType variable;
7235 bool result = detail::lexical_conversion<ArgType, ArgType>(res, variable);
7236 if(result) {
7237 func(variable);
7238 }
7239 return result;
7240 };
7241
7242 Option *opt = add_option(option_name, std::move(fun), option_description, false);
7243 opt->type_name(detail::type_name<ArgType>());
7244 opt->type_size(detail::type_count_min<ArgType>::value, detail::type_count<ArgType>::value);
7245 opt->expected(detail::expected_count<ArgType>::value);
7246 return opt;
7247 }
7248
7250 Option *add_option(std::string option_name) {
7251 return add_option(option_name, CLI::callback_t{}, std::string{}, false);
7252 }
7253
7255 template <typename T,
7256 enable_if_t<std::is_const<T>::value && std::is_constructible<std::string, T>::value, detail::enabler> =
7257 detail::dummy>
7258 Option *add_option(std::string option_name, T &option_description) {
7259 return add_option(option_name, CLI::callback_t(), option_description, false);
7260 }

7278 private:
7280 Option *_add_flag_internal(std::string flag_name, CLI::callback_t fun, std::string flag_description);
7281
7282 public:
7284 Option *add_flag(std::string flag_name) { return _add_flag_internal(flag_name, CLI::callback_t(), std::string{}); }
7285
7289 template <typename T,
7290 enable_if_t<std::is_const<T>::value && std::is_constructible<std::string, T>::value, detail::enabler> =
7291 detail::dummy>
7292 Option *add_flag(std::string flag_name, T &flag_description) {
7293 return _add_flag_internal(flag_name, CLI::callback_t(), flag_description);
7294 }
7295
7298 template <typename T,
7299 enable_if_t<!detail::is_mutable_container<T>::value && !std::is_const<T>::value &&
7300 !std::is_constructible<std::function<void(int)>, T>::value,
7301 detail::enabler> = detail::dummy>
7302 Option *add_flag(std::string flag_name,
7303 T &flag_result,
7304 std::string flag_description = "") {
7305
7306 CLI::callback_t fun = [&flag_result](const CLI::results_t &res) {
7307 using CLI::detail::lexical_cast;
7308 return lexical_cast(res[0], flag_result);
7309 };
7310 auto *opt = _add_flag_internal(flag_name, std::move(fun), std::move(flag_description));
7311 return detail::default_flag_modifiers<T>(opt);
7312 }
7313
7315 template <typename T,
7316 enable_if_t<!std::is_assignable<std::function<void(std::int64_t)> &, T>::value, detail::enabler> =
7317 detail::dummy>
7318 Option *add_flag(std::string flag_name,
7319 std::vector<T> &flag_results,
7320 std::string flag_description = "") {
7321 CLI::callback_t fun = [&flag_results](const CLI::results_t &res) {
7322 bool retval = true;
7323 for(const auto &elem : res) {
7324 using CLI::detail::lexical_cast;
7325 flag_results.emplace_back();
7326 retval &= lexical_cast(elem, flag_results.back());
7327 }
7328 return retval;
7329 };
7330 return _add_flag_internal(flag_name, std::move(fun), std::move(flag_description))
7331 ->multi_option_policy(MultiOptionPolicy::TakeAll)
7332 ->run_callback_for_default();
7333 }
7334
7336 Option *add_flag_callback(std::string flag_name,
7337 std::function<void(void)> function,
7338 std::string flag_description = "");
7339
7341 Option *add_flag_function(std::string flag_name,
7342 std::function<void(std::int64_t)> function,
7343 std::string flag_description = "");
7344
7345#ifdef CLI11_CPP14
7347 Option *add_flag(std::string flag_name,
7348 std::function<void(std::int64_t)> function,
7349 std::string flag_description = "") {
7350 return add_flag_function(std::move(flag_name), std::move(function), std::move(flag_description));
7351 }
7352#endif

7364 template <typename T = Option_group>
7365 T *add_option_group(std::string group_name, std::string group_description = "") {
7366 if(!detail::valid_alias_name_string(group_name)) {
7367 throw IncorrectConstruction("option group names may not contain newlines or null characters");
7368 }
7369 auto option_group = std::make_shared<T>(std::move(group_description), group_name, this);
7370 auto *ptr = option_group.get();
7371 // move to App_p for overload resolution on older gcc versions
7372 App_p app_ptr = std::dynamic_pointer_cast<App>(option_group);
7373 add_subcommand(std::move(app_ptr));
7374 return ptr;
7375 }

7594
7596 App *excludes(App *app) {
7597 if(app == nullptr) {
7598 throw OptionNotFound("nullptr passed");
7599 }
7600 if(app == this) {
7601 throw OptionNotFound("cannot self reference in needs");
7602 }
7603 auto res = exclude_subcommands_.insert(app);
7604 // subcommand exclusion should be symmetric
7605 if(res.second) {
7606 app->exclude_subcommands_.insert(this);
7607 }
7608 return this;
7609 }

7977 _find_subcommand(const std::string &subc_name, bool ignore_disabled, bool ignore_used) const noexcept;
7978
7983 bool _parse_subcommand(std::vector<std::string> &args);
7984
7988 bool _parse_arg(std::vector<std::string> &args, detail::Classifier current_type, bool local_processing_only);
7989
7991 void _trigger_pre_parse(std::size_t remaining_args);
7992
7994 App *_get_fallthrough_parent();
7995
7997 CLI11_NODISCARD const std::string &_compare_subcommand_names(const App &subcom, const App &base) const;
7998
8000 void _move_to_missing(detail::Classifier val_type, const std::string &val);
8001
8002 public:
8004 void _move_option(Option *opt, App *app);
8005}; // namespace CLI
8006
8008class Option_group : public App {
8009 public:
8010 Option_group(std::string group_description, std::string group_name, App *parent)
8011 : App(std::move(group_description), "", parent) {
8012 group(group_name);
8013 // option groups should have automatic fallthrough
8014 if(group_name.empty() || group_name.front() == '+') {
8015 // help will not be used by default in these contexts
8016 set_help_flag("");
8017 set_help_all_flag("");
8018 }
8019 }
8020 using App::add_option;
8022 Option *add_option(Option *opt) {
8023 if(get_parent() == nullptr) {
8024 throw OptionNotFound("Unable to locate the specified option");
8025 }
8026 get_parent()->_move_option(opt, this);
8027 return opt;
8028 }
8029
8030 void add_options(Option *opt) { add_option(opt); }
8032 template <typename... Args> void add_options(Option *opt, Args... args) {
8033 add_option(opt);
8034 add_options(args...);
8035 }
8036 using App::add_subcommand;
8038 App *add_subcommand(App *subcom) {
8039 App_p subc = subcom->get_parent()->get_subcommand_ptr(subcom);
8040 subc->get_parent()->remove_subcommand(subcom);
8041 add_subcommand(std::move(subc));
8042 return subcom;
8043 }
8044};

8085namespace detail {
8087struct AppFriend {
8088#ifdef CLI11_CPP14
8089
8091 template <typename... Args> static decltype(auto) parse_arg(App *app, Args &&...args) {
8092 return app->_parse_arg(std::forward<Args>(args)...);
8093 }
8094
8096 template <typename... Args> static decltype(auto) parse_subcommand(App *app, Args &&...args) {
8097 return app->_parse_subcommand(std::forward<Args>(args)...);
8098 }
8099#else
8101 template <typename... Args>
8102 static auto parse_arg(App *app, Args &&...args) ->
8103 typename std::result_of<decltype (&App::_parse_arg)(App, Args...)>::type {
8104 return app->_parse_arg(std::forward<Args>(args)...);
8105 }
8106
8108 template <typename... Args>
8109 static auto parse_subcommand(App *app, Args &&...args) ->
8110 typename std::result_of<decltype (&App::_parse_subcommand)(App, Args...)>::type {
8111 return app->_parse_subcommand(std::forward<Args>(args)...);
8112 }
8113#endif
8115 static App *get_fallthrough_parent(App *app) { return app->_get_fallthrough_parent(); }
8116};
8117} // namespace detail

8122CLI11_INLINE App::App(std::string app_description, std::string app_name, App *parent)
8123 : name_(std::move(app_name)), description_(std::move(app_description)), parent_(parent) {
8124 // Inherit if not from a nullptr
8125 if(parent_ != nullptr) {
8126 if(parent_->help_ptr_ != nullptr)
8127 set_help_flag(parent_->help_ptr_->get_name(false, true), parent_->help_ptr_->get_description());
8128 if(parent_->help_all_ptr_ != nullptr)
8129 set_help_all_flag(parent_->help_all_ptr_->get_name(false, true), parent_->help_all_ptr_->get_description());
8130
8132 option_defaults_ = parent_->option_defaults_;
8133
8134 // INHERITABLE
8135 failure_message_ = parent_->failure_message_;
8136 allow_extras_ = parent_->allow_extras_;
8137 allow_config_extras_ = parent_->allow_config_extras_;
8138 prefix_command_ = parent_->prefix_command_;
8139 immediate_callback_ = parent_->immediate_callback_;
8140 ignore_case_ = parent_->ignore_case_;
8141 ignore_underscore_ = parent_->ignore_underscore_;
8142 fallthrough_ = parent_->fallthrough_;
8143 validate_positionals_ = parent_->validate_positionals_;
8144 validate_optional_arguments_ = parent_->validate_optional_arguments_;
8145 configurable_ = parent_->configurable_;
8146 allow_windows_style_options_ = parent_->allow_windows_style_options_;
8147 group_ = parent_->group_;
8148 usage_ = parent_->usage_;
8149 footer_ = parent_->footer_;
8150 formatter_ = parent_->formatter_;
8151 config_formatter_ = parent_->config_formatter_;
8152 require_subcommand_max_ = parent_->require_subcommand_max_;
8153 }
8154}
