8156CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE char **App::ensure_utf8(char **argv) {
8157#ifdef _WIN32
8158 (void)argv;
8159
8160 normalized_argv_ = detail::compute_win32_argv();
8161
8162 if(!normalized_argv_view_.empty()) {
8163 normalized_argv_view_.clear();
8164 }
8165
8166 normalized_argv_view_.reserve(normalized_argv_.size());
8167 for(auto &arg : normalized_argv_) {
8168 // using const_cast is well-defined, string is known to not be const.
8169 normalized_argv_view_.push_back(const_cast<char *>(arg.data()));
8170 }
8171
8172 return normalized_argv_view_.data();
8173#else
8174 return argv;
8175#endif
8176}
8177
8178CLI11_INLINE App *App::name(std::string app_name) {
8179
8180 if(parent_ != nullptr) {
8181 std::string oname = name_;
8182 name_ = app_name;
8183 const auto &res = _compare_subcommand_names(*this, *_get_fallthrough_parent());
8184 if(!res.empty()) {
8185 name_ = oname;
8186 throw(OptionAlreadyAdded(app_name + " conflicts with existing subcommand names"));
8187 }
8188 } else {
8189 name_ = app_name;
8190 }
8191 has_automatic_name_ = false;
8192 return this;
8193}
8194
8195CLI11_INLINE App *App::alias(std::string app_name) {
8196 if(app_name.empty() || !detail::valid_alias_name_string(app_name)) {
8197 throw IncorrectConstruction("Aliases may not be empty or contain newlines or null characters");
8198 }
8199 if(parent_ != nullptr) {
8200 aliases_.push_back(app_name);
8201 const auto &res = _compare_subcommand_names(*this, *_get_fallthrough_parent());
8202 if(!res.empty()) {
8203 aliases_.pop_back();
8204 throw(OptionAlreadyAdded("alias already matches an existing subcommand: " + app_name));
8205 }
8206 } else {
8207 aliases_.push_back(app_name);
8208 }
8209
8210 return this;
8211}
8212
8213CLI11_INLINE App *App::immediate_callback(bool immediate) {
8214 immediate_callback_ = immediate;
8215 if(immediate_callback_) {
8216 if(final_callback_ && !(parse_complete_callback_)) {
8217 std::swap(final_callback_, parse_complete_callback_);
8218 }
8219 } else if(!(final_callback_) && parse_complete_callback_) {
8220 std::swap(final_callback_, parse_complete_callback_);
8221 }
8222 return this;
8223}
8224
8225CLI11_INLINE App *App::ignore_case(bool value) {
8226 if(value && !ignore_case_) {
8227 ignore_case_ = true;
8228 auto *p = (parent_ != nullptr) ? _get_fallthrough_parent() : this;
8229 const auto &match = _compare_subcommand_names(*this, *p);
8230 if(!match.empty()) {
8231 ignore_case_ = false; // we are throwing so need to be exception invariant
8232 throw OptionAlreadyAdded("ignore case would cause subcommand name conflicts: " + match);
8233 }
8234 }
8235 ignore_case_ = value;
8236 return this;
8237}
8238
8239CLI11_INLINE App *App::ignore_underscore(bool value) {
8240 if(value && !ignore_underscore_) {
8241 ignore_underscore_ = true;
8242 auto *p = (parent_ != nullptr) ? _get_fallthrough_parent() : this;
8243 const auto &match = _compare_subcommand_names(*this, *p);
8244 if(!match.empty()) {
8245 ignore_underscore_ = false;
8246 throw OptionAlreadyAdded("ignore underscore would cause subcommand name conflicts: " + match);
8247 }
8248 }
8249 ignore_underscore_ = value;
8250 return this;
8251}
8252
8253CLI11_INLINE Option *App::add_option(std::string option_name,
8254 callback_t option_callback,
8255 std::string option_description,
8256 bool defaulted,
8257 std::function<std::string()> func) {
8258 Option myopt{option_name, option_description, option_callback, this, allow_non_standard_options_};
8259
8260 if(std::find_if(std::begin(options_), std::end(options_), [&myopt](const Option_p &v) { return *v == myopt; }) ==
8261 std::end(options_)) {
8262 if(myopt.lnames_.empty() && myopt.snames_.empty()) {
8263 // if the option is positional only there is additional potential for ambiguities in config files and needs
8264 // to be checked
8265 std::string test_name = "--" + myopt.get_single_name();
8266 if(test_name.size() == 3) {
8267 test_name.erase(0, 1);
8268 }
8269
8270 auto *op = get_option_no_throw(test_name);
8271 if(op != nullptr && op->get_configurable()) {
8272 throw(OptionAlreadyAdded("added option positional name matches existing option: " + test_name));
8273 }
8274 } else if(parent_ != nullptr) {
8275 for(auto &ln : myopt.lnames_) {
8276 auto *op = parent_->get_option_no_throw(ln);
8277 if(op != nullptr && op->get_configurable()) {
8278 throw(OptionAlreadyAdded("added option matches existing positional option: " + ln));
8279 }
8280 }
8281 for(auto &sn : myopt.snames_) {
8282 auto *op = parent_->get_option_no_throw(sn);
8283 if(op != nullptr && op->get_configurable()) {
8284 throw(OptionAlreadyAdded("added option matches existing positional option: " + sn));
8285 }
8286 }
8287 }
8288 if(allow_non_standard_options_ && !myopt.snames_.empty()) {
8289 for(auto &sname : myopt.snames_) {
8290 if(sname.length() > 1) {
8291 std::string test_name;
8292 test_name.push_back('-');
8293 test_name.push_back(sname.front());
8294 auto *op = get_option_no_throw(test_name);
8295 if(op != nullptr) {
8296 throw(OptionAlreadyAdded("added option interferes with existing short option: " + sname));
8297 }
8298 }
8299 }
8300 for(auto &opt : options_) {
8301 for(const auto &osn : opt->snames_) {
8302 if(osn.size() > 1) {
8303 std::string test_name;
8304 test_name.push_back(osn.front());
8305 if(myopt.check_sname(test_name)) {
8306 throw(OptionAlreadyAdded("added option interferes with existing non standard option: " +
8307 osn));
8308 }
8309 }
8310 }
8311 }
8312 }
8313 options_.emplace_back();
8314 Option_p &option = options_.back();
8315 option.reset(new Option(option_name, option_description, option_callback, this, allow_non_standard_options_));
8316
8317 // Set the default string capture function
8318 option->default_function(func);
8319
8320 // For compatibility with CLI11 1.7 and before, capture the default string here
8321 if(defaulted)
8322 option->capture_default_str();
8323
8324 // Transfer defaults to the new option
8325 option_defaults_.copy_to(option.get());
8326
8327 // Don't bother to capture if we already did
8328 if(!defaulted && option->get_always_capture_default())
8329 option->capture_default_str();
8330
8331 return option.get();
8332 }
8333 // we know something matches now find what it is so we can produce more error information
8334 for(auto &opt : options_) {
8335 const auto &matchname = opt->matching_name(myopt);
8336 if(!matchname.empty()) {
8337 throw(OptionAlreadyAdded("added option matched existing option name: " + matchname));
8338 }
8339 }
8340 // this line should not be reached the above loop should trigger the throw
8341 throw(OptionAlreadyAdded("added option matched existing option name")); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
8342}
8343
8344CLI11_INLINE Option *App::set_help_flag(std::string flag_name, const std::string &help_description) {
8345 // take flag_description by const reference otherwise add_flag tries to assign to help_description
8346 if(help_ptr_ != nullptr) {
8347 remove_option(help_ptr_);
8348 help_ptr_ = nullptr;
8349 }
8350
8351 // Empty name will simply remove the help flag
8352 if(!flag_name.empty()) {
8353 help_ptr_ = add_flag(flag_name, help_description);
8354 help_ptr_->configurable(false);
8355 }
8356
8357 return help_ptr_;
8358}
8359
8360CLI11_INLINE Option *App::set_help_all_flag(std::string help_name, const std::string &help_description) {
8361 // take flag_description by const reference otherwise add_flag tries to assign to flag_description
8362 if(help_all_ptr_ != nullptr) {
8363 remove_option(help_all_ptr_);
8364 help_all_ptr_ = nullptr;
8365 }
8366
8367 // Empty name will simply remove the help all flag
8368 if(!help_name.empty()) {
8369 help_all_ptr_ = add_flag(help_name, help_description);
8370 help_all_ptr_->configurable(false);
8371 }
8372
8373 return help_all_ptr_;
8374}
8375
8376CLI11_INLINE Option *
8377App::set_version_flag(std::string flag_name, const std::string &versionString, const std::string &version_help) {
8378 // take flag_description by const reference otherwise add_flag tries to assign to version_description
8379 if(version_ptr_ != nullptr) {
8380 remove_option(version_ptr_);
8381 version_ptr_ = nullptr;
8382 }
8383
8384 // Empty name will simply remove the version flag
8385 if(!flag_name.empty()) {
8386 version_ptr_ = add_flag_callback(
8387 flag_name, [versionString]() { throw(CLI::CallForVersion(versionString, 0)); }, version_help);
8388 version_ptr_->configurable(false);
8389 }
8390
8391 return version_ptr_;
8392}
8393
8394CLI11_INLINE Option *
8395App::set_version_flag(std::string flag_name, std::function<std::string()> vfunc, const std::string &version_help) {
8396 if(version_ptr_ != nullptr) {
8397 remove_option(version_ptr_);
8398 version_ptr_ = nullptr;
8399 }
8400
8401 // Empty name will simply remove the version flag
8402 if(!flag_name.empty()) {
8403 version_ptr_ =
8404 add_flag_callback(flag_name, [vfunc]() { throw(CLI::CallForVersion(vfunc(), 0)); }, version_help);
8405 version_ptr_->configurable(false);
8406 }
8407
8408 return version_ptr_;
8409}
8410
8411CLI11_INLINE Option *App::_add_flag_internal(std::string flag_name, CLI::callback_t fun, std::string flag_description) {
8412 Option *opt = nullptr;
8413 if(detail::has_default_flag_values(flag_name)) {
8414 // check for default values and if it has them
8415 auto flag_defaults = detail::get_default_flag_values(flag_name);
8416 detail::remove_default_flag_values(flag_name);
8417 opt = add_option(std::move(flag_name), std::move(fun), std::move(flag_description), false);
8418 for(const auto &fname : flag_defaults)
8419 opt->fnames_.push_back(fname.first);
8420 opt->default_flag_values_ = std::move(flag_defaults);
8421 } else {
8422 opt = add_option(std::move(flag_name), std::move(fun), std::move(flag_description), false);
8423 }
8424 // flags cannot have positional values
8425 if(opt->get_positional()) {
8426 auto pos_name = opt->get_name(true);
8427 remove_option(opt);
8428 throw IncorrectConstruction::PositionalFlag(pos_name);
8429 }
8430 opt->multi_option_policy(MultiOptionPolicy::TakeLast);
8431 opt->expected(0);
8432 opt->required(false);
8433 return opt;
8434}
8435
8436CLI11_INLINE Option *App::add_flag_callback(std::string flag_name,
8437 std::function<void(void)> function,
8438 std::string flag_description) {
8439
8440 CLI::callback_t fun = [function](const CLI::results_t &res) {
8441 using CLI::detail::lexical_cast;
8442 bool trigger{false};
8443 auto result = lexical_cast(res[0], trigger);
8444 if(result && trigger) {
8445 function();
8446 }
8447 return result;
8448 };
8449 return _add_flag_internal(flag_name, std::move(fun), std::move(flag_description));
8450}
8451
8452CLI11_INLINE Option *
8453App::add_flag_function(std::string flag_name,
8454 std::function<void(std::int64_t)> function,
8455 std::string flag_description) {
8456
8457 CLI::callback_t fun = [function](const CLI::results_t &res) {
8458 using CLI::detail::lexical_cast;
8459 std::int64_t flag_count{0};
8460 lexical_cast(res[0], flag_count);
8461 function(flag_count);
8462 return true;
8463 };
8464 return _add_flag_internal(flag_name, std::move(fun), std::move(flag_description))
8465 ->multi_option_policy(MultiOptionPolicy::Sum);
8466}
8467
8468CLI11_INLINE Option *App::set_config(std::string option_name,
8469 std::string default_filename,
8470 const std::string &help_message,
8471 bool config_required) {
8472
8473 // Remove existing config if present
8474 if(config_ptr_ != nullptr) {
8475 remove_option(config_ptr_);
8476 config_ptr_ = nullptr; // need to remove the config_ptr completely
8477 }
8478
8479 // Only add config if option passed
8480 if(!option_name.empty()) {
8481 config_ptr_ = add_option(option_name, help_message);
8482 if(config_required) {
8483 config_ptr_->required();
8484 }
8485 if(!default_filename.empty()) {
8486 config_ptr_->default_str(std::move(default_filename));
8487 config_ptr_->force_callback_ = true;
8488 }
8489 config_ptr_->configurable(false);
8490 // set the option to take the last value and reverse given by default
8491 config_ptr_->multi_option_policy(MultiOptionPolicy::Reverse);
8492 }
8493
8494 return config_ptr_;
8495}
8496
8497CLI11_INLINE bool App::remove_option(Option *opt) {
8498 // Make sure no links exist
8499 for(Option_p &op : options_) {
8500 op->remove_needs(opt);
8501 op->remove_excludes(opt);
8502 }
8503
8504 if(help_ptr_ == opt)
8505 help_ptr_ = nullptr;
8506 if(help_all_ptr_ == opt)
8507 help_all_ptr_ = nullptr;
8508
8509 auto iterator =
8510 std::find_if(std::begin(options_), std::end(options_), [opt](const Option_p &v) { return v.get() == opt; });
8511 if(iterator != std::end(options_)) {
8512 options_.erase(iterator);
8513 return true;
8514 }
8515 return false;
8516}
8517
8518CLI11_INLINE App *App::add_subcommand(std::string subcommand_name, std::string subcommand_description) {
8519 if(!subcommand_name.empty() && !detail::valid_name_string(subcommand_name)) {
8520 if(!detail::valid_first_char(subcommand_name[0])) {
8521 throw IncorrectConstruction(
8522 "Subcommand name starts with invalid character, '!' and '-' and control characters");
8523 }
8524 for(auto c : subcommand_name) {
8525 if(!detail::valid_later_char(c)) {
8526 throw IncorrectConstruction(std::string("Subcommand name contains invalid character ('") + c +
8527 "'), all characters are allowed except"
8528 "'=',':','{','}', ' ', and control characters");
8529 }
8530 }
8531 }
8532 CLI::App_p subcom = std::shared_ptr<App>(new App(std::move(subcommand_description), subcommand_name, this));
8533 return add_subcommand(std::move(subcom));
8534}
8535
8536CLI11_INLINE App *App::add_subcommand(CLI::App_p subcom) {
8537 if(!subcom)
8538 throw IncorrectConstruction("passed App is not valid");
8539 auto *ckapp = (name_.empty() && parent_ != nullptr) ? _get_fallthrough_parent() : this;
8540 const auto &mstrg = _compare_subcommand_names(*subcom, *ckapp);
8541 if(!mstrg.empty()) {
8542 throw(OptionAlreadyAdded("subcommand name or alias matches existing subcommand: " + mstrg));
8543 }
8544 subcom->parent_ = this;
8545 subcommands_.push_back(std::move(subcom));
8546 return subcommands_.back().get();
8547}
8548
8549CLI11_INLINE bool App::remove_subcommand(App *subcom) {
8550 // Make sure no links exist
8551 for(App_p &sub : subcommands_) {
8552 sub->remove_excludes(subcom);
8553 sub->remove_needs(subcom);
8554 }
8555
8556 auto iterator = std::find_if(
8557 std::begin(subcommands_), std::end(subcommands_), [subcom](const App_p &v) { return v.get() == subcom; });
8558 if(iterator != std::end(subcommands_)) {
8559 subcommands_.erase(iterator);
8560 return true;
8561 }
8562 return false;
8563}
8564
8565CLI11_INLINE App *App::get_subcommand(const App *subcom) const {
8566 if(subcom == nullptr)
8567 throw OptionNotFound("nullptr passed");
8568 for(const App_p &subcomptr : subcommands_)
8569 if(subcomptr.get() == subcom)
8570 return subcomptr.get();
8571 throw OptionNotFound(subcom->get_name());
8572}
8573
8574CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE App *App::get_subcommand(std::string subcom) const {
8575 auto *subc = _find_subcommand(subcom, false, false);
8576 if(subc == nullptr)
8577 throw OptionNotFound(subcom);
8578 return subc;
8579}
8580
8581CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE App *App::get_subcommand_no_throw(std::string subcom) const noexcept {
8582 return _find_subcommand(subcom, false, false);
8583}

8585CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE App *App::get_subcommand(int index) const {
8586 if(index >= 0) {
8587 auto uindex = static_cast<unsigned>(index);
8588 if(uindex < subcommands_.size())
8589 return subcommands_[uindex].get();
8590 }
8591 throw OptionNotFound(std::to_string(index));
8592}

8594CLI11_INLINE CLI::App_p App::get_subcommand_ptr(App *subcom) const {
8595 if(subcom == nullptr)
8596 throw OptionNotFound("nullptr passed");
8597 for(const App_p &subcomptr : subcommands_)
8598 if(subcomptr.get() == subcom)
8599 return subcomptr;
8600 throw OptionNotFound(subcom->get_name());
8601}

8604 for(const App_p &subcomptr : subcommands_)
8605 if(subcomptr->check_name(subcom))
8606 return subcomptr;
8607 throw OptionNotFound(subcom);
8608}

8610CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE CLI::App_p App::get_subcommand_ptr(int index) const {
8611 if(index >= 0) {
8612 auto uindex = static_cast<unsigned>(index);
8613 if(uindex < subcommands_.size())
8614 return subcommands_[uindex];

8616 throw OptionNotFound(std::to_string(index));
8617}
8618
8619CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE CLI::App *App::get_option_group(std::string group_name) const {
8620 for(const App_p &app : subcommands_) {
8621 if(app->name_.empty() && app->group_ == group_name) {
8622 return app.get();
8623 }
8624 }
8625 throw OptionNotFound(group_name);
8626}
8627
8628CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE std::size_t App::count_all() const {
8629 std::size_t cnt{0};
8630 for(const auto &opt : options_) {
8631 cnt += opt->count();
8632 }
8633 for(const auto &sub : subcommands_) {
8634 cnt += sub->count_all();
8635 }
8636 if(!get_name().empty()) { // for named subcommands add the number of times the subcommand was called
8637 cnt += parsed_;
8638 }
8639 return cnt;
8640}
8641
8642CLI11_INLINE void App::clear() {
8643
8644 parsed_ = 0;
8645 pre_parse_called_ = false;
8646
8647 missing_.clear();
8648 parsed_subcommands_.clear();
8649 for(const Option_p &opt : options_) {
8650 opt->clear();
8651 }
8652 for(const App_p &subc : subcommands_) {
8653 subc->clear();
8654 }
8655}
8656
8657CLI11_INLINE void App::parse(int argc, const char *const *argv) { parse_char_t(argc, argv); }
8658CLI11_INLINE void App::parse(int argc, const wchar_t *const *argv) { parse_char_t(argc, argv); }
8659
8660namespace detail {
8661
8662// Do nothing or perform narrowing
8663CLI11_INLINE const char *maybe_narrow(const char *str) { return str; }
8664CLI11_INLINE std::string maybe_narrow(const wchar_t *str) { return narrow(str); }
8665
8666} // namespace detail
8667
8668template <class CharT> CLI11_INLINE void App::parse_char_t(int argc, const CharT *const *argv) {
8669 // If the name is not set, read from command line
8670 if(name_.empty() || has_automatic_name_) {
8671 has_automatic_name_ = true;
8672 name_ = detail::maybe_narrow(argv[0]);
8673 }
8674
8675 std::vector<std::string> args;
8676 args.reserve(static_cast<std::size_t>(argc) - 1U);
8677 for(auto i = static_cast<std::size_t>(argc) - 1U; i > 0U; --i)
8678 args.emplace_back(detail::maybe_narrow(argv[i]));
8679
8680 parse(std::move(args));
8681}
8682
8683CLI11_INLINE void App::parse(std::string commandline, bool program_name_included) {
8684
8685 if(program_name_included) {
8686 auto nstr = detail::split_program_name(commandline);
8687 if((name_.empty()) || (has_automatic_name_)) {
8688 has_automatic_name_ = true;
8689 name_ = nstr.first;
8690 }
8691 commandline = std::move(nstr.second);
8692 } else {
8693 detail::trim(commandline);
8694 }
8695 // the next section of code is to deal with quoted arguments after an '=' or ':' for windows like operations
8696 if(!commandline.empty()) {
8697 commandline = detail::find_and_modify(commandline, "=", detail::escape_detect);
8698 if(allow_windows_style_options_)
8699 commandline = detail::find_and_modify(commandline, ":", detail::escape_detect);
8700 }
8701
8702 auto args = detail::split_up(std::move(commandline));
8703 // remove all empty strings
8704 args.erase(std::remove(args.begin(), args.end(), std::string{}), args.end());
8705 try {
8706 detail::remove_quotes(args);
8707 } catch(const std::invalid_argument &arg) {
8708 throw CLI::ParseError(arg.what(), CLI::ExitCodes::InvalidError);
8709 }
8710 std::reverse(args.begin(), args.end());
8711 parse(std::move(args));
8712}
8713
8714CLI11_INLINE void App::parse(std::wstring commandline, bool program_name_included) {
8715 parse(narrow(commandline), program_name_included);
8716}
8717
8718CLI11_INLINE void App::parse(std::vector<std::string> &args) {
8719 // Clear if parsed
8720 if(parsed_ > 0)
8721 clear();
8722
8723 // parsed_ is incremented in commands/subcommands,
8724 // but placed here to make sure this is cleared when
8725 // running parse after an error is thrown, even by _validate or _configure.
8726 parsed_ = 1;
8727 _validate();
8728 _configure();
8729 // set the parent as nullptr as this object should be the top now
8730 parent_ = nullptr;
8731 parsed_ = 0;
8732
8733 _parse(args);
8734 run_callback();
8735}
8736
8737CLI11_INLINE void App::parse(std::vector<std::string> &&args) {
8738 // Clear if parsed
8739 if(parsed_ > 0)
8740 clear();
8741
8742 // parsed_ is incremented in commands/subcommands,
8743 // but placed here to make sure this is cleared when
8744 // running parse after an error is thrown, even by _validate or _configure.
8745 parsed_ = 1;
8746 _validate();
8747 _configure();
8748 // set the parent as nullptr as this object should be the top now
8749 parent_ = nullptr;
8750 parsed_ = 0;
8751
8752 _parse(std::move(args));
8753 run_callback();
8754}
8755
8756CLI11_INLINE void App::parse_from_stream(std::istream &input) {
8757 if(parsed_ == 0) {
8758 _validate();
8759 _configure();
8760 // set the parent as nullptr as this object should be the top now
8761 }
8762
8763 _parse_stream(input);
8764 run_callback();
8765}
8766
8767CLI11_INLINE int App::exit(const Error &e, std::ostream &out, std::ostream &err) const {
8768
8770 if(e.get_name() == "RuntimeError")
8771 return e.get_exit_code();
8772
8773 if(e.get_name() == "CallForHelp") {
8774 out << help();
8775 return e.get_exit_code();
8776 }
8777
8778 if(e.get_name() == "CallForAllHelp") {
8779 out << help("", AppFormatMode::All);
8780 return e.get_exit_code();
8781 }
8782
8783 if(e.get_name() == "CallForVersion") {
8784 out << e.what() << '\n';
8785 return e.get_exit_code();
8786 }
8787
8788 if(e.get_exit_code() != static_cast<int>(ExitCodes::Success)) {
8789 if(failure_message_)
8790 err << failure_message_(this, e) << std::flush;
8791 }
8792
8793 return e.get_exit_code();
8794}

8796CLI11_INLINE std::vector<const App *> App::get_subcommands(const std::function<bool(const App *)> &filter) const {
8797 std::vector<const App *> subcomms(subcommands_.size());
8798 std::transform(
8799 std::begin(subcommands_), std::end(subcommands_), std::begin(subcomms), [](const App_p &v) { return v.get(); });
8800
8801 if(filter) {
8802 subcomms.erase(std::remove_if(std::begin(subcomms),
8803 std::end(subcomms),
8804 [&filter](const App *app) { return !filter(app); }),
8805 std::end(subcomms));
8806 }
8807
8808 return subcomms;
8809}

8812 std::vector<App *> subcomms(subcommands_.size());
8813 std::transform(
8814 std::begin(subcommands_), std::end(subcommands_), std::begin(subcomms), [](const App_p &v) { return v.get(); });
8815
8816 if(filter) {
8817 subcomms.erase(
8818 std::remove_if(std::begin(subcomms), std::end(subcomms), [&filter](App *app) { return !filter(app); }),
8819 std::end(subcomms));
8820 }
8821
8822 return subcomms;
8823}

8825CLI11_INLINE bool App::remove_excludes(Option *opt) {
8826 auto iterator = std::find(std::begin(exclude_options_), std::end(exclude_options_), opt);
8827 if(iterator == std::end(exclude_options_)) {
8828 return false;
8829 }
8830 exclude_options_.erase(iterator);
8831 return true;
8832}
8833
8834CLI11_INLINE bool App::remove_excludes(App *app) {
8835 auto iterator = std::find(std::begin(exclude_subcommands_), std::end(exclude_subcommands_), app);
8836 if(iterator == std::end(exclude_subcommands_)) {
8837 return false;
8838 }
8839 auto *other_app = *iterator;
8840 exclude_subcommands_.erase(iterator);
8841 other_app->remove_excludes(this);
8842 return true;
8843}
8844
8845CLI11_INLINE bool App::remove_needs(Option *opt) {
8846 auto iterator = std::find(std::begin(need_options_), std::end(need_options_), opt);
8847 if(iterator == std::end(need_options_)) {
8848 return false;
8849 }
8850 need_options_.erase(iterator);
8851 return true;
8852}
8853
8854CLI11_INLINE bool App::remove_needs(App *app) {
8855 auto iterator = std::find(std::begin(need_subcommands_), std::end(need_subcommands_), app);
8856 if(iterator == std::end(need_subcommands_)) {
8857 return false;
8858 }
8859 need_subcommands_.erase(iterator);
8860 return true;
8861}

8863CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE std::string App::help(std::string prev, AppFormatMode mode) const {
8864 if(prev.empty())
8865 prev = get_name();
8866 else
8867 prev += " " + get_name();
8868
8869 // Delegate to subcommand if needed
8870 auto selected_subcommands = get_subcommands();
8871 if(!selected_subcommands.empty()) {
8872 return selected_subcommands.back()->help(prev, mode);
8873 }
8874 return formatter_->make_help(this, prev, mode);
8875}
8876
8877CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE std::string App::version() const {
8878 std::string val;
8879 if(version_ptr_ != nullptr) {
8880 // copy the results for reuse later
8881 results_t rv = version_ptr_->results();
8882 version_ptr_->clear();
8883 version_ptr_->add_result("true");
8884 try {
8885 version_ptr_->run_callback();
8886 } catch(const CLI::CallForVersion &cfv) {
8887 val = cfv.what();
8888 }
8889 version_ptr_->clear();
8890 version_ptr_->add_result(rv);
8891 }
8892 return val;
8893}

8895CLI11_INLINE std::vector<const Option *> App::get_options(const std::function<bool(const Option *)> filter) const {
8896 std::vector<const Option *> options(options_.size());
8897 std::transform(
8898 std::begin(options_), std::end(options_), std::begin(options), [](const Option_p &val) { return val.get(); });
8899
8900 if(filter) {
8901 options.erase(std::remove_if(std::begin(options),
8902 std::end(options),
8903 [&filter](const Option *opt) { return !filter(opt); }),
8904 std::end(options));
8905 }
8906 for(const auto &subcp : subcommands_) {
8907 // also check down into nameless subcommands
8908 const App *subc = subcp.get();
8909 if(subc->get_name().empty() && !subc->get_group().empty() && subc->get_group().front() == '+') {
8910 std::vector<const Option *> subcopts = subc->get_options(filter);
8911 options.insert(options.end(), subcopts.begin(), subcopts.end());
8912 }
8913 }
8914 return options;
8915}
8916
8917CLI11_INLINE std::vector<Option *> App::get_options(const std::function<bool(Option *)> filter) {
8918 std::vector<Option *> options(options_.size());
8919 std::transform(
8920 std::begin(options_), std::end(options_), std::begin(options), [](const Option_p &val) { return val.get(); });
8921
8922 if(filter) {
8923 options.erase(
8924 std::remove_if(std::begin(options), std::end(options), [&filter](Option *opt) { return !filter(opt); }),
8925 std::end(options));
8926 }
8927 for(auto &subc : subcommands_) {
8928 // also check down into nameless subcommands
8929 if(subc->get_name().empty() && !subc->get_group().empty() && subc->get_group().front() == '+') {
8930 auto subcopts = subc->get_options(filter);
8931 options.insert(options.end(), subcopts.begin(), subcopts.end());
8932 }
8933 }
8934 return options;
8935}

8937CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE Option *App::get_option_no_throw(std::string option_name) noexcept {
8938 for(Option_p &opt : options_) {
8939 if(opt->check_name(option_name)) {
8940 return opt.get();
8941 }
8942 }
8943 for(auto &subc : subcommands_) {
8944 // also check down into nameless subcommands
8945 if(subc->get_name().empty()) {
8946 auto *opt = subc->get_option_no_throw(option_name);
8947 if(opt != nullptr) {
8948 return opt;
8949 }
8950 }
8951 }
8952 return nullptr;
8953}
8954
8955CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE const Option *App::get_option_no_throw(std::string option_name) const noexcept {
8956 for(const Option_p &opt : options_) {
8957 if(opt->check_name(option_name)) {
8958 return opt.get();
8959 }
8960 }
8961 for(const auto &subc : subcommands_) {
8962 // also check down into nameless subcommands
8963 if(subc->get_name().empty()) {
8964 auto *opt = subc->get_option_no_throw(option_name);
8965 if(opt != nullptr) {
8966 return opt;
8967 }
8968 }
8969 }
8970 return nullptr;
8971}
8972
8973CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE std::string App::get_display_name(bool with_aliases) const {
8974 if(name_.empty()) {
8975 return std::string("[Option Group: ") + get_group() + "]";
8976 }
8977 if(aliases_.empty() || !with_aliases) {
8978 return name_;
8979 }
8980 std::string dispname = name_;
8981 for(const auto &lalias : aliases_) {
8982 dispname.push_back(',');
8983 dispname.push_back(' ');
8984 dispname.append(lalias);
8985 }
8986 return dispname;
8987}
8988
8989CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE bool App::check_name(std::string name_to_check) const {
8990 std::string local_name = name_;
8991 if(ignore_underscore_) {
8992 local_name = detail::remove_underscore(name_);
8993 name_to_check = detail::remove_underscore(name_to_check);
8994 }
8995 if(ignore_case_) {
8996 local_name = detail::to_lower(name_);
8997 name_to_check = detail::to_lower(name_to_check);
8998 }
8999
9000 if(local_name == name_to_check) {
9001 return true;
9002 }
9003 for(std::string les : aliases_) { // NOLINT(performance-for-range-copy)
9004 if(ignore_underscore_) {
9005 les = detail::remove_underscore(les);
9006 }
9007 if(ignore_case_) {
9008 les = detail::to_lower(les);
9009 }
9010 if(les == name_to_check) {
9011 return true;
9012 }
9013 }
9014 return false;
9015}
9016
9017CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE std::vector<std::string> App::get_groups() const {
9018 std::vector<std::string> groups;
9019
9020 for(const Option_p &opt : options_) {
9021 // Add group if it is not already in there
9022 if(std::find(groups.begin(), groups.end(), opt->get_group()) == groups.end()) {
9023 groups.push_back(opt->get_group());
9024 }
9025 }
9026
9027 return groups;
9028}
9029
9030CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE std::vector<std::string> App::remaining(bool recurse) const {
9031 std::vector<std::string> miss_list;
9032 for(const std::pair<detail::Classifier, std::string> &miss : missing_) {
9033 miss_list.push_back(std::get<1>(miss));
9034 }
9035 // Get from a subcommand that may allow extras
9036 if(recurse) {
9037 if(!allow_extras_) {
9038 for(const auto &sub : subcommands_) {
9039 if(sub->name_.empty() && !sub->missing_.empty()) {
9040 for(const std::pair<detail::Classifier, std::string> &miss : sub->missing_) {
9041 miss_list.push_back(std::get<1>(miss));
9042 }
9043 }
9044 }
9045 }
9046 // Recurse into subcommands
9047
9048 for(const App *sub : parsed_subcommands_) {
9049 std::vector<std::string> output = sub->remaining(recurse);
9050 std::copy(std::begin(output), std::end(output), std::back_inserter(miss_list));
9051 }
9052 }
9053 return miss_list;
9054}
9055
9056CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE std::vector<std::string> App::remaining_for_passthrough(bool recurse) const {
9057 std::vector<std::string> miss_list = remaining(recurse);
9058 std::reverse(std::begin(miss_list), std::end(miss_list));
9059 return miss_list;
9060}
9061
9062CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE std::size_t App::remaining_size(bool recurse) const {
9063 auto remaining_options = static_cast<std::size_t>(std::count_if(
9064 std::begin(missing_), std::end(missing_), [](const std::pair<detail::Classifier, std::string> &val) {
9065 return val.first != detail::Classifier::POSITIONAL_MARK;
9066 }));
9067
9068 if(recurse) {
9069 for(const App_p &sub : subcommands_) {
9070 remaining_options += sub->remaining_size(recurse);
9071 }
9072 }
9073 return remaining_options;
9074}
9075
9076CLI11_INLINE void App::_validate() const {
9077 // count the number of positional only args
9078 auto pcount = std::count_if(std::begin(options_), std::end(options_), [](const Option_p &opt) {
9079 return opt->get_items_expected_max() >= detail::expected_max_vector_size && !opt->nonpositional();
9080 });
9081 if(pcount > 1) {
9082 auto pcount_req = std::count_if(std::begin(options_), std::end(options_), [](const Option_p &opt) {
9083 return opt->get_items_expected_max() >= detail::expected_max_vector_size && !opt->nonpositional() &&
9084 opt->get_required();
9085 });
9086 if(pcount - pcount_req > 1) {
9087 throw InvalidError(name_);
9088 }
9089 }
9090
9091 std::size_t nameless_subs{0};
9092 for(const App_p &app : subcommands_) {
9093 app->_validate();
9094 if(app->get_name().empty())
9095 ++nameless_subs;
9096 }
9097
9098 if(require_option_min_ > 0) {
9099 if(require_option_max_ > 0) {
9100 if(require_option_max_ < require_option_min_) {
9101 throw(InvalidError("Required min options greater than required max options", ExitCodes::InvalidError));
9102 }
9103 }
9104 if(require_option_min_ > (options_.size() + nameless_subs)) {
9105 throw(
9106 InvalidError("Required min options greater than number of available options", ExitCodes::InvalidError));
9107 }
9108 }
9109}
9110
9111CLI11_INLINE void App::_configure() {
9112 if(default_startup == startup_mode::enabled) {
9113 disabled_ = false;
9114 } else if(default_startup == startup_mode::disabled) {
9115 disabled_ = true;
9116 }
9117 for(const App_p &app : subcommands_) {
9118 if(app->has_automatic_name_) {
9119 app->name_.clear();
9120 }
9121 if(app->name_.empty()) {
9122 app->fallthrough_ = false; // make sure fallthrough_ is false to prevent infinite loop
9123 app->prefix_command_ = false;
9124 }
9125 // make sure the parent is set to be this object in preparation for parse
9126 app->parent_ = this;
9127 app->_configure();
9128 }
9129}
9130
9131CLI11_INLINE void App::run_callback(bool final_mode, bool suppress_final_callback) {
9132 pre_callback();
9133 // in the main app if immediate_callback_ is set it runs the main callback before the used subcommands
9134 if(!final_mode && parse_complete_callback_) {
9135 parse_complete_callback_();
9136 }
9137 // run the callbacks for the received subcommands
9138 for(App *subc : get_subcommands()) {
9139 if(subc->parent_ == this) {
9140 subc->run_callback(true, suppress_final_callback);
9141 }
9142 }
9143 // now run callbacks for option_groups
9144 for(auto &subc : subcommands_) {
9145 if(subc->name_.empty() && subc->count_all() > 0) {
9146 subc->run_callback(true, suppress_final_callback);
9147 }
9148 }
9149
9150 // finally run the main callback
9151 if(final_callback_ && (parsed_ > 0) && (!suppress_final_callback)) {
9152 if(!name_.empty() || count_all() > 0 || parent_ == nullptr) {
9153 final_callback_();
9154 }
9155 }
9156}
9157
9158CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE bool App::_valid_subcommand(const std::string &current, bool ignore_used) const {
9159 // Don't match if max has been reached - but still check parents
9160 if(require_subcommand_max_ != 0 && parsed_subcommands_.size() >= require_subcommand_max_ &&
9161 subcommand_fallthrough_) {
9162 return parent_ != nullptr && parent_->_valid_subcommand(current, ignore_used);
9163 }
9164 auto *com = _find_subcommand(current, true, ignore_used);
9165 if(com != nullptr) {
9166 return true;
9167 }
9168 // Check parent if exists, else return false
9169 if(subcommand_fallthrough_) {
9170 return parent_ != nullptr && parent_->_valid_subcommand(current, ignore_used);
9171 }
9172 return false;
9173}
9174
9175CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE detail::Classifier App::_recognize(const std::string &current,
9176 bool ignore_used_subcommands) const {
9177 std::string dummy1, dummy2;
9178
9179 if(current == "--")
9180 return detail::Classifier::POSITIONAL_MARK;
9181 if(_valid_subcommand(current, ignore_used_subcommands))
9182 return detail::Classifier::SUBCOMMAND;
9183 if(detail::split_long(current, dummy1, dummy2))
9184 return detail::Classifier::LONG;
9185 if(detail::split_short(current, dummy1, dummy2)) {
9186 if(dummy1[0] >= '0' && dummy1[0] <= '9') {
9187 if(get_option_no_throw(std::string{'-', dummy1[0]}) == nullptr) {
9188 return detail::Classifier::NONE;
9189 }
9190 }
9191 return detail::Classifier::SHORT;
9192 }
9193 if((allow_windows_style_options_) && (detail::split_windows_style(current, dummy1, dummy2)))
9194 return detail::Classifier::WINDOWS_STYLE;
9195 if((current == "++") && !name_.empty() && parent_ != nullptr)
9196 return detail::Classifier::SUBCOMMAND_TERMINATOR;
9197 auto dotloc = current.find_first_of('.');
9198 if(dotloc != std::string::npos) {
9199 auto *cm = _find_subcommand(current.substr(0, dotloc), true, ignore_used_subcommands);
9200 if(cm != nullptr) {
9201 auto res = cm->_recognize(current.substr(dotloc + 1), ignore_used_subcommands);
9202 if(res == detail::Classifier::SUBCOMMAND) {
9203 return res;
9204 }
9205 }
9206 }
9207 return detail::Classifier::NONE;
9208}
9209
9210CLI11_INLINE bool App::_process_config_file(const std::string &config_file, bool throw_error) {
9211 auto path_result = detail::check_path(config_file.c_str());
9212 if(path_result == detail::path_type::file) {
9213 try {
9214 std::vector<ConfigItem> values = config_formatter_->from_file(config_file);
9215 _parse_config(values);
9216 return true;
9217 } catch(const FileError &) {
9218 if(throw_error) {
9219 throw;
9220 }
9221 return false;
9222 }
9223 } else if(throw_error) {
9224 throw FileError::Missing(config_file);
9225 } else {
9226 return false;
9227 }
9228}
9229
9230CLI11_INLINE void App::_process_config_file() {
9231 if(config_ptr_ != nullptr) {
9232 bool config_required = config_ptr_->get_required();
9233 auto file_given = config_ptr_->count() > 0;
9234 if(!(file_given || config_ptr_->envname_.empty())) {
9235 std::string ename_string = detail::get_environment_value(config_ptr_->envname_);
9236 if(!ename_string.empty()) {
9237 config_ptr_->add_result(ename_string);
9238 }
9239 }
9240 config_ptr_->run_callback();
9241
9242 auto config_files = config_ptr_->as<std::vector<std::string>>();
9243 bool files_used{file_given};
9244 if(config_files.empty() || config_files.front().empty()) {
9245 if(config_required) {
9246 throw FileError("config file is required but none was given");
9247 }
9248 return;
9249 }
9250 for(const auto &config_file : config_files) {
9251 if(_process_config_file(config_file, config_required || file_given)) {
9252 files_used = true;
9253 }
9254 }
9255 if(!files_used) {
9256 // this is done so the count shows as 0 if no callbacks were processed
9257 config_ptr_->clear();
9258 bool force = config_ptr_->force_callback_;
9259 config_ptr_->force_callback_ = false;
9260 config_ptr_->run_callback();
9261 config_ptr_->force_callback_ = force;
9262 }
9263 }
9264}
9265
9266CLI11_INLINE void App::_process_env() {
9267 for(const Option_p &opt : options_) {
9268 if(opt->count() == 0 && !opt->envname_.empty()) {
9269 std::string ename_string = detail::get_environment_value(opt->envname_);
9270 if(!ename_string.empty()) {
9271 std::string result = ename_string;
9272 result = opt->_validate(result, 0);
9273 if(result.empty()) {
9274 opt->add_result(ename_string);
9275 }
9276 }
9277 }
9278 }
9279
9280 for(App_p &sub : subcommands_) {
9281 if(sub->get_name().empty() || (sub->count_all() > 0 && !sub->parse_complete_callback_)) {
9282 // only process environment variables if the callback has actually been triggered already
9283 sub->_process_env();
9284 }
9285 }
9286}
9287
9288CLI11_INLINE void App::_process_callbacks() {
9289
9290 for(App_p &sub : subcommands_) {
9291 // process the priority option_groups first
9292 if(sub->get_name().empty() && sub->parse_complete_callback_) {
9293 if(sub->count_all() > 0) {
9294 sub->_process_callbacks();
9295 sub->run_callback();
9296 }
9297 }
9298 }
9299
9300 for(const Option_p &opt : options_) {
9301 if((*opt) && !opt->get_callback_run()) {
9302 opt->run_callback();
9303 }
9304 }
9305 for(App_p &sub : subcommands_) {
9306 if(!sub->parse_complete_callback_) {
9307 sub->_process_callbacks();
9308 }
9309 }
9310}
9311
9312CLI11_INLINE void App::_process_help_flags(bool trigger_help, bool trigger_all_help) const {
9313 const Option *help_ptr = get_help_ptr();
9314 const Option *help_all_ptr = get_help_all_ptr();
9315
9316 if(help_ptr != nullptr && help_ptr->count() > 0)
9317 trigger_help = true;
9318 if(help_all_ptr != nullptr && help_all_ptr->count() > 0)
9319 trigger_all_help = true;
9320
9321 // If there were parsed subcommands, call those. First subcommand wins if there are multiple ones.
9322 if(!parsed_subcommands_.empty()) {
9323 for(const App *sub : parsed_subcommands_)
9324 sub->_process_help_flags(trigger_help, trigger_all_help);
9325
9326 // Only the final subcommand should call for help. All help wins over help.
9327 } else if(trigger_all_help) {
9328 throw CallForAllHelp();
9329 } else if(trigger_help) {
9330 throw CallForHelp();
9331 }
9332}
9333
9334CLI11_INLINE void App::_process_requirements() {
9335 // check excludes
9336 bool excluded{false};
9337 std::string excluder;
9338 for(const auto &opt : exclude_options_) {
9339 if(opt->count() > 0) {
9340 excluded = true;
9341 excluder = opt->get_name();
9342 }
9343 }
9344 for(const auto &subc : exclude_subcommands_) {
9345 if(subc->count_all() > 0) {
9346 excluded = true;
9347 excluder = subc->get_display_name();
9348 }
9349 }
9350 if(excluded) {
9351 if(count_all() > 0) {
9352 throw ExcludesError(get_display_name(), excluder);
9353 }
9354 // if we are excluded but didn't receive anything, just return
9355 return;
9356 }
9357
9358 // check excludes
9359 bool missing_needed{false};
9360 std::string missing_need;
9361 for(const auto &opt : need_options_) {
9362 if(opt->count() == 0) {
9363 missing_needed = true;
9364 missing_need = opt->get_name();
9365 }
9366 }
9367 for(const auto &subc : need_subcommands_) {
9368 if(subc->count_all() == 0) {
9369 missing_needed = true;
9370 missing_need = subc->get_display_name();
9371 }
9372 }
9373 if(missing_needed) {
9374 if(count_all() > 0) {
9375 throw RequiresError(get_display_name(), missing_need);
9376 }
9377 // if we missing something but didn't have any options, just return
9378 return;
9379 }
9380
9381 std::size_t used_options = 0;
9382 for(const Option_p &opt : options_) {
9383
9384 if(opt->count() != 0) {
9385 ++used_options;
9386 }
9387 // Required but empty
9388 if(opt->get_required() && opt->count() == 0) {
9389 throw RequiredError(opt->get_name());
9390 }
9391 // Requires
9392 for(const Option *opt_req : opt->needs_)
9393 if(opt->count() > 0 && opt_req->count() == 0)
9394 throw RequiresError(opt->get_name(), opt_req->get_name());
9395 // Excludes
9396 for(const Option *opt_ex : opt->excludes_)
9397 if(opt->count() > 0 && opt_ex->count() != 0)
9398 throw ExcludesError(opt->get_name(), opt_ex->get_name());
9399 }
9400 // check for the required number of subcommands
9401 if(require_subcommand_min_ > 0) {
9402 auto selected_subcommands = get_subcommands();
9403 if(require_subcommand_min_ > selected_subcommands.size())
9404 throw RequiredError::Subcommand(require_subcommand_min_);
9405 }
9406
9407 // Max error cannot occur, the extra subcommand will parse as an ExtrasError or a remaining item.
9408
9409 // run this loop to check how many unnamed subcommands were actually used since they are considered options
9410 // from the perspective of an App
9411 for(App_p &sub : subcommands_) {
9412 if(sub->disabled_)
9413 continue;
9414 if(sub->name_.empty() && sub->count_all() > 0) {
9415 ++used_options;
9416 }
9417 }
9418
9419 if(require_option_min_ > used_options || (require_option_max_ > 0 && require_option_max_ < used_options)) {
9420 auto option_list = detail::join(options_, [this](const Option_p &ptr) {
9421 if(ptr.get() == help_ptr_ || ptr.get() == help_all_ptr_) {
9422 return std::string{};
9423 }
9424 return ptr->get_name(false, true);
9425 });
9426
9427 auto subc_list = get_subcommands([](App *app) { return ((app->get_name().empty()) && (!app->disabled_)); });
9428 if(!subc_list.empty()) {
9429 option_list += "," + detail::join(subc_list, [](const App *app) { return app->get_display_name(); });
9430 }
9431 throw RequiredError::Option(require_option_min_, require_option_max_, used_options, option_list);
9432 }
9433
9434 // now process the requirements for subcommands if needed
9435 for(App_p &sub : subcommands_) {
9436 if(sub->disabled_)
9437 continue;
9438 if(sub->name_.empty() && sub->required_ == false) {
9439 if(sub->count_all() == 0) {
9440 if(require_option_min_ > 0 && require_option_min_ <= used_options) {
9441 continue;
9442 // if we have met the requirement and there is nothing in this option group skip checking
9443 // requirements
9444 }
9445 if(require_option_max_ > 0 && used_options >= require_option_min_) {
9446 continue;
9447 // if we have met the requirement and there is nothing in this option group skip checking
9448 // requirements
9449 }
9450 }
9451 }
9452 if(sub->count() > 0 || sub->name_.empty()) {
9453 sub->_process_requirements();
9454 }
9455
9456 if(sub->required_ && sub->count_all() == 0) {
9457 throw(CLI::RequiredError(sub->get_display_name()));
9458 }
9459 }
9460}
9461
9462CLI11_INLINE void App::_process() {
9463 // help takes precedence over other potential errors and config and environment shouldn't be processed if help
9464 // throws
9465 _process_help_flags();
9466 try {
9467 // the config file might generate a FileError but that should not be processed until later in the process
9468 // to allow for help, version and other errors to generate first.
9469 _process_config_file();
9470
9471 // process env shouldn't throw but no reason to process it if config generated an error
9472 _process_env();
9473 } catch(const CLI::FileError &) {
9474 // callbacks can generate exceptions which should take priority
9475 // over the config file error if one exists.
9476 _process_callbacks();
9477 throw;
9478 }
9479
9480 _process_callbacks();
9481
9482 _process_requirements();
9483}
9484
9485CLI11_INLINE void App::_process_extras() {
9486 if(!(allow_extras_ || prefix_command_)) {
9487 std::size_t num_left_over = remaining_size();
9488 if(num_left_over > 0) {
9489 throw ExtrasError(name_, remaining(false));
9490 }
9491 }
9492
9493 for(App_p &sub : subcommands_) {
9494 if(sub->count() > 0)
9495 sub->_process_extras();
9496 }
9497}
9498
9499CLI11_INLINE void App::_process_extras(std::vector<std::string> &args) {
9500 if(!(allow_extras_ || prefix_command_)) {
9501 std::size_t num_left_over = remaining_size();
9502 if(num_left_over > 0) {
9503 args = remaining(false);
9504 throw ExtrasError(name_, args);
9505 }
9506 }
9507
9508 for(App_p &sub : subcommands_) {
9509 if(sub->count() > 0)
9510 sub->_process_extras(args);
9511 }
9512}
9513
9514CLI11_INLINE void App::increment_parsed() {
9515 ++parsed_;
9516 for(App_p &sub : subcommands_) {
9517 if(sub->get_name().empty())
9518 sub->increment_parsed();
9519 }
9520}
9521
9522CLI11_INLINE void App::_parse(std::vector<std::string> &args) {
9523 increment_parsed();
9524 _trigger_pre_parse(args.size());
9525 bool positional_only = false;
9526
9527 while(!args.empty()) {
9528 if(!_parse_single(args, positional_only)) {
9529 break;
9530 }
9531 }
9532
9533 if(parent_ == nullptr) {
9534 _process();
9535
9536 // Throw error if any items are left over (depending on settings)
9537 _process_extras(args);
9538
9539 // Convert missing (pairs) to extras (string only) ready for processing in another app
9540 args = remaining_for_passthrough(false);
9541 } else if(parse_complete_callback_) {
9542 _process_env();
9543 _process_callbacks();
9544 _process_help_flags();
9545 _process_requirements();
9546 run_callback(false, true);
9547 }
9548}
9549
9550CLI11_INLINE void App::_parse(std::vector<std::string> &&args) {
9551 // this can only be called by the top level in which case parent == nullptr by definition
9552 // operation is simplified
9553 increment_parsed();
9554 _trigger_pre_parse(args.size());
9555 bool positional_only = false;
9556
9557 while(!args.empty()) {
9558 _parse_single(args, positional_only);
9559 }
9560 _process();
9561
9562 // Throw error if any items are left over (depending on settings)
9563 _process_extras();
9564}
9565
9566CLI11_INLINE void App::_parse_stream(std::istream &input) {
9567 auto values = config_formatter_->from_config(input);
9568 _parse_config(values);
9569 increment_parsed();
9570 _trigger_pre_parse(values.size());
9571 _process();
9572
9573 // Throw error if any items are left over (depending on settings)
9574 _process_extras();
9575}
9576
9577CLI11_INLINE void App::_parse_config(const std::vector<ConfigItem> &args) {
9578 for(const ConfigItem &item : args) {
9579 if(!_parse_single_config(item) && allow_config_extras_ == config_extras_mode::error)
9580 throw ConfigError::Extras(item.fullname());
9581 }
9582}
9583
9584CLI11_INLINE bool App::_parse_single_config(const ConfigItem &item, std::size_t level) {
9585
9586 if(level < item.parents.size()) {
9587 auto *subcom = get_subcommand_no_throw(item.parents.at(level));
9588 return (subcom != nullptr) ? subcom->_parse_single_config(item, level + 1) : false;
9589 }
9590 // check for section open
9591 if(item.name == "++") {
9592 if(configurable_) {
9593 increment_parsed();
9594 _trigger_pre_parse(2);
9595 if(parent_ != nullptr) {
9596 parent_->parsed_subcommands_.push_back(this);
9597 }
9598 }
9599 return true;
9600 }
9601 // check for section close
9602 if(item.name == "--") {
9603 if(configurable_ && parse_complete_callback_) {
9604 _process_callbacks();
9605 _process_requirements();
9606 run_callback();
9607 }
9608 return true;
9609 }
9610 Option *op = get_option_no_throw("--" + item.name);
9611 if(op == nullptr) {
9612 if(item.name.size() == 1) {
9613 op = get_option_no_throw("-" + item.name);
9614 }
9615 if(op == nullptr) {
9616 op = get_option_no_throw(item.name);
9617 } else if(!op->get_configurable()) {
9618 auto *testop = get_option_no_throw(item.name);
9619 if(testop != nullptr && testop->get_configurable()) {
9620 op = testop;
9621 }
9622 }
9623 } else if(!op->get_configurable()) {
9624 if(item.name.size() == 1) {
9625 auto *testop = get_option_no_throw("-" + item.name);
9626 if(testop != nullptr && testop->get_configurable()) {
9627 op = testop;
9628 }
9629 }
9630 if(!op->get_configurable()) {
9631 auto *testop = get_option_no_throw(item.name);
9632 if(testop != nullptr && testop->get_configurable()) {
9633 op = testop;
9634 }
9635 }
9636 }
9637
9638 if(op == nullptr) {
9639 // If the option was not present
9640 if(get_allow_config_extras() == config_extras_mode::capture) {
9641 // Should we worry about classifying the extras properly?
9642 missing_.emplace_back(detail::Classifier::NONE, item.fullname());
9643 for(const auto &input : item.inputs) {
9644 missing_.emplace_back(detail::Classifier::NONE, input);
9645 }
9646 }
9647 return false;
9648 }
9649
9650 if(!op->get_configurable()) {
9651 if(get_allow_config_extras() == config_extras_mode::ignore_all) {
9652 return false;
9653 }
9654 throw ConfigError::NotConfigurable(item.fullname());
9655 }
9656 if(op->empty()) {
9657 std::vector<std::string> buffer; // a buffer to use for copying an modifying inputs in a few cases
9658 bool useBuffer{false};
9659 if(item.multiline) {
9660 if(!op->get_inject_separator()) {
9661 buffer = item.inputs;
9662 buffer.erase(std::remove(buffer.begin(), buffer.end(), "%%"), buffer.end());
9663 useBuffer = true;
9664 }
9665 }
9666 const std::vector<std::string> &inputs = (useBuffer) ? buffer : item.inputs;
9667 if(op->get_expected_min() == 0) {
9668 if(item.inputs.size() <= 1) {
9669 // Flag parsing
9670 auto res = config_formatter_->to_flag(item);
9671 bool converted{false};
9672 if(op->get_disable_flag_override()) {
9673 auto val = detail::to_flag_value(res);
9674 if(val == 1) {
9675 res = op->get_flag_value(item.name, "{}");
9676 converted = true;
9677 }
9678 }
9679
9680 if(!converted) {
9681 errno = 0;
9682 if(res != "{}" || op->get_expected_max() <= 1) {
9683 res = op->get_flag_value(item.name, res);
9684 }
9685 }
9686
9687 op->add_result(res);
9688 return true;
9689 }
9690 if(static_cast<int>(inputs.size()) > op->get_items_expected_max() &&
9691 op->get_multi_option_policy() != MultiOptionPolicy::TakeAll) {
9692 if(op->get_items_expected_max() > 1) {
9693 throw ArgumentMismatch::AtMost(item.fullname(), op->get_items_expected_max(), inputs.size());
9694 }
9695
9696 if(!op->get_disable_flag_override()) {
9697 throw ConversionError::TooManyInputsFlag(item.fullname());
9698 }
9699 // if the disable flag override is set then we must have the flag values match a known flag value
9700 // this is true regardless of the output value, so an array input is possible and must be accounted for
9701 for(const auto &res : inputs) {
9702 bool valid_value{false};
9703 if(op->default_flag_values_.empty()) {
9704 if(res == "true" || res == "false" || res == "1" || res == "0") {
9705 valid_value = true;
9706 }
9707 } else {
9708 for(const auto &valid_res : op->default_flag_values_) {
9709 if(valid_res.second == res) {
9710 valid_value = true;
9711 break;
9712 }
9713 }
9714 }
9715
9716 if(valid_value) {
9717 op->add_result(res);
9718 } else {
9719 throw InvalidError("invalid flag argument given");
9720 }
9721 }
9722 return true;
9723 }
9724 }
9725 op->add_result(inputs);
9726 op->run_callback();
9727 }
9728
9729 return true;
9730}
9731
9732CLI11_INLINE bool App::_parse_single(std::vector<std::string> &args, bool &positional_only) {
9733 bool retval = true;
9734 detail::Classifier classifier = positional_only ? detail::Classifier::NONE : _recognize(args.back());
9735 switch(classifier) {
9736 case detail::Classifier::POSITIONAL_MARK:
9737 args.pop_back();
9738 positional_only = true;
9739 if((!_has_remaining_positionals()) && (parent_ != nullptr)) {
9740 retval = false;
9741 } else {
9742 _move_to_missing(classifier, "--");
9743 }
9744 break;
9745 case detail::Classifier::SUBCOMMAND_TERMINATOR:
9746 // treat this like a positional mark if in the parent app
9747 args.pop_back();
9748 retval = false;
9749 break;
9750 case detail::Classifier::SUBCOMMAND:
9751 retval = _parse_subcommand(args);
9752 break;
9753 case detail::Classifier::LONG:
9754 case detail::Classifier::SHORT:
9755 case detail::Classifier::WINDOWS_STYLE:
9756 // If already parsed a subcommand, don't accept options_
9757 retval = _parse_arg(args, classifier, false);
9758 break;
9759 case detail::Classifier::NONE:
9760 // Probably a positional or something for a parent (sub)command
9761 retval = _parse_positional(args, false);
9762 if(retval && positionals_at_end_) {
9763 positional_only = true;
9764 }
9765 break;
9766 // LCOV_EXCL_START
9767 default:
9768 throw HorribleError("unrecognized classifier (you should not see this!)");
9769 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
9770 }
9771 return retval;
9772}
9773
9774CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE std::size_t App::_count_remaining_positionals(bool required_only) const {
9775 std::size_t retval = 0;
9776 for(const Option_p &opt : options_) {
9777 if(opt->get_positional() && (!required_only || opt->get_required())) {
9778 if(opt->get_items_expected_min() > 0 && static_cast<int>(opt->count()) < opt->get_items_expected_min()) {
9779 retval += static_cast<std::size_t>(opt->get_items_expected_min()) - opt->count();
9780 }
9781 }
9782 }
9783 return retval;
9784}
9785
9786CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE bool App::_has_remaining_positionals() const {
9787 for(const Option_p &opt : options_) {
9788 if(opt->get_positional() && ((static_cast<int>(opt->count()) < opt->get_items_expected_min()))) {
9789 return true;
9790 }
9791 }
9792
9793 return false;
9794}
9795
9796CLI11_INLINE bool App::_parse_positional(std::vector<std::string> &args, bool haltOnSubcommand) {
9797
9798 const std::string &positional = args.back();
9799 Option *posOpt{nullptr};
9800
9801 if(positionals_at_end_) {
9802 // deal with the case of required arguments at the end which should take precedence over other arguments
9803 auto arg_rem = args.size();
9804 auto remreq = _count_remaining_positionals(true);
9805 if(arg_rem <= remreq) {
9806 for(const Option_p &opt : options_) {
9807 if(opt->get_positional() && opt->required_) {
9808 if(static_cast<int>(opt->count()) < opt->get_items_expected_min()) {
9809 if(validate_positionals_) {
9810 std::string pos = positional;
9811 pos = opt->_validate(pos, 0);
9812 if(!pos.empty()) {
9813 continue;
9814 }
9815 }
9816 posOpt = opt.get();
9817 break;
9818 }
9819 }
9820 }
9821 }
9822 }
9823 if(posOpt == nullptr) {
9824 for(const Option_p &opt : options_) {
9825 // Eat options, one by one, until done
9826 if(opt->get_positional() &&
9827 (static_cast<int>(opt->count()) < opt->get_items_expected_max() || opt->get_allow_extra_args())) {
9828 if(validate_positionals_) {
9829 std::string pos = positional;
9830 pos = opt->_validate(pos, 0);
9831 if(!pos.empty()) {
9832 continue;
9833 }
9834 }
9835 posOpt = opt.get();
9836 break;
9837 }
9838 }
9839 }
9840 if(posOpt != nullptr) {
9841 parse_order_.push_back(posOpt);
9842 if(posOpt->get_inject_separator()) {
9843 if(!posOpt->results().empty() && !posOpt->results().back().empty()) {
9844 posOpt->add_result(std::string{});
9845 }
9846 }
9847 if(posOpt->get_trigger_on_parse() && posOpt->current_option_state_ == Option::option_state::callback_run) {
9848 posOpt->clear();
9849 }
9850 posOpt->add_result(positional);
9851 if(posOpt->get_trigger_on_parse()) {
9852 posOpt->run_callback();
9853 }
9854
9855 args.pop_back();
9856 return true;
9857 }
9858
9859 for(auto &subc : subcommands_) {
9860 if((subc->name_.empty()) && (!subc->disabled_)) {
9861 if(subc->_parse_positional(args, false)) {
9862 if(!subc->pre_parse_called_) {
9863 subc->_trigger_pre_parse(args.size());
9864 }
9865 return true;
9866 }
9867 }
9868 }
9869 // let the parent deal with it if possible
9870 if(parent_ != nullptr && fallthrough_) {
9871 return _get_fallthrough_parent()->_parse_positional(args, static_cast<bool>(parse_complete_callback_));
9872 }
9874 auto *com = _find_subcommand(args.back(), true, false);
9875 if(com != nullptr && (require_subcommand_max_ == 0 || require_subcommand_max_ > parsed_subcommands_.size())) {
9876 if(haltOnSubcommand) {
9877 return false;
9878 }
9879 args.pop_back();
9880 com->_parse(args);
9881 return true;
9882 }
9883 if(subcommand_fallthrough_) {
9886 auto *parent_app = (parent_ != nullptr) ? _get_fallthrough_parent() : this;
9887 com = parent_app->_find_subcommand(args.back(), true, false);
9888 if(com != nullptr && (com->parent_->require_subcommand_max_ == 0 ||
9889 com->parent_->require_subcommand_max_ > com->parent_->parsed_subcommands_.size())) {
9890 return false;
9891 }
9892 }
9893 if(positionals_at_end_) {
9894 throw CLI::ExtrasError(name_, args);
9895 }
9897 if(parent_ != nullptr && name_.empty()) {
9898 return false;
9899 }
9901 _move_to_missing(detail::Classifier::NONE, positional);
9902 args.pop_back();
9903 if(prefix_command_) {
9904 while(!args.empty()) {
9905 _move_to_missing(detail::Classifier::NONE, args.back());
9906 args.pop_back();
9907 }
9908 }
9909
9910 return true;
9911}
9912
9913CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE App *
9914App::_find_subcommand(const std::string &subc_name, bool ignore_disabled, bool ignore_used) const noexcept {
9915 for(const App_p &com : subcommands_) {
9916 if(com->disabled_ && ignore_disabled)
9917 continue;
9918 if(com->get_name().empty()) {
9919 auto *subc = com->_find_subcommand(subc_name, ignore_disabled, ignore_used);
9920 if(subc != nullptr) {
9921 return subc;
9922 }
9923 }
9924 if(com->check_name(subc_name)) {
9925 if((!*com) || !ignore_used)
9926 return com.get();
9927 }
9928 }
9929 return nullptr;
9930}
9931
9932CLI11_INLINE bool App::_parse_subcommand(std::vector<std::string> &args) {
9933 if(_count_remaining_positionals(/* required */ true) > 0) {
9934 _parse_positional(args, false);
9935 return true;
9936 }
9937 auto *com = _find_subcommand(args.back(), true, true);
9938 if(com == nullptr) {
9939 // the main way to get here is using .notation
9940 auto dotloc = args.back().find_first_of('.');
9941 if(dotloc != std::string::npos) {
9942 com = _find_subcommand(args.back().substr(0, dotloc), true, true);
9943 if(com != nullptr) {
9944 args.back() = args.back().substr(dotloc + 1);
9945 args.push_back(com->get_display_name());
9946 }
9947 }
9948 }
9949 if(com != nullptr) {
9950 args.pop_back();
9951 if(!com->silent_) {
9952 parsed_subcommands_.push_back(com);
9953 }
9954 com->_parse(args);
9955 auto *parent_app = com->parent_;
9956 while(parent_app != this) {
9957 parent_app->_trigger_pre_parse(args.size());
9958 if(!com->silent_) {
9959 parent_app->parsed_subcommands_.push_back(com);
9960 }
9961 parent_app = parent_app->parent_;
9962 }
9963 return true;
9964 }
9965
9966 if(parent_ == nullptr)
9967 throw HorribleError("Subcommand " + args.back() + " missing");
9968 return false;
9969}
9970
9971CLI11_INLINE bool
9972App::_parse_arg(std::vector<std::string> &args, detail::Classifier current_type, bool local_processing_only) {
9973
9974 std::string current = args.back();
9975
9976 std::string arg_name;
9977 std::string value;
9978 std::string rest;
9979
9980 switch(current_type) {
9981 case detail::Classifier::LONG:
9982 if(!detail::split_long(current, arg_name, value))
9983 throw HorribleError("Long parsed but missing (you should not see this):" + args.back());
9984 break;
9985 case detail::Classifier::SHORT:
9986 if(!detail::split_short(current, arg_name, rest))
9987 throw HorribleError("Short parsed but missing! You should not see this");
9988 break;
9989 case detail::Classifier::WINDOWS_STYLE:
9990 if(!detail::split_windows_style(current, arg_name, value))
9991 throw HorribleError("windows option parsed but missing! You should not see this");
9992 break;
9993 case detail::Classifier::SUBCOMMAND:
9994 case detail::Classifier::SUBCOMMAND_TERMINATOR:
9995 case detail::Classifier::POSITIONAL_MARK:
9996 case detail::Classifier::NONE:
9997 default:
9998 throw HorribleError("parsing got called with invalid option! You should not see this");
9999 }
10000
10001 auto op_ptr = std::find_if(std::begin(options_), std::end(options_), [arg_name, current_type](const Option_p &opt) {
10002 if(current_type == detail::Classifier::LONG)
10003 return opt->check_lname(arg_name);
10004 if(current_type == detail::Classifier::SHORT)
10005 return opt->check_sname(arg_name);
10006 // this will only get called for detail::Classifier::WINDOWS_STYLE
10007 return opt->check_lname(arg_name) || opt->check_sname(arg_name);
10008 });
10009
10010 // Option not found
10011 while(op_ptr == std::end(options_)) {
10012 // using while so we can break
10013 for(auto &subc : subcommands_) {
10014 if(subc->name_.empty() && !subc->disabled_) {
10015 if(subc->_parse_arg(args, current_type, local_processing_only)) {
10016 if(!subc->pre_parse_called_) {
10017 subc->_trigger_pre_parse(args.size());
10018 }
10019 return true;
10020 }
10021 }
10022 }
10023 if(allow_non_standard_options_ && current_type == detail::Classifier::SHORT && current.size() > 2) {
10024 std::string narg_name;
10025 std::string nvalue;
10026 detail::split_long(std::string{'-'} + current, narg_name, nvalue);
10027 op_ptr = std::find_if(std::begin(options_), std::end(options_), [narg_name](const Option_p &opt) {
10028 return opt->check_sname(narg_name);
10029 });
10030 if(op_ptr != std::end(options_)) {
10031 arg_name = narg_name;
10032 value = nvalue;
10033 rest.clear();
10034 break;
10035 }
10036 }
10037
10038 // don't capture missing if this is a nameless subcommand and nameless subcommands can't fallthrough
10039 if(parent_ != nullptr && name_.empty()) {
10040 return false;
10041 }
10042
10043 // now check for '.' notation of subcommands
10044 auto dotloc = arg_name.find_first_of('.', 1);
10045 if(dotloc != std::string::npos) {
10046 // using dot notation is equivalent to single argument subcommand
10047 auto *sub = _find_subcommand(arg_name.substr(0, dotloc), true, false);
10048 if(sub != nullptr) {
10049 std::string v = args.back();
10050 args.pop_back();
10051 arg_name = arg_name.substr(dotloc + 1);
10052 if(arg_name.size() > 1) {
10053 args.push_back(std::string("--") + v.substr(dotloc + 3));
10054 current_type = detail::Classifier::LONG;
10055 } else {
10056 auto nval = v.substr(dotloc + 2);
10057 nval.front() = '-';
10058 if(nval.size() > 2) {
10059 // '=' not allowed in short form arguments
10060 args.push_back(nval.substr(3));
10061 nval.resize(2);
10062 }
10063 args.push_back(nval);
10064 current_type = detail::Classifier::SHORT;
10065 }
10066 auto val = sub->_parse_arg(args, current_type, true);
10067 if(val) {
10068 if(!sub->silent_) {
10069 parsed_subcommands_.push_back(sub);
10070 }
10071 // deal with preparsing
10072 increment_parsed();
10073 _trigger_pre_parse(args.size());
10074 // run the parse complete callback since the subcommand processing is now complete
10075 if(sub->parse_complete_callback_) {
10076 sub->_process_env();
10077 sub->_process_callbacks();
10078 sub->_process_help_flags();
10079 sub->_process_requirements();
10080 sub->run_callback(false, true);
10081 }
10082 return true;
10083 }
10084 args.pop_back();
10085 args.push_back(v);
10086 }
10087 }
10088 if(local_processing_only) {
10089 return false;
10090 }
10091 // If a subcommand, try the main command
10092 if(parent_ != nullptr && fallthrough_)
10093 return _get_fallthrough_parent()->_parse_arg(args, current_type, false);
10094
10095 // Otherwise, add to missing
10096 args.pop_back();
10097 _move_to_missing(current_type, current);
10098 return true;
10099 }
10100
10101 args.pop_back();
10102
10103 // Get a reference to the pointer to make syntax bearable
10104 Option_p &op = *op_ptr;
10106 if(op->get_inject_separator()) {
10107 if(!op->results().empty() && !op->results().back().empty()) {
10108 op->add_result(std::string{});
10109 }
10110 }
10111 if(op->get_trigger_on_parse() && op->current_option_state_ == Option::option_state::callback_run) {
10112 op->clear();
10113 }
10114 int min_num = (std::min)(op->get_type_size_min(), op->get_items_expected_min());
10115 int max_num = op->get_items_expected_max();
10116 // check container like options to limit the argument size to a single type if the allow_extra_flags argument is
10117 // set. 16 is somewhat arbitrary (needs to be at least 4)
10118 if(max_num >= detail::expected_max_vector_size / 16 && !op->get_allow_extra_args()) {
10119 auto tmax = op->get_type_size_max();
10120 max_num = detail::checked_multiply(tmax, op->get_expected_min()) ? tmax : detail::expected_max_vector_size;
10121 }
10122 // Make sure we always eat the minimum for unlimited vectors
10123 int collected = 0; // total number of arguments collected
10124 int result_count = 0; // local variable for number of results in a single arg string
10125 // deal with purely flag like things
10126 if(max_num == 0) {
10127 auto res = op->get_flag_value(arg_name, value);
10128 op->add_result(res);
10129 parse_order_.push_back(op.get());
10130 } else if(!value.empty()) { // --this=value
10131 op->add_result(value, result_count);
10132 parse_order_.push_back(op.get());
10133 collected += result_count;
10134 // -Trest
10135 } else if(!rest.empty()) {
10136 op->add_result(rest, result_count);
10137 parse_order_.push_back(op.get());
10138 rest = "";
10139 collected += result_count;
10140 }
10141
10142 // gather the minimum number of arguments
10143 while(min_num > collected && !args.empty()) {
10144 std::string current_ = args.back();
10145 args.pop_back();
10146 op->add_result(current_, result_count);
10147 parse_order_.push_back(op.get());
10148 collected += result_count;
10149 }
10150
10151 if(min_num > collected) { // if we have run out of arguments and the minimum was not met
10152 throw ArgumentMismatch::TypedAtLeast(op->get_name(), min_num, op->get_type_name());
10153 }
10154
10155 // now check for optional arguments
10156 if(max_num > collected || op->get_allow_extra_args()) { // we allow optional arguments
10157 auto remreqpos = _count_remaining_positionals(true);
10158 // we have met the minimum now optionally check up to the maximum
10159 while((collected < max_num || op->get_allow_extra_args()) && !args.empty() &&
10160 _recognize(args.back(), false) == detail::Classifier::NONE) {
10161 // If any required positionals remain, don't keep eating
10162 if(remreqpos >= args.size()) {
10163 break;
10164 }
10165 if(validate_optional_arguments_) {
10166 std::string arg = args.back();
10167 arg = op->_validate(arg, 0);
10168 if(!arg.empty()) {
10169 break;
10170 }
10171 }
10172 op->add_result(args.back(), result_count);
10173 parse_order_.push_back(op.get());
10174 args.pop_back();
10175 collected += result_count;
10176 }
10177
10178 // Allow -- to end an unlimited list and "eat" it
10179 if(!args.empty() && _recognize(args.back()) == detail::Classifier::POSITIONAL_MARK)
10180 args.pop_back();
10181 // optional flag that didn't receive anything now get the default value
10182 if(min_num == 0 && max_num > 0 && collected == 0) {
10183 auto res = op->get_flag_value(arg_name, std::string{});
10184 op->add_result(res);
10185 parse_order_.push_back(op.get());
10186 }
10187 }
10188 // if we only partially completed a type then add an empty string if allowed for later processing
10189 if(min_num > 0 && (collected % op->get_type_size_max()) != 0) {
10190 if(op->get_type_size_max() != op->get_type_size_min()) {
10191 op->add_result(std::string{});
10192 } else {
10193 throw ArgumentMismatch::PartialType(op->get_name(), op->get_type_size_min(), op->get_type_name());
10194 }
10195 }
10196 if(op->get_trigger_on_parse()) {
10197 op->run_callback();
10198 }
10199 if(!rest.empty()) {
10200 rest = "-" + rest;
10201 args.push_back(rest);
10202 }
10203 return true;
10204}
10205
10206CLI11_INLINE void App::_trigger_pre_parse(std::size_t remaining_args) {
10207 if(!pre_parse_called_) {
10208 pre_parse_called_ = true;
10209 if(pre_parse_callback_) {
10210 pre_parse_callback_(remaining_args);
10211 }
10212 } else if(immediate_callback_) {
10213 if(!name_.empty()) {
10214 auto pcnt = parsed_;
10215 missing_t extras = std::move(missing_);
10216 clear();
10217 parsed_ = pcnt;
10218 pre_parse_called_ = true;
10219 missing_ = std::move(extras);
10220 }
10221 }
10222}
10223
10224CLI11_INLINE App *App::_get_fallthrough_parent() {
10225 if(parent_ == nullptr) {
10226 throw(HorribleError("No Valid parent"));
10227 }
10228 auto *fallthrough_parent = parent_;
10229 while((fallthrough_parent->parent_ != nullptr) && (fallthrough_parent->get_name().empty())) {
10230 fallthrough_parent = fallthrough_parent->parent_;
10231 }
10232 return fallthrough_parent;
10233}
10234
10235CLI11_NODISCARD CLI11_INLINE const std::string &App::_compare_subcommand_names(const App &subcom,
10236 const App &base) const {
10237 static const std::string estring;
10238 if(subcom.disabled_) {
10239 return estring;
10240 }
10241 for(const auto &subc : base.subcommands_) {
10242 if(subc.get() != &subcom) {
10243 if(subc->disabled_) {
10244 continue;
10245 }
10246 if(!subcom.get_name().empty()) {
10247 if(subc->check_name(subcom.get_name())) {
10248 return subcom.get_name();
10249 }
10250 }
10251 if(!subc->get_name().empty()) {
10252 if(subcom.check_name(subc->get_name())) {
10253 return subc->get_name();
10254 }
10255 }
10256 for(const auto &les : subcom.aliases_) {
10257 if(subc->check_name(les)) {
10258 return les;
10259 }
10260 }
10261 // this loop is needed in case of ignore_underscore or ignore_case on one but not the other
10262 for(const auto &les : subc->aliases_) {
10263 if(subcom.check_name(les)) {
10264 return les;
10265 }
10266 }
10267 // if the subcommand is an option group we need to check deeper
10268 if(subc->get_name().empty()) {
10269 const auto &cmpres = _compare_subcommand_names(subcom, *subc);
10270 if(!cmpres.empty()) {
10271 return cmpres;
10272 }
10273 }
10274 // if the test subcommand is an option group we need to check deeper
10275 if(subcom.get_name().empty()) {
10276 const auto &cmpres = _compare_subcommand_names(*subc, subcom);
10277 if(!cmpres.empty()) {
10278 return cmpres;
10279 }
10280 }
10281 }
10282 }
10283 return estring;
10284}
10285
10286CLI11_INLINE void App::_move_to_missing(detail::Classifier val_type, const std::string &val) {
10287 if(allow_extras_ || subcommands_.empty()) {
10288 missing_.emplace_back(val_type, val);
10289 return;
10290 }
10291 // allow extra arguments to be places in an option group if it is allowed there
10292 for(auto &subc : subcommands_) {
10293 if(subc->name_.empty() && subc->allow_extras_) {
10294 subc->missing_.emplace_back(val_type, val);
10295 return;
10296 }
10297 }
10298 // if we haven't found any place to put them yet put them in missing
10299 missing_.emplace_back(val_type, val);
10300}
10301
10302CLI11_INLINE void App::_move_option(Option *opt, App *app) {
10303 if(opt == nullptr) {
10304 throw OptionNotFound("the option is NULL");
10305 }
10306 // verify that the give app is actually a subcommand
10307 bool found = false;
10308 for(auto &subc : subcommands_) {
10309 if(app == subc.get()) {
10310 found = true;
10311 }
10312 }
10313 if(!found) {
10314 throw OptionNotFound("The Given app is not a subcommand");
10315 }
10316
10317 if((help_ptr_ == opt) || (help_all_ptr_ == opt))
10318 throw OptionAlreadyAdded("cannot move help options");
10319
10320 if(config_ptr_ == opt)
10321 throw OptionAlreadyAdded("cannot move config file options");
10322
10323 auto iterator =
10324 std::find_if(std::begin(options_), std::end(options_), [opt](const Option_p &v) { return v.get() == opt; });
10325 if(iterator != std::end(options_)) {
10326 const auto &opt_p = *iterator;
10327 if(std::find_if(std::begin(app->options_), std::end(app->options_), [&opt_p](const Option_p &v) {
10328 return (*v == *opt_p);
10329 }) == std::end(app->options_)) {
10330 // only erase after the insertion was successful
10331 app->options_.push_back(std::move(*iterator));
10332 options_.erase(iterator);
10333 } else {
10334 throw OptionAlreadyAdded("option was not located: " + opt->get_name());
10335 }
10336 } else {
10337 throw OptionNotFound("could not locate the given Option");
10338 }
10339}

10341CLI11_INLINE void TriggerOn(App *trigger_app, App *app_to_enable) {
10342 app_to_enable->enabled_by_default(false);
10343 app_to_enable->disabled_by_default();
10344 trigger_app->preparse_callback([app_to_enable](std::size_t) { app_to_enable->disabled(false); });
10345}
10346
10347CLI11_INLINE void TriggerOn(App *trigger_app, std::vector<App *> apps_to_enable) {
10348 for(auto &app : apps_to_enable) {
10349 app->enabled_by_default(false);
10350 app->disabled_by_default();
10351 }
10352
10353 trigger_app->preparse_callback([apps_to_enable](std::size_t) {
10354 for(const auto &app : apps_to_enable) {
10355 app->disabled(false);
10356 }
10357 });
10358}
10359
10360CLI11_INLINE void TriggerOff(App *trigger_app, App *app_to_enable) {
10361 app_to_enable->disabled_by_default(false);
10362 app_to_enable->enabled_by_default();
10363 trigger_app->preparse_callback([app_to_enable](std::size_t) { app_to_enable->disabled(); });
10364}
10365
10366CLI11_INLINE void TriggerOff(App *trigger_app, std::vector<App *> apps_to_enable) {
10367 for(auto &app : apps_to_enable) {
10368 app->disabled_by_default(false);
10369 app->enabled_by_default();
10370 }
10371
10372 trigger_app->preparse_callback([apps_to_enable](std::size_t) {
10373 for(const auto &app : apps_to_enable) {
10374 app->disabled();
10375 }
10376 });
10377}

10379CLI11_INLINE void deprecate_option(Option *opt, const std::string &replacement) {
10380 Validator deprecate_warning{[opt, replacement](std::string &) {
10381 std::cout << opt->get_name() << " is deprecated please use '" << replacement
10382 << "' instead\n";
10383 return std::string();
10384 },
10385 "DEPRECATED"};
10386 deprecate_warning.application_index(0);
10387 opt->check(deprecate_warning);
10388 if(!replacement.empty()) {
10389 opt->description(opt->get_description() + " DEPRECATED: please use '" + replacement + "' instead");
10390 }
10391}
10392
10393CLI11_INLINE void retire_option(App *app, Option *opt) {
10394 App temp;
10395 auto *option_copy = temp.add_option(opt->get_name(false, true))
10396 ->type_size(opt->get_type_size_min(), opt->get_type_size_max())
10397 ->expected(opt->get_expected_min(), opt->get_expected_max())
10398 ->allow_extra_args(opt->get_allow_extra_args());
10399
10400 app->remove_option(opt);
10401 auto *opt2 = app->add_option(option_copy->get_name(false, true), "option has been retired and has no effect");
10402 opt2->type_name("RETIRED")
10403 ->default_str("RETIRED")
10404 ->type_size(option_copy->get_type_size_min(), option_copy->get_type_size_max())
10405 ->expected(option_copy->get_expected_min(), option_copy->get_expected_max())
10406 ->allow_extra_args(option_copy->get_allow_extra_args());
10407
10408 // LCOV_EXCL_START
10409 // something odd with coverage on new compilers
10410 Validator retired_warning{[opt2](std::string &) {
10411 std::cout << "WARNING " << opt2->get_name() << " is retired and has no effect\n";
10412 return std::string();
10413 },
10414 ""};
10415 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
10416 retired_warning.application_index(0);
10417 opt2->check(retired_warning);
10418}
10419
10420CLI11_INLINE void retire_option(App &app, Option *opt) { retire_option(&app, opt); }
10421
10422CLI11_INLINE void retire_option(App *app, const std::string &option_name) {
10423
10424 auto *opt = app->get_option_no_throw(option_name);
10425 if(opt != nullptr) {
10426 retire_option(app, opt);
10427 return;
10428 }
10429 auto *opt2 = app->add_option(option_name, "option has been retired and has no effect")
10430 ->type_name("RETIRED")
10431 ->expected(0, 1)
10432 ->default_str("RETIRED");
10433 // LCOV_EXCL_START
10434 // something odd with coverage on new compilers
10435 Validator retired_warning{[opt2](std::string &) {
10436 std::cout << "WARNING " << opt2->get_name() << " is retired and has no effect\n";
10437 return std::string();
10438 },
10439 ""};
10440 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
10441 retired_warning.application_index(0);
10442 opt2->check(retired_warning);
10443}
10444
10445CLI11_INLINE void retire_option(App &app, const std::string &option_name) { retire_option(&app, option_name); }

10447namespace FailureMessage {
10448
10449CLI11_INLINE std::string simple(const App *app, const Error &e) {
10450 std::string header = std::string(e.what()) + "\n";
10451 std::vector<std::string> names;
10452
10453 // Collect names
10454 if(app->get_help_ptr() != nullptr)
10455 names.push_back(app->get_help_ptr()->get_name());
10456
10457 if(app->get_help_all_ptr() != nullptr)
10458 names.push_back(app->get_help_all_ptr()->get_name());
10459
10460 // If any names found, suggest those
10461 if(!names.empty())
10462 header += "Run with " + detail::join(names, " or ") + " for more information.\n";
10463
10464 return header;
10465}
10466
10467CLI11_INLINE std::string help(const App *app, const Error &e) {
10468 std::string header = std::string("ERROR: ") + e.get_name() + ": " + e.what() + "\n";
10469 header += app->help();
10470 return header;
10471}

10504static constexpr auto multiline_literal_quote = R"(''')";
10505static constexpr auto multiline_string_quote = R"(""")";
