10507namespace detail {
10508
10509CLI11_INLINE bool is_printable(const std::string &test_string) {
10510 return std::all_of(test_string.begin(), test_string.end(), [](char x) {
10511 return (isprint(static_cast<unsigned char>(x)) != 0 || x == '\n' || x == '\t');
10512 });
10513}
10514
10515CLI11_INLINE std::string
10516convert_arg_for_ini(const std::string &arg, char stringQuote, char literalQuote, bool disable_multi_line) {
10517 if(arg.empty()) {
10518 return std::string(2, stringQuote);
10519 }
10520 // some specifically supported strings
10521 if(arg == "true" || arg == "false" || arg == "nan" || arg == "inf") {
10522 return arg;
10523 }
10524 // floating point conversion can convert some hex codes, but don't try that here
10525 if(arg.compare(0, 2, "0x") != 0 && arg.compare(0, 2, "0X") != 0) {
10526 using CLI::detail::lexical_cast;
10527 double val = 0.0;
10528 if(lexical_cast(arg, val)) {
10529 if(arg.find_first_not_of("0123456789.-+eE") == std::string::npos) {
10530 return arg;
10531 }
10532 }
10533 }
10534 // just quote a single non numeric character
10535 if(arg.size() == 1) {
10536 if(isprint(static_cast<unsigned char>(arg.front())) == 0) {
10537 return binary_escape_string(arg);
10538 }
10539 if(arg == "'") {
10540 return std::string(1, stringQuote) + "'" + stringQuote;
10541 }
10542 return std::string(1, literalQuote) + arg + literalQuote;
10543 }
10544 // handle hex, binary or octal arguments
10545 if(arg.front() == '0') {
10546 if(arg[1] == 'x') {
10547 if(std::all_of(arg.begin() + 2, arg.end(), [](char x) {
10548 return (x >= '0' && x <= '9') || (x >= 'A' && x <= 'F') || (x >= 'a' && x <= 'f');
10549 })) {
10550 return arg;
10551 }
10552 } else if(arg[1] == 'o') {
10553 if(std::all_of(arg.begin() + 2, arg.end(), [](char x) { return (x >= '0' && x <= '7'); })) {
10554 return arg;
10555 }
10556 } else if(arg[1] == 'b') {
10557 if(std::all_of(arg.begin() + 2, arg.end(), [](char x) { return (x == '0' || x == '1'); })) {
10558 return arg;
10559 }
10560 }
10561 }
10562 if(!is_printable(arg)) {
10563 return binary_escape_string(arg);
10564 }
10565 if(detail::has_escapable_character(arg)) {
10566 if(arg.size() > 100 && !disable_multi_line) {
10567 return std::string(multiline_literal_quote) + arg + multiline_literal_quote;
10568 }
10569 return std::string(1, stringQuote) + detail::add_escaped_characters(arg) + stringQuote;
10570 }
10571 return std::string(1, stringQuote) + arg + stringQuote;
10572}
10573
10574CLI11_INLINE std::string ini_join(const std::vector<std::string> &args,
10575 char sepChar,
10576 char arrayStart,
10577 char arrayEnd,
10578 char stringQuote,
10579 char literalQuote) {
10580 bool disable_multi_line{false};
10581 std::string joined;
10582 if(args.size() > 1 && arrayStart != '\0') {
10583 joined.push_back(arrayStart);
10584 disable_multi_line = true;
10585 }
10586 std::size_t start = 0;
10587 for(const auto &arg : args) {
10588 if(start++ > 0) {
10589 joined.push_back(sepChar);
10590 if(!std::isspace<char>(sepChar, std::locale())) {
10591 joined.push_back(' ');
10592 }
10593 }
10594 joined.append(convert_arg_for_ini(arg, stringQuote, literalQuote, disable_multi_line));
10595 }
10596 if(args.size() > 1 && arrayEnd != '\0') {
10597 joined.push_back(arrayEnd);
10598 }
10599 return joined;
10600}
10601
10602CLI11_INLINE std::vector<std::string>
10603generate_parents(const std::string &section, std::string &name, char parentSeparator) {
10604 std::vector<std::string> parents;
10605 if(detail::to_lower(section) != "default") {
10606 if(section.find(parentSeparator) != std::string::npos) {
10607 parents = detail::split_up(section, parentSeparator);
10608 } else {
10609 parents = {section};
10610 }
10611 }
10612 if(name.find(parentSeparator) != std::string::npos) {
10613 std::vector<std::string> plist = detail::split_up(name, parentSeparator);
10614 name = plist.back();
10615 plist.pop_back();
10616 parents.insert(parents.end(), plist.begin(), plist.end());
10617 }
10618 // clean up quotes on the parents
10619 try {
10620 detail::remove_quotes(parents);
10621 } catch(const std::invalid_argument &iarg) {
10622 throw CLI::ParseError(iarg.what(), CLI::ExitCodes::InvalidError);
10623 }
10624 return parents;
10625}
10626
10627CLI11_INLINE void
10628checkParentSegments(std::vector<ConfigItem> &output, const std::string &currentSection, char parentSeparator) {
10629
10630 std::string estring;
10631 auto parents = detail::generate_parents(currentSection, estring, parentSeparator);
10632 if(!output.empty() && output.back().name == "--") {
10633 std::size_t msize = (parents.size() > 1U) ? parents.size() : 2;
10634 while(output.back().parents.size() >= msize) {
10635 output.push_back(output.back());
10636 output.back().parents.pop_back();
10637 }
10638
10639 if(parents.size() > 1) {
10640 std::size_t common = 0;
10641 std::size_t mpair = (std::min)(output.back().parents.size(), parents.size() - 1);
10642 for(std::size_t ii = 0; ii < mpair; ++ii) {
10643 if(output.back().parents[ii] != parents[ii]) {
10644 break;
10645 }
10646 ++common;
10647 }
10648 if(common == mpair) {
10649 output.pop_back();
10650 } else {
10651 while(output.back().parents.size() > common + 1) {
10652 output.push_back(output.back());
10653 output.back().parents.pop_back();
10654 }
10655 }
10656 for(std::size_t ii = common; ii < parents.size() - 1; ++ii) {
10657 output.emplace_back();
10658 output.back().parents.assign(parents.begin(), parents.begin() + static_cast<std::ptrdiff_t>(ii) + 1);
10659 output.back().name = "++";
10660 }
10661 }
10662 } else if(parents.size() > 1) {
10663 for(std::size_t ii = 0; ii < parents.size() - 1; ++ii) {
10664 output.emplace_back();
10665 output.back().parents.assign(parents.begin(), parents.begin() + static_cast<std::ptrdiff_t>(ii) + 1);
10666 output.back().name = "++";
10667 }
10668 }
10669
10670 // insert a section end which is just an empty items_buffer
10671 output.emplace_back();
10672 output.back().parents = std::move(parents);
10673 output.back().name = "++";
10674}
10675
10677CLI11_INLINE bool hasMLString(std::string const &fullString, char check) {
10678 if(fullString.length() < 3) {
10679 return false;
10680 }
10681 auto it = fullString.rbegin();
10682 return (*it == check) && (*(it + 1) == check) && (*(it + 2) == check);
10683}
10684
10686inline auto find_matching_config(std::vector<ConfigItem> &items,
10687 const std::vector<std::string> &parents,
10688 const std::string &name,
10689 bool fullSearch) -> decltype(items.begin()) {
10690 if(items.empty()) {
10691 return items.end();
10692 }
10693 auto search = items.end() - 1;
10694 do {
10695 if(search->parents == parents && search->name == name) {
10696 return search;
10697 }
10698 if(search == items.begin()) {
10699 break;
10700 }
10701 --search;
10702 } while(fullSearch);
10703 return items.end();
10704}
10705} // namespace detail
10706
10707inline std::vector<ConfigItem> ConfigBase::from_config(std::istream &input) const {
10708 std::string line;
10709 std::string buffer;
10710 std::string currentSection = "default";
10711 std::string previousSection = "default";
10712 std::vector<ConfigItem> output;
10713 bool isDefaultArray = (arrayStart == '[' && arrayEnd == ']' && arraySeparator == ',');
10714 bool isINIArray = (arrayStart == '\0' || arrayStart == ' ') && arrayStart == arrayEnd;
10715 bool inSection{false};
10716 bool inMLineComment{false};
10717 bool inMLineValue{false};
10718
10719 char aStart = (isINIArray) ? '[' : arrayStart;
10720 char aEnd = (isINIArray) ? ']' : arrayEnd;
10721 char aSep = (isINIArray && arraySeparator == ' ') ? ',' : arraySeparator;
10722 int currentSectionIndex{0};
10723
10724 std::string line_sep_chars{parentSeparatorChar, commentChar, valueDelimiter};
10725 while(getline(input, buffer)) {
10726 std::vector<std::string> items_buffer;
10727 std::string name;
10728 line = detail::trim_copy(buffer);
10729 std::size_t len = line.length();
10730 // lines have to be at least 3 characters to have any meaning to CLI just skip the rest
10731 if(len < 3) {
10732 continue;
10733 }
10734 if(line.compare(0, 3, multiline_string_quote) == 0 || line.compare(0, 3, multiline_literal_quote) == 0) {
10735 inMLineComment = true;
10736 auto cchar = line.front();
10737 while(inMLineComment) {
10738 if(getline(input, line)) {
10739 detail::trim(line);
10740 } else {
10741 break;
10742 }
10743 if(detail::hasMLString(line, cchar)) {
10744 inMLineComment = false;
10745 }
10746 }
10747 continue;
10748 }
10749 if(line.front() == '[' && line.back() == ']') {
10750 if(currentSection != "default") {
10751 // insert a section end which is just an empty items_buffer
10752 output.emplace_back();
10753 output.back().parents = detail::generate_parents(currentSection, name, parentSeparatorChar);
10754 output.back().name = "--";
10755 }
10756 currentSection = line.substr(1, len - 2);
10757 // deal with double brackets for TOML
10758 if(currentSection.size() > 1 && currentSection.front() == '[' && currentSection.back() == ']') {
10759 currentSection = currentSection.substr(1, currentSection.size() - 2);
10760 }
10761 if(detail::to_lower(currentSection) == "default") {
10762 currentSection = "default";
10763 } else {
10764 detail::checkParentSegments(output, currentSection, parentSeparatorChar);
10765 }
10766 inSection = false;
10767 if(currentSection == previousSection) {
10768 ++currentSectionIndex;
10769 } else {
10770 currentSectionIndex = 0;
10771 previousSection = currentSection;
10772 }
10773 continue;
10774 }
10775
10776 // comment lines
10777 if(line.front() == ';' || line.front() == '#' || line.front() == commentChar) {
10778 continue;
10779 }
10780 std::size_t search_start = 0;
10781 if(line.find_first_of("\"'`") != std::string::npos) {
10782 while(search_start < line.size()) {
10783 auto test_char = line[search_start];
10784 if(test_char == '\"' || test_char == '\'' || test_char == '`') {
10785 search_start = detail::close_sequence(line, search_start, line[search_start]);
10786 ++search_start;
10787 } else if(test_char == valueDelimiter || test_char == commentChar) {
10788 --search_start;
10789 break;
10790 } else if(test_char == ' ' || test_char == '\t' || test_char == parentSeparatorChar) {
10791 ++search_start;
10792 } else {
10793 search_start = line.find_first_of(line_sep_chars, search_start);
10794 }
10795 }
10796 }
10797 // Find = in string, split and recombine
10798 auto delimiter_pos = line.find_first_of(valueDelimiter, search_start + 1);
10799 auto comment_pos = line.find_first_of(commentChar, search_start);
10800 if(comment_pos < delimiter_pos) {
10801 delimiter_pos = std::string::npos;
10802 }
10803 if(delimiter_pos != std::string::npos) {
10804
10805 name = detail::trim_copy(line.substr(0, delimiter_pos));
10806 std::string item = detail::trim_copy(line.substr(delimiter_pos + 1, std::string::npos));
10807 bool mlquote =
10808 (item.compare(0, 3, multiline_literal_quote) == 0 || item.compare(0, 3, multiline_string_quote) == 0);
10809 if(!mlquote && comment_pos != std::string::npos) {
10810 auto citems = detail::split_up(item, commentChar);
10811 item = detail::trim_copy(citems.front());
10812 }
10813 if(mlquote) {
10814 // multiline string
10815 auto keyChar = item.front();
10816 item = buffer.substr(delimiter_pos + 1, std::string::npos);
10817 detail::ltrim(item);
10818 item.erase(0, 3);
10819 inMLineValue = true;
10820 bool lineExtension{false};
10821 bool firstLine = true;
10822 if(!item.empty() && item.back() == '\\') {
10823 item.pop_back();
10824 lineExtension = true;
10825 } else if(detail::hasMLString(item, keyChar)) {
10826 // deal with the first line closing the multiline literal
10827 item.pop_back();
10828 item.pop_back();
10829 item.pop_back();
10830 if(keyChar == '\"') {
10831 try {
10832 item = detail::remove_escaped_characters(item);
10833 } catch(const std::invalid_argument &iarg) {
10834 throw CLI::ParseError(iarg.what(), CLI::ExitCodes::InvalidError);
10835 }
10836 }
10837 inMLineValue = false;
10838 }
10839 while(inMLineValue) {
10840 std::string l2;
10841 if(!std::getline(input, l2)) {
10842 break;
10843 }
10844 line = l2;
10845 detail::rtrim(line);
10846 if(detail::hasMLString(line, keyChar)) {
10847 line.pop_back();
10848 line.pop_back();
10849 line.pop_back();
10850 if(lineExtension) {
10851 detail::ltrim(line);
10852 } else if(!(firstLine && item.empty())) {
10853 item.push_back('\n');
10854 }
10855 firstLine = false;
10856 item += line;
10857 inMLineValue = false;
10858 if(!item.empty() && item.back() == '\n') {
10859 item.pop_back();
10860 }
10861 if(keyChar == '\"') {
10862 try {
10863 item = detail::remove_escaped_characters(item);
10864 } catch(const std::invalid_argument &iarg) {
10865 throw CLI::ParseError(iarg.what(), CLI::ExitCodes::InvalidError);
10866 }
10867 }
10868 } else {
10869 if(lineExtension) {
10870 detail::trim(l2);
10871 } else if(!(firstLine && item.empty())) {
10872 item.push_back('\n');
10873 }
10874 lineExtension = false;
10875 firstLine = false;
10876 if(!l2.empty() && l2.back() == '\\') {
10877 lineExtension = true;
10878 l2.pop_back();
10879 }
10880 item += l2;
10881 }
10882 }
10883 items_buffer = {item};
10884 } else if(item.size() > 1 && item.front() == aStart) {
10885 for(std::string multiline; item.back() != aEnd && std::getline(input, multiline);) {
10886 detail::trim(multiline);
10887 item += multiline;
10888 }
10889 if(item.back() == aEnd) {
10890 items_buffer = detail::split_up(item.substr(1, item.length() - 2), aSep);
10891 } else {
10892 items_buffer = detail::split_up(item.substr(1, std::string::npos), aSep);
10893 }
10894 } else if((isDefaultArray || isINIArray) && item.find_first_of(aSep) != std::string::npos) {
10895 items_buffer = detail::split_up(item, aSep);
10896 } else if((isDefaultArray || isINIArray) && item.find_first_of(' ') != std::string::npos) {
10897 items_buffer = detail::split_up(item, '\0');
10898 } else {
10899 items_buffer = {item};
10900 }
10901 } else {
10902 name = detail::trim_copy(line.substr(0, comment_pos));
10903 items_buffer = {"true"};
10904 }
10905 std::vector<std::string> parents;
10906 try {
10907 parents = detail::generate_parents(currentSection, name, parentSeparatorChar);
10908 detail::process_quoted_string(name);
10909 // clean up quotes on the items and check for escaped strings
10910 for(auto &it : items_buffer) {
10911 detail::process_quoted_string(it, stringQuote, literalQuote);
10912 }
10913 } catch(const std::invalid_argument &ia) {
10914 throw CLI::ParseError(ia.what(), CLI::ExitCodes::InvalidError);
10915 }
10916
10917 if(parents.size() > maximumLayers) {
10918 continue;
10919 }
10920 if(!configSection.empty() && !inSection) {
10921 if(parents.empty() || parents.front() != configSection) {
10922 continue;
10923 }
10924 if(configIndex >= 0 && currentSectionIndex != configIndex) {
10925 continue;
10926 }
10927 parents.erase(parents.begin());
10928 inSection = true;
10929 }
10930 auto match = detail::find_matching_config(output, parents, name, allowMultipleDuplicateFields);
10931 if(match != output.end()) {
10932 if((match->inputs.size() > 1 && items_buffer.size() > 1) || allowMultipleDuplicateFields) {
10933 // insert a separator if one is not already present
10934 if(!(match->inputs.back().empty() || items_buffer.front().empty() || match->inputs.back() == "%%" ||
10935 items_buffer.front() == "%%")) {
10936 match->inputs.emplace_back("%%");
10937 match->multiline = true;
10938 }
10939 }
10940 match->inputs.insert(match->inputs.end(), items_buffer.begin(), items_buffer.end());
10941 } else {
10942 output.emplace_back();
10943 output.back().parents = std::move(parents);
10944 output.back().name = std::move(name);
10945 output.back().inputs = std::move(items_buffer);
10946 }
10947 }
10948 if(currentSection != "default") {
10949 // insert a section end which is just an empty items_buffer
10950 std::string ename;
10951 output.emplace_back();
10952 output.back().parents = detail::generate_parents(currentSection, ename, parentSeparatorChar);
10953 output.back().name = "--";
10954 while(output.back().parents.size() > 1) {
10955 output.push_back(output.back());
10956 output.back().parents.pop_back();
10957 }
10958 }
10959 return output;
10960}
10961
10962CLI11_INLINE std::string &clean_name_string(std::string &name, const std::string &keyChars) {
10963 if(name.find_first_of(keyChars) != std::string::npos || (name.front() == '[' && name.back() == ']') ||
10964 (name.find_first_of("'`\"\\") != std::string::npos)) {
10965 if(name.find_first_of('\'') == std::string::npos) {
10966 name.insert(0, 1, '\'');
10967 name.push_back('\'');
10968 } else {
10969 if(detail::has_escapable_character(name)) {
10970 name = detail::add_escaped_characters(name);
10971 }
10972 name.insert(0, 1, '\"');
10973 name.push_back('\"');
10974 }
10975 }
10976 return name;
10977}
10978
10979CLI11_INLINE std::string
10980ConfigBase::to_config(const App *app, bool default_also, bool write_description, std::string prefix) const {
10981 std::stringstream out;
10982 std::string commentLead;
10983 commentLead.push_back(commentChar);
10984 commentLead.push_back(' ');
10985
10986 std::string commentTest = "#;";
10987 commentTest.push_back(commentChar);
10988 commentTest.push_back(parentSeparatorChar);
10989
10990 std::string keyChars = commentTest;
10991 keyChars.push_back(literalQuote);
10992 keyChars.push_back(stringQuote);
10993 keyChars.push_back(arrayStart);
10994 keyChars.push_back(arrayEnd);
10995 keyChars.push_back(valueDelimiter);
10996 keyChars.push_back(arraySeparator);
10997
10998 std::vector<std::string> groups = app->get_groups();
10999 bool defaultUsed = false;
11000 groups.insert(groups.begin(), std::string("OPTIONS"));
11001
11002 for(auto &group : groups) {
11003 if(group == "OPTIONS" || group.empty()) {
11004 if(defaultUsed) {
11005 continue;
11006 }
11007 defaultUsed = true;
11008 }
11009 if(write_description && group != "OPTIONS" && !group.empty()) {
11010 out << '\n' << commentChar << commentLead << group << " Options\n";
11011 }
11012 for(const Option *opt : app->get_options({})) {
11013 // Only process options that are configurable
11014 if(opt->get_configurable()) {
11015 if(opt->get_group() != group) {
11016 if(!(group == "OPTIONS" && opt->get_group().empty())) {
11017 continue;
11018 }
11019 }
11020 std::string single_name = opt->get_single_name();
11021 if(single_name.empty()) {
11022 continue;
11023 }
11024
11025 auto results = opt->reduced_results();
11026 std::string value =
11027 detail::ini_join(results, arraySeparator, arrayStart, arrayEnd, stringQuote, literalQuote);
11028
11029 bool isDefault = false;
11030 if(value.empty() && default_also) {
11031 if(!opt->get_default_str().empty()) {
11032 value = detail::convert_arg_for_ini(opt->get_default_str(), stringQuote, literalQuote, false);
11033 } else if(opt->get_expected_min() == 0) {
11034 value = "false";
11035 } else if(opt->get_run_callback_for_default() || !opt->get_required()) {
11036 value = "\"\""; // empty string default value
11037 } else {
11038 value = "\"<REQUIRED>\"";
11039 }
11040 isDefault = true;
11041 }
11042
11043 if(!value.empty()) {
11044 if(!opt->get_fnames().empty()) {
11045 try {
11046 value = opt->get_flag_value(single_name, value);
11047 } catch(const CLI::ArgumentMismatch &) {
11048 bool valid{false};
11049 for(const auto &test_name : opt->get_fnames()) {
11050 try {
11051 value = opt->get_flag_value(test_name, value);
11052 single_name = test_name;
11053 valid = true;
11054 } catch(const CLI::ArgumentMismatch &) {
11055 continue;
11056 }
11057 }
11058 if(!valid) {
11059 value = detail::ini_join(
11060 opt->results(), arraySeparator, arrayStart, arrayEnd, stringQuote, literalQuote);
11061 }
11062 }
11063 }
11064 if(write_description && opt->has_description()) {
11065 if(out.tellp() != std::streampos(0)) {
11066 out << '\n';
11067 }
11068 out << commentLead << detail::fix_newlines(commentLead, opt->get_description()) << '\n';
11069 }
11070 clean_name_string(single_name, keyChars);
11071
11072 std::string name = prefix + single_name;
11073 if(commentDefaultsBool && isDefault) {
11074 name = commentChar + name;
11075 }
11076 out << name << valueDelimiter << value << '\n';
11077 }
11078 }
11079 }
11080 }
11081
11082 auto subcommands = app->get_subcommands({});
11083 for(const App *subcom : subcommands) {
11084 if(subcom->get_name().empty()) {
11085 if(!default_also && (subcom->count_all() == 0)) {
11086 continue;
11087 }
11088 if(write_description && !subcom->get_group().empty()) {
11089 out << '\n' << commentLead << subcom->get_group() << " Options\n";
11090 }
11091 /*if (!prefix.empty() || app->get_parent() == nullptr) {
11092 out << '[' << prefix << "___"<< subcom->get_group() << "]\n";
11093 } else {
11094 std::string subname = app->get_name() + parentSeparatorChar + "___"+subcom->get_group();
11095 const auto *p = app->get_parent();
11096 while(p->get_parent() != nullptr) {
11097 subname = p->get_name() + parentSeparatorChar +subname;
11098 p = p->get_parent();
11099 }
11100 out << '[' << subname << "]\n";
11101 }
11102 */
11103 out << to_config(subcom, default_also, write_description, prefix);
11104 }
11105 }
11106
11107 for(const App *subcom : subcommands) {
11108 if(!subcom->get_name().empty()) {
11109 if(!default_also && (subcom->count_all() == 0)) {
11110 continue;
11111 }
11112 std::string subname = subcom->get_name();
11113 clean_name_string(subname, keyChars);
11114
11115 if(subcom->get_configurable() && (default_also || app->got_subcommand(subcom))) {
11116 if(!prefix.empty() || app->get_parent() == nullptr) {
11117
11118 out << '[' << prefix << subname << "]\n";
11119 } else {
11120 std::string appname = app->get_name();
11121 clean_name_string(appname, keyChars);
11122 subname = appname + parentSeparatorChar + subname;
11123 const auto *p = app->get_parent();
11124 while(p->get_parent() != nullptr) {
11125 std::string pname = p->get_name();
11126 clean_name_string(pname, keyChars);
11127 subname = pname + parentSeparatorChar + subname;
11128 p = p->get_parent();
11129 }
11130 out << '[' << subname << "]\n";
11131 }
11132 out << to_config(subcom, default_also, write_description, "");
11133 } else {
11134 out << to_config(subcom, default_also, write_description, prefix + subname + parentSeparatorChar);
11135 }
11136 }
11137 }
11138
11139 if(write_description && !out.str().empty()) {
11140 std::string outString =
11141 commentChar + commentLead + detail::fix_newlines(commentChar + commentLead, app->get_description()) + '\n';
11142 return outString + out.str();
11143 }
11144 return out.str();
11145}

11151
11152CLI11_INLINE std::string
11153Formatter::make_group(std::string group, bool is_positional, std::vector<const Option *> opts) const {
11154 std::stringstream out;
11155
11156 out << "\n" << group << ":\n";
11157 for(const Option *opt : opts) {
11158 out << make_option(opt, is_positional);
11159 }
11160
11161 return out.str();
11162}
11163
11164CLI11_INLINE std::string Formatter::make_positionals(const App *app) const {
11165 std::vector<const Option *> opts =
11166 app->get_options([](const Option *opt) { return !opt->get_group().empty() && opt->get_positional(); });
11167
11168 if(opts.empty())
11169 return {};
11170
11171 return make_group(get_label("POSITIONALS"), true, opts);
11172}
11173
11174CLI11_INLINE std::string Formatter::make_groups(const App *app, AppFormatMode mode) const {
11175 std::stringstream out;
11176 std::vector<std::string> groups = app->get_groups();
11177
11178 // Options
11179 for(const std::string &group : groups) {
11180 std::vector<const Option *> opts = app->get_options([app, mode, &group](const Option *opt) {
11181 return opt->get_group() == group // Must be in the right group
11182 && opt->nonpositional() // Must not be a positional
11183 && (mode != AppFormatMode::Sub // If mode is Sub, then
11184 || (app->get_help_ptr() != opt // Ignore help pointer
11185 && app->get_help_all_ptr() != opt)); // Ignore help all pointer
11186 });
11187 if(!group.empty() && !opts.empty()) {
11188 out << make_group(group, false, opts);
11189
11190 // Removed double newline between groups for consistency of help text
11191 // if(group != groups.back())
11192 // out << "\n";
11193 }
11194 }
11195
11196 return out.str();
11197}
11198
11199CLI11_INLINE std::string Formatter::make_description(const App *app) const {
11200 std::string desc = app->get_description();
11201 auto min_options = app->get_require_option_min();
11202 auto max_options = app->get_require_option_max();
11203
11204 if(app->get_required()) {
11205 desc += " " + get_label("REQUIRED") + " ";
11206 }
11207
11208 if(min_options > 0) {
11209 if(max_options == min_options) {
11210 desc += " \n[Exactly " + std::to_string(min_options) + " of the following options are required]";
11211 } else if(max_options > 0) {
11212 desc += " \n[Between " + std::to_string(min_options) + " and " + std::to_string(max_options) +
11213 " of the following options are required]";
11214 } else {
11215 desc += " \n[At least " + std::to_string(min_options) + " of the following options are required]";
11216 }
11217 } else if(max_options > 0) {
11218 desc += " \n[At most " + std::to_string(max_options) + " of the following options are allowed]";
11219 }
11220
11221 return (!desc.empty()) ? desc + "\n\n" : std::string{};
11222}
11223
11224CLI11_INLINE std::string Formatter::make_usage(const App *app, std::string name) const {
11225 std::string usage = app->get_usage();
11226 if(!usage.empty()) {
11227 return usage + "\n\n";
11228 }
11229
11230 std::stringstream out;
11231 out << '\n';
11232
11233 if(name.empty())
11234 out << get_label("Usage") << ':';
11235 else
11236 out << name;
11237
11238 std::vector<std::string> groups = app->get_groups();
11239
11240 // Print an Options badge if any options exist
11241 std::vector<const Option *> non_pos_options =
11242 app->get_options([](const Option *opt) { return opt->nonpositional(); });
11243 if(!non_pos_options.empty())
11244 out << " [" << get_label("OPTIONS") << "]";
11245
11246 // Positionals need to be listed here
11247 std::vector<const Option *> positionals = app->get_options([](const Option *opt) { return opt->get_positional(); });
11248
11249 // Print out positionals if any are left
11250 if(!positionals.empty()) {
11251 // Convert to help names
11252 std::vector<std::string> positional_names(positionals.size());
11253 std::transform(positionals.begin(), positionals.end(), positional_names.begin(), [this](const Option *opt) {
11254 return make_option_usage(opt);
11255 });
11256
11257 out << " " << detail::join(positional_names, " ");
11258 }
11259
11260 // Add a marker if subcommands are expected or optional
11261 if(!app->get_subcommands(
11262 [](const CLI::App *subc) { return ((!subc->get_disabled()) && (!subc->get_name().empty())); })
11263 .empty()) {
11264 out << ' ' << (app->get_require_subcommand_min() == 0 ? "[" : "")
11265 << get_label(app->get_require_subcommand_max() < 2 || app->get_require_subcommand_min() > 1 ? "SUBCOMMAND"
11266 : "SUBCOMMANDS")
11267 << (app->get_require_subcommand_min() == 0 ? "]" : "");
11268 }
11269
11270 out << "\n\n";
11271
11272 return out.str();
11273}
11274
11275CLI11_INLINE std::string Formatter::make_footer(const App *app) const {
11276 std::string footer = app->get_footer();
11277 if(footer.empty()) {
11278 return std::string{};
11279 }
11280 return '\n' + footer + "\n\n";
11281}
11282
11283CLI11_INLINE std::string Formatter::make_help(const App *app, std::string name, AppFormatMode mode) const {
11284 // This immediately forwards to the make_expanded method. This is done this way so that subcommands can
11285 // have overridden formatters
11286 if(mode == AppFormatMode::Sub)
11287 return make_expanded(app, mode);
11288
11289 std::stringstream out;
11290 if((app->get_name().empty()) && (app->get_parent() != nullptr)) {
11291 if(app->get_group() != "SUBCOMMANDS") {
11292 out << app->get_group() << ':';
11293 }
11294 }
11295
11296 detail::streamOutAsParagraph(
11297 out, make_description(app), description_paragraph_width_, ""); // Format description as paragraph
11298 out << make_usage(app, name);
11299 out << make_positionals(app);
11300 out << make_groups(app, mode);
11301 out << make_subcommands(app, mode);
11302 detail::streamOutAsParagraph(out, make_footer(app), footer_paragraph_width_); // Format footer as paragraph
11303
11304 return out.str();
11305}
11306
11307CLI11_INLINE std::string Formatter::make_subcommands(const App *app, AppFormatMode mode) const {
11308 std::stringstream out;
11309
11310 std::vector<const App *> subcommands = app->get_subcommands({});
11311
11312 // Make a list in definition order of the groups seen
11313 std::vector<std::string> subcmd_groups_seen;
11314 for(const App *com : subcommands) {
11315 if(com->get_name().empty()) {
11316 if(!com->get_group().empty() && com->get_group().front() != '+') {
11317 out << make_expanded(com, mode);
11318 }
11319 continue;
11320 }
11321 std::string group_key = com->get_group();
11322 if(!group_key.empty() &&
11323 std::find_if(subcmd_groups_seen.begin(), subcmd_groups_seen.end(), [&group_key](std::string a) {
11324 return detail::to_lower(a) == detail::to_lower(group_key);
11325 }) == subcmd_groups_seen.end())
11326 subcmd_groups_seen.push_back(group_key);
11327 }
11328
11329 // For each group, filter out and print subcommands
11330 for(const std::string &group : subcmd_groups_seen) {
11331 out << '\n' << group << ":\n";
11332 std::vector<const App *> subcommands_group = app->get_subcommands(
11333 [&group](const App *sub_app) { return detail::to_lower(sub_app->get_group()) == detail::to_lower(group); });
11334 for(const App *new_com : subcommands_group) {
11335 if(new_com->get_name().empty())
11336 continue;
11337 if(mode != AppFormatMode::All) {
11338 out << make_subcommand(new_com);
11339 } else {
11340 out << new_com->help(new_com->get_name(), AppFormatMode::Sub);
11341 out << '\n';
11342 }
11343 }
11344 }
11345
11346 return out.str();
11347}
11348
11349CLI11_INLINE std::string Formatter::make_subcommand(const App *sub) const {
11350 std::stringstream out;
11351 std::string name = " " + sub->get_display_name(true) + (sub->get_required() ? " " + get_label("REQUIRED") : "");
11352
11353 out << std::setw(static_cast<int>(column_width_)) << std::left << name;
11354 detail::streamOutAsParagraph(
11355 out, sub->get_description(), right_column_width_, std::string(column_width_, ' '), true);
11356 out << '\n';
11357 return out.str();
11358}
11359
11360CLI11_INLINE std::string Formatter::make_expanded(const App *sub, AppFormatMode mode) const {
11361 std::stringstream out;
11362 out << sub->get_display_name(true) << '\n';
11363
11364 detail::streamOutAsParagraph(
11365 out, make_description(sub), description_paragraph_width_, " "); // Format description as paragraph
11366
11367 if(sub->get_name().empty() && !sub->get_aliases().empty()) {
11368 detail::format_aliases(out, sub->get_aliases(), column_width_ + 2);
11369 }
11370
11371 out << make_positionals(sub);
11372 out << make_groups(sub, mode);
11373 out << make_subcommands(sub, mode);
11374 detail::streamOutAsParagraph(out, make_footer(sub), footer_paragraph_width_); // Format footer as paragraph
11375
11376 out << '\n';
11377 return out.str();
11378}
11379
11380CLI11_INLINE std::string Formatter::make_option(const Option *opt, bool is_positional) const {
11381 std::stringstream out;
11382 if(is_positional) {
11383 const std::string left = " " + make_option_name(opt, true) + make_option_opts(opt);
11384 const std::string desc = make_option_desc(opt);
11385 out << std::setw(static_cast<int>(column_width_)) << std::left << left;
11386
11387 if(!desc.empty()) {
11388 bool skipFirstLinePrefix = true;
11389 if(left.length() >= column_width_) {
11390 out << '\n';
11391 skipFirstLinePrefix = false;
11392 }
11393 detail::streamOutAsParagraph(
11394 out, desc, right_column_width_, std::string(column_width_, ' '), skipFirstLinePrefix);
11395 }
11396 } else {
11397 const std::string namesCombined = make_option_name(opt, false);
11398 const std::string opts = make_option_opts(opt);
11399 const std::string desc = make_option_desc(opt);
11400
11401 // Split all names at comma and sort them into short names and long names
11402 const auto names = detail::split(namesCombined, ',');
11403 std::vector<std::string> vshortNames;
11404 std::vector<std::string> vlongNames;
11405 std::for_each(names.begin(), names.end(), [&vshortNames, &vlongNames](const std::string &name) {
11406 if(name.find("--", 0) != std::string::npos)
11407 vlongNames.push_back(name);
11408 else
11409 vshortNames.push_back(name);
11410 });
11411
11412 // Assemble short and long names
11413 std::string shortNames = detail::join(vshortNames, ", ");
11414 std::string longNames = detail::join(vlongNames, ", ");
11415
11416 // Calculate setw sizes
11417 const auto shortNamesColumnWidth = static_cast<int>(column_width_ / 3); // 33% left for short names
11418 const auto longNamesColumnWidth = static_cast<int>(std::ceil(
11419 static_cast<float>(column_width_) / 3.0f * 2.0f)); // 66% right for long names and options, ceil result
11420 int shortNamesOverSize = 0;
11421
11422 // Print short names
11423 if(shortNames.length() > 0) {
11424 shortNames = " " + shortNames; // Indent
11425 if(longNames.length() == 0 && opts.length() > 0)
11426 shortNames += opts; // Add opts if only short names and no long names
11427 if(longNames.length() > 0)
11428 shortNames += ",";
11429 if(static_cast<int>(shortNames.length()) >= shortNamesColumnWidth) {
11430 shortNames += " ";
11431 shortNamesOverSize = static_cast<int>(shortNames.length()) - shortNamesColumnWidth;
11432 }
11433 out << std::setw(shortNamesColumnWidth) << std::left << shortNames;
11434 } else {
11435 out << std::setw(shortNamesColumnWidth) << std::left << "";
11436 }
11437
11438 // Adjust long name column width in case of short names column reaching into long names column
11439 shortNamesOverSize =
11440 (std::min)(shortNamesOverSize, longNamesColumnWidth); // Prevent negative result with unsigned integers
11441 const auto adjustedLongNamesColumnWidth = longNamesColumnWidth - shortNamesOverSize;
11442
11443 // Print long names
11444 if(longNames.length() > 0) {
11445 if(opts.length() > 0)
11446 longNames += opts;
11447 if(static_cast<int>(longNames.length()) >= adjustedLongNamesColumnWidth)
11448 longNames += " ";
11449
11450 out << std::setw(adjustedLongNamesColumnWidth) << std::left << longNames;
11451 } else {
11452 out << std::setw(adjustedLongNamesColumnWidth) << std::left << "";
11453 }
11454
11455 if(!desc.empty()) {
11456 bool skipFirstLinePrefix = true;
11457 if(out.str().length() > column_width_) {
11458 out << '\n';
11459 skipFirstLinePrefix = false;
11460 }
11461 detail::streamOutAsParagraph(
11462 out, desc, right_column_width_, std::string(column_width_, ' '), skipFirstLinePrefix);
11463 }
11464 }
11465
11466 out << '\n';
11467 return out.str();
11468}
11469
11470CLI11_INLINE std::string Formatter::make_option_name(const Option *opt, bool is_positional) const {
11471 if(is_positional)
11472 return opt->get_name(true, false);
11473
11474 return opt->get_name(false, true);
11475}
11476
11477CLI11_INLINE std::string Formatter::make_option_opts(const Option *opt) const {
11478 std::stringstream out;
11479
11480 if(!opt->get_option_text().empty()) {
11481 out << " " << opt->get_option_text();
11482 } else {
11483 if(opt->get_type_size() != 0) {
11484 if(!opt->get_type_name().empty())
11485 out << " " << get_label(opt->get_type_name());
11486 if(!opt->get_default_str().empty())
11487 out << " [" << opt->get_default_str() << "] ";
11488 if(opt->get_expected_max() == detail::expected_max_vector_size)
11489 out << " ...";
11490 else if(opt->get_expected_min() > 1)
11491 out << " x " << opt->get_expected();
11492
11493 if(opt->get_required())
11494 out << " " << get_label("REQUIRED");
11495 }
11496 if(!opt->get_envname().empty())
11497 out << " (" << get_label("Env") << ":" << opt->get_envname() << ")";
11498 if(!opt->get_needs().empty()) {
11499 out << " " << get_label("Needs") << ":";
11500 for(const Option *op : opt->get_needs())
11501 out << " " << op->get_name();
11502 }
11503 if(!opt->get_excludes().empty()) {
11504 out << " " << get_label("Excludes") << ":";
11505 for(const Option *op : opt->get_excludes())
11506 out << " " << op->get_name();
11507 }
11508 }
11509 return out.str();
11510}
11511
11512CLI11_INLINE std::string Formatter::make_option_desc(const Option *opt) const { return opt->get_description(); }
11513
11514CLI11_INLINE std::string Formatter::make_option_usage(const Option *opt) const {
11515 // Note that these are positionals usages
11516 std::stringstream out;
11517 out << make_option_name(opt, true);
11518 if(opt->get_expected_max() >= detail::expected_max_vector_size)
11519 out << "...";
11520 else if(opt->get_expected_max() > 1)
11521 out << "(" << opt->get_expected() << "x)";
11522
11523 return opt->get_required() ? out.str() : "[" + out.str() + "]";
11524}
